5189 int i;
5190
5191 /* No TCs or already enabled TCs just return */
5192 if (!enabled_tc || veb->enabled_tc == enabled_tc)
5193 return ret;
5194
5195 bw_data.tc_valid_bits = enabled_tc;
5196 /* bw_data.absolute_credits is not set (relative) */
5197
5198 /* Enable ETS TCs with equal BW Share for now */
5199 for (i = 0; i < I40E_MAX_TRAFFIC_CLASS; i++) {
5200 if (enabled_tc & BIT(i))
5201 bw_data.tc_bw_share_credits[i] = 1;
5202 }
5203
5204 ret = i40e_aq_config_switch_comp_bw_config(&pf->hw, veb->seid,
5205 &bw_data, NULL);
5206 if (ret) {
5207 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
5208 "VEB bw config failed, err %s aq_err %s\n",
5209 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
5210 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw, pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
5211 goto out;
5212 }
5213
5214 /* Update the BW information */
5215 ret = i40e_veb_get_bw_info(veb);
5216 if (ret) {
5217 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
5218 "Failed getting veb bw config, err %s aq_err %s\n",
5219 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
5220 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw, pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
5221 }
5222
5223out:
5224 return ret;
5225}
5226
5227#ifdef CONFIG_I40E_DCB
5228/**
5229 * i40e_dcb_reconfigure - Reconfigure all VEBs and VSIs
5230 * @pf: PF struct
5231 *
5232 * Reconfigure VEB/VSIs on a given PF; it is assumed that
5233 * the caller would've quiesce all the VSIs before calling
5234 * this function
5235 **/
5236static void i40e_dcb_reconfigure(struct i40e_pf *pf)
5237{
5238 u8 tc_map = 0;
5239 int ret;
5240 u8 v;
5241
5242 /* Enable the TCs available on PF to all VEBs */
5243 tc_map = i40e_pf_get_tc_map(pf);
5244 for (v = 0; v < I40E_MAX_VEB; v++) {
5245 if (!pf->veb[v])
5246 continue;
5247 ret = i40e_veb_config_tc(pf->veb[v], tc_map);
5248 if (ret) {
5249 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
5250 "Failed configuring TC for VEB seid=%d\n",
5251 pf->veb[v]->seid);
5252 /* Will try to configure as many components */
5253 }
5254 }
5255
5256 /* Update each VSI */
5257 for (v = 0; v < pf->num_alloc_vsi; v++) {
5258 if (!pf->vsi[v])
5259 continue;
5260
5261 /* - Enable all TCs for the LAN VSI
5262 * - For all others keep them at TC0 for now
5263 */
5264 if (v == pf->lan_vsi)
5265 tc_map = i40e_pf_get_tc_map(pf);
5266 else
5267 tc_map = I40E_DEFAULT_TRAFFIC_CLASS;
5268
5269 ret = i40e_vsi_config_tc(pf->vsi[v], tc_map);
5270 if (ret) {
5271 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
5272 "Failed configuring TC for VSI seid=%d\n",
5273 pf->vsi[v]->seid);
5274 /* Will try to configure as many components */
5275 } else {
5276 /* Re-configure VSI vectors based on updated TC map */
5277 i40e_vsi_map_rings_to_vectors(pf->vsi[v]);
5278 if (pf->vsi[v]->netdev)
5279 i40e_dcbnl_set_all(pf->vsi[v]);
5280 }
5281 }
5282}
5283
5284/**
5285 * i40e_resume_port_tx - Resume port Tx
5286 * @pf: PF struct
5287 *
5288 * Resume a port's Tx and issue a PF reset in case of failure to
5289 * resume.
5290 **/
5291static int i40e_resume_port_tx(struct i40e_pf *pf)
5292{
5293 struct i40e_hw *hw = &pf->hw;
5294 int ret;
5295
5296 ret = i40e_aq_resume_port_tx(hw, NULL);
5297 if (ret) {
5298 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
5299 "Resume Port Tx failed, err %s aq_err %s\n",
5300 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
5301 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw, pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
5302 /* Schedule PF reset to recover */
5303 set_bit(__I40E_PF_RESET_REQUESTED, pf->state);
5304 i40e_service_event_schedule(pf);
5305 }
5306
5307 return ret;
5308}
5309
5310/**
5311 * i40e_init_pf_dcb - Initialize DCB configuration
5312 * @pf: PF being configured
5313 *
5314 * Query the current DCB configuration and cache it
5315 * in the hardware structure
5316 **/
5317static int i40e_init_pf_dcb(struct i40e_pf *pf)
5318{
5319 struct i40e_hw *hw = &pf->hw;
5320 int err = 0;
5321
5322 /* Do not enable DCB for SW1 and SW2 images even if the FW is capable */
5323 if (pf->hw_features & I40E_HW_NO_DCB_SUPPORT)
5324 goto out;
5325
5326 /* Get the initial DCB configuration */
5327 err = i40e_init_dcb(hw);
5328 if (!err) {
5329 /* Device/Function is not DCBX capable */
5330 if ((!hw->func_caps.dcb) ||
5331 (hw->dcbx_status == I40E_DCBX_STATUS_DISABLED)) {
5332 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
5333 "DCBX offload is not supported or is disabled for this PF.\n");
5334 } else {
5335 /* When status is not DISABLED then DCBX in FW */
5336 pf->dcbx_cap = DCB_CAP_DCBX_LLD_MANAGED |
5337 DCB_CAP_DCBX_VER_IEEE;
5338
5339 pf->flags |= I40E_FLAG_DCB_CAPABLE;
5340 /* Enable DCB tagging only when more than one TC
5341 * or explicitly disable if only one TC
5342 */
5343 if (i40e_dcb_get_num_tc(&hw->local_dcbx_config) > 1)
5344 pf->flags |= I40E_FLAG_DCB_ENABLED;
5345 else
5346 pf->flags &= ~I40E_FLAG_DCB_ENABLED;
5347 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev,
5348 "DCBX offload is supported for this PF.\n");
5349 }
5350 } else {
5351 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
5352 "Query for DCB configuration failed, err %s aq_err %s\n",
5353 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, err),
5354 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw, pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
5355 }
5356
5357out:
5358 return err;
5359}
5360#endif /* CONFIG_I40E_DCB */
5361#define SPEED_SIZE 14
5362#define FC_SIZE 8
5363/**
5364 * i40e_print_link_message - print link up or down
5365 * @vsi: the VSI for which link needs a message
5366 */
5367void i40e_print_link_message(struct i40e_vsi *vsi, bool isup)
5368{
5369 enum i40e_aq_link_speed new_speed;
5370 char *speed = "Unknown";
5371 char *fc = "Unknown";
5372 char *fec = "";
5373 char *req_fec = "";
5374 char *an = "";
5375
5376 new_speed = vsi->back->hw.phy.link_info.link_speed;
5377
5378 if ((vsi->current_isup == isup) && (vsi->current_speed == new_speed))
5379 return;
5380 vsi->current_isup = isup;
5381 vsi->current_speed = new_speed;
5382 if (!isup) {
5383 netdev_info(vsi->netdev, "NIC Link is Down\n");
5384 return;
5385 }
5386
5387 /* Warn user if link speed on NPAR enabled partition is not at
5388 * least 10GB
5389 */
5390 if (vsi->back->hw.func_caps.npar_enable &&
5391 (vsi->back->hw.phy.link_info.link_speed == I40E_LINK_SPEED_1GB ||
5392 vsi->back->hw.phy.link_info.link_speed == I40E_LINK_SPEED_100MB))
5393 netdev_warn(vsi->netdev,
5394 "The partition detected link speed that is less than 10Gbps\n");
5395
5396 switch (vsi->back->hw.phy.link_info.link_speed) {
5397 case I40E_LINK_SPEED_40GB:
5398 speed = "40 G";
5399 break;
5400 case I40E_LINK_SPEED_20GB:
5401 speed = "20 G";
5402 break;
5403 case I40E_LINK_SPEED_25GB:
5404 speed = "25 G";
5405 break;
5406 case I40E_LINK_SPEED_10GB:
5407 speed = "10 G";
5408 break;
5409 case I40E_LINK_SPEED_1GB:
5410 speed = "1000 M";
5411 break;
5412 case I40E_LINK_SPEED_100MB:
5413 speed = "100 M";
5414 break;
5415 default:
5416 break;
5417 }
5418
5419 switch (vsi->back->hw.fc.current_mode) {
5420 case I40E_FC_FULL:
5421 fc = "RX/TX";
5422 break;
5423 case I40E_FC_TX_PAUSE:
5424 fc = "TX";
5425 break;
5426 case I40E_FC_RX_PAUSE:
5427 fc = "RX";
5428 break;
5429 default:
5430 fc = "None";
5431 break;
5432 }
5433
5434 if (vsi->back->hw.phy.link_info.link_speed == I40E_LINK_SPEED_25GB) {
5435 req_fec = ", Requested FEC: None";
5436 fec = ", FEC: None";
5437 an = ", Autoneg: False";
5438
5439 if (vsi->back->hw.phy.link_info.an_info & I40E_AQ_AN_COMPLETED)
5440 an = ", Autoneg: True";
5441
5442 if (vsi->back->hw.phy.link_info.fec_info &
5443 I40E_AQ_CONFIG_FEC_KR_ENA)
5444 fec = ", FEC: CL74 FC-FEC/BASE-R";
5445 else if (vsi->back->hw.phy.link_info.fec_info &
5446 I40E_AQ_CONFIG_FEC_RS_ENA)
5447 fec = ", FEC: CL108 RS-FEC";
5448
5449 /* 'CL108 RS-FEC' should be displayed when RS is requested, or
5450 * both RS and FC are requested
5451 */
5452 if (vsi->back->hw.phy.link_info.req_fec_info &
5453 (I40E_AQ_REQUEST_FEC_KR | I40E_AQ_REQUEST_FEC_RS)) {
5454 if (vsi->back->hw.phy.link_info.req_fec_info &
5455 I40E_AQ_REQUEST_FEC_RS)
5456 req_fec = ", Requested FEC: CL108 RS-FEC";
5457 else
5458 req_fec = ", Requested FEC: CL74 FC-FEC/BASE-R";
5459 }
5460 }
5461
5462 netdev_info(vsi->netdev, "NIC Link is Up, %sbps Full Duplex%s%s%s, Flow Control: %s\n",
5463 speed, req_fec, fec, an, fc);
5464}
5465
5466/**
5467 * i40e_up_complete - Finish the last steps of bringing up a connection
5468 * @vsi: the VSI being configured
5469 **/
5470static int i40e_up_complete(struct i40e_vsi *vsi)
5471{
5472 struct i40e_pf *pf = vsi->back;
5473 int err;
5474
5475 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_MSIX_ENABLED)
5476 i40e_vsi_configure_msix(vsi);
5477 else
5478 i40e_configure_msi_and_legacy(vsi);
5479
5480 /* start rings */
5481 err = i40e_vsi_start_rings(vsi);
5482 if (err)
5483 return err;
5484
5485 clear_bit(__I40E_VSI_DOWN, vsi->state);
5486 i40e_napi_enable_all(vsi);
5487 i40e_vsi_enable_irq(vsi);
5488
5489 if ((pf->hw.phy.link_info.link_info & I40E_AQ_LINK_UP) &&
5490 (vsi->netdev)) {
5491 i40e_print_link_message(vsi, true);
5492 netif_tx_start_all_queues(vsi->netdev);
5493 netif_carrier_on(vsi->netdev);
5494 } else if (vsi->netdev) {
5495 i40e_print_link_message(vsi, false);
5496 /* need to check for qualified module here*/
5497 if ((pf->hw.phy.link_info.link_info &
5498 I40E_AQ_MEDIA_AVAILABLE) &&
5499 (!(pf->hw.phy.link_info.an_info &
5500 I40E_AQ_QUALIFIED_MODULE)))
5501 netdev_err(vsi->netdev,
5502 "the driver failed to link because an unqualified module was detected.");
5503 }
5504
5505 /* replay FDIR SB filters */
5506 if (vsi->type == I40E_VSI_FDIR) {
5507 /* reset fd counters */
5508 pf->fd_add_err = 0;
5509 pf->fd_atr_cnt = 0;
5510 i40e_fdir_filter_restore(vsi);
5511 }
5512
5513 /* On the next run of the service_task, notify any clients of the new
5514 * opened netdev
5515 */
5516 pf->flags |= I40E_FLAG_SERVICE_CLIENT_REQUESTED;
5517 i40e_service_event_schedule(pf);
5518
5519 return 0;
5520}
5521
5522/**
5523 * i40e_vsi_reinit_locked - Reset the VSI
5524 * @vsi: the VSI being configured
5525 *
5526 * Rebuild the ring structs after some configuration
5527 * has changed, e.g. MTU size.
5528 **/
5529static void i40e_vsi_reinit_locked(struct i40e_vsi *vsi)
5530{
5531 struct i40e_pf *pf = vsi->back;
5532
5533 WARN_ON(in_interrupt());
5534 while (test_and_set_bit(__I40E_CONFIG_BUSY, pf->state))
5535 usleep_range(1000, 2000);
5536 i40e_down(vsi);
5537
5538 i40e_up(vsi);
5539 clear_bit(__I40E_CONFIG_BUSY, pf->state);
5540}
5541
5542/**
5543 * i40e_up - Bring the connection back up after being down
5544 * @vsi: the VSI being configured
5545 **/
5546int i40e_up(struct i40e_vsi *vsi)
5547{
5548 int err;
5549
5550 err = i40e_vsi_configure(vsi);
5551 if (!err)
5552 err = i40e_up_complete(vsi);
5553
5554 return err;
5555}
5556
5557/**
5558 * i40e_down - Shutdown the connection processing
5559 * @vsi: the VSI being stopped
5560 **/
5561void i40e_down(struct i40e_vsi *vsi)
5562{
5563 int i;
5564
5565 /* It is assumed that the caller of this function
5566 * sets the vsi->state __I40E_VSI_DOWN bit.
5567 */
5568 if (vsi->netdev) {
5569 netif_carrier_off(vsi->netdev);
5570 netif_tx_disable(vsi->netdev);
5571 }
5572 i40e_vsi_disable_irq(vsi);
5573 i40e_vsi_stop_rings(vsi);
5574 i40e_napi_disable_all(vsi);
5575
5576 for (i = 0; i < vsi->num_queue_pairs; i++) {
5577 i40e_clean_tx_ring(vsi->tx_rings[i]);
5578 if (i40e_enabled_xdp_vsi(vsi))
5579 i40e_clean_tx_ring(vsi->xdp_rings[i]);
5580 i40e_clean_rx_ring(vsi->rx_rings[i]);
5581 }
5582
5583}
5584
5585/**
5586 * i40e_setup_tc - configure multiple traffic classes
5587 * @netdev: net device to configure
5588 * @tc: number of traffic classes to enable
5589 **/
5590static int i40e_setup_tc(struct net_device *netdev, u8 tc)
5591{
5592 struct i40e_netdev_priv *np = netdev_priv(netdev);
5593 struct i40e_vsi *vsi = np->vsi;
5594 struct i40e_pf *pf = vsi->back;
5595 u8 enabled_tc = 0;
5596 int ret = -EINVAL;
5597 int i;
5598
5599 /* Check if DCB enabled to continue */
5600 if (!(pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_DCB_ENABLED)) {
5601 netdev_info(netdev, "DCB is not enabled for adapter\n");
5602 goto exit;
5603 }
5604
5605 /* Check if MFP enabled */
5606 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_MFP_ENABLED) {
5607 netdev_info(netdev, "Configuring TC not supported in MFP mode\n");
5608 goto exit;
5609 }
5610
5611 /* Check whether tc count is within enabled limit */
5612 if (tc > i40e_pf_get_num_tc(pf)) {
5613 netdev_info(netdev, "TC count greater than enabled on link for adapter\n");
5614 goto exit;
5615 }
5616
5617 /* Generate TC map for number of tc requested */
5618 for (i = 0; i < tc; i++)
5619 enabled_tc |= BIT(i);
5620
5621 /* Requesting same TC configuration as already enabled */
5622 if (enabled_tc == vsi->tc_config.enabled_tc)
5623 return 0;
5624
5625 /* Quiesce VSI queues */
5626 i40e_quiesce_vsi(vsi);
5627
5628 /* Configure VSI for enabled TCs */
5629 ret = i40e_vsi_config_tc(vsi, enabled_tc);
5630 if (ret) {
5631 netdev_info(netdev, "Failed configuring TC for VSI seid=%d\n",
5632 vsi->seid);
5633 goto exit;
5634 }
5635
5636 /* Unquiesce VSI */
5637 i40e_unquiesce_vsi(vsi);
5638
5639exit:
5640 return ret;
5641}
5642
5643static int __i40e_setup_tc(struct net_device *netdev, enum tc_setup_type type,
5644 void *type_data)
5645{
5646 struct tc_mqprio_qopt *mqprio = type_data;
5647
5648 if (type != TC_SETUP_MQPRIO)
5649 return -EOPNOTSUPP;
5650
5651 mqprio->hw = TC_MQPRIO_HW_OFFLOAD_TCS;
5652
5653 return i40e_setup_tc(netdev, mqprio->num_tc);
5654}
5655
5656/**
5657 * i40e_open - Called when a network interface is made active
5658 * @netdev: network interface device structure
5659 *
5660 * The open entry point is called when a network interface is made
5661 * active by the system (IFF_UP). At this point all resources needed
5662 * for transmit and receive operations are allocated, the interrupt
5663 * handler is registered with the OS, the netdev watchdog subtask is
5664 * enabled, and the stack is notified that the interface is ready.
5665 *
5666 * Returns 0 on success, negative value on failure
5667 **/
5668int i40e_open(struct net_device *netdev)
5669{
5670 struct i40e_netdev_priv *np = netdev_priv(netdev);
5671 struct i40e_vsi *vsi = np->vsi;
5672 struct i40e_pf *pf = vsi->back;
5673 int err;
5674
5675 /* disallow open during test or if eeprom is broken */
5676 if (test_bit(__I40E_TESTING, pf->state) ||
5677 test_bit(__I40E_BAD_EEPROM, pf->state))
5678 return -EBUSY;
5679
5680 netif_carrier_off(netdev);
5681
5682 err = i40e_vsi_open(vsi);
5683 if (err)
5684 return err;
5685
5686 /* configure global TSO hardware offload settings */
5687 wr32(&pf->hw, I40E_GLLAN_TSOMSK_F, be32_to_cpu(TCP_FLAG_PSH |
5688 TCP_FLAG_FIN) >> 16);
5689 wr32(&pf->hw, I40E_GLLAN_TSOMSK_M, be32_to_cpu(TCP_FLAG_PSH |
5690 TCP_FLAG_FIN |
5691 TCP_FLAG_CWR) >> 16);
5692 wr32(&pf->hw, I40E_GLLAN_TSOMSK_L, be32_to_cpu(TCP_FLAG_CWR) >> 16);
5693
5694 udp_tunnel_get_rx_info(netdev);
5695
5696 return 0;
5697}
5698
5699/**
5700 * i40e_vsi_open -
5701 * @vsi: the VSI to open
5702 *
5703 * Finish initialization of the VSI.
5704 *
5705 * Returns 0 on success, negative value on failure
5706 *
5707 * Note: expects to be called while under rtnl_lock()
5708 **/
5709int i40e_vsi_open(struct i40e_vsi *vsi)
5710{
5711 struct i40e_pf *pf = vsi->back;
5712 char int_name[I40E_INT_NAME_STR_LEN];
5713 int err;
5714
5715 /* allocate descriptors */
5716 err = i40e_vsi_setup_tx_resources(vsi);
5717 if (err)
5718 goto err_setup_tx;
5719 err = i40e_vsi_setup_rx_resources(vsi);
5720 if (err)
5721 goto err_setup_rx;
5722
5723 err = i40e_vsi_configure(vsi);
5724 if (err)
5725 goto err_setup_rx;
5726
5727 if (vsi->netdev) {
5728 snprintf(int_name, sizeof(int_name) - 1, "%s-%s",
5729 dev_driver_string(&pf->pdev->dev), vsi->netdev->name);
5730 err = i40e_vsi_request_irq(vsi, int_name);
5731 if (err)
5732 goto err_setup_rx;
5733
5734 /* Notify the stack of the actual queue counts. */
5735 err = netif_set_real_num_tx_queues(vsi->netdev,
5736 vsi->num_queue_pairs);
5737 if (err)
5738 goto err_set_queues;
5739
5740 err = netif_set_real_num_rx_queues(vsi->netdev,
5741 vsi->num_queue_pairs);
5742 if (err)
5743 goto err_set_queues;
5744
5745 } else if (vsi->type == I40E_VSI_FDIR) {
5746 snprintf(int_name, sizeof(int_name) - 1, "%s-%s:fdir",
5747 dev_driver_string(&pf->pdev->dev),
5748 dev_name(&pf->pdev->dev));
5749 err = i40e_vsi_request_irq(vsi, int_name);
5750
5751 } else {
5752 err = -EINVAL;
5753 goto err_setup_rx;
5754 }
5755
5756 err = i40e_up_complete(vsi);
5757 if (err)
5758 goto err_up_complete;
5759
5760 return 0;
5761
5762err_up_complete:
5763 i40e_down(vsi);
5764err_set_queues:
5765 i40e_vsi_free_irq(vsi);
5766err_setup_rx:
5767 i40e_vsi_free_rx_resources(vsi);
5768err_setup_tx:
5769 i40e_vsi_free_tx_resources(vsi);
5770 if (vsi == pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi])
5771 i40e_do_reset(pf, BIT_ULL(__I40E_PF_RESET_REQUESTED), true);
5772
5773 return err;
5774}
5775
5776/**
5777 * i40e_fdir_filter_exit - Cleans up the Flow Director accounting
5778 * @pf: Pointer to PF
5779 *
5780 * This function destroys the hlist where all the Flow Director
5781 * filters were saved.
5782 **/
5783static void i40e_fdir_filter_exit(struct i40e_pf *pf)
5784{
5785 struct i40e_fdir_filter *filter;
5786 struct i40e_flex_pit *pit_entry, *tmp;
5787 struct hlist_node *node2;
5788
5789 hlist_for_each_entry_safe(filter, node2,
5790 &pf->fdir_filter_list, fdir_node) {
5791 hlist_del(&filter->fdir_node);
5792 kfree(filter);
5793 }
5794
5795 list_for_each_entry_safe(pit_entry, tmp, &pf->l3_flex_pit_list, list) {
5796 list_del(&pit_entry->list);
5797 kfree(pit_entry);
5798 }
5799 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&pf->l3_flex_pit_list);
5800
5801 list_for_each_entry_safe(pit_entry, tmp, &pf->l4_flex_pit_list, list) {
5802 list_del(&pit_entry->list);
5803 kfree(pit_entry);
5804 }
5805 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&pf->l4_flex_pit_list);
5806
5807 pf->fdir_pf_active_filters = 0;
5808 pf->fd_tcp4_filter_cnt = 0;
5809 pf->fd_udp4_filter_cnt = 0;
5810 pf->fd_sctp4_filter_cnt = 0;
5811 pf->fd_ip4_filter_cnt = 0;
5812
5813 /* Reprogram the default input set for TCP/IPv4 */
5814 i40e_write_fd_input_set(pf, I40E_FILTER_PCTYPE_NONF_IPV4_TCP,
5815 I40E_L3_SRC_MASK | I40E_L3_DST_MASK |
5816 I40E_L4_SRC_MASK | I40E_L4_DST_MASK);
5817
5818 /* Reprogram the default input set for UDP/IPv4 */
5819 i40e_write_fd_input_set(pf, I40E_FILTER_PCTYPE_NONF_IPV4_UDP,
5820 I40E_L3_SRC_MASK | I40E_L3_DST_MASK |
5821 I40E_L4_SRC_MASK | I40E_L4_DST_MASK);
5822
5823 /* Reprogram the default input set for SCTP/IPv4 */
5824 i40e_write_fd_input_set(pf, I40E_FILTER_PCTYPE_NONF_IPV4_SCTP,
5825 I40E_L3_SRC_MASK | I40E_L3_DST_MASK |
5826 I40E_L4_SRC_MASK | I40E_L4_DST_MASK);
5827
5828 /* Reprogram the default input set for Other/IPv4 */
5829 i40e_write_fd_input_set(pf, I40E_FILTER_PCTYPE_NONF_IPV4_OTHER,
5830 I40E_L3_SRC_MASK | I40E_L3_DST_MASK);
5831
5832 i40e_write_fd_input_set(pf, I40E_FILTER_PCTYPE_FRAG_IPV4,
5833 I40E_L3_SRC_MASK | I40E_L3_DST_MASK);
5834}
5835
5836/**
5837 * i40e_close - Disables a network interface
5838 * @netdev: network interface device structure
5839 *
5840 * The close entry point is called when an interface is de-activated
5841 * by the OS. The hardware is still under the driver's control, but
5842 * this netdev interface is disabled.
5843 *
5844 * Returns 0, this is not allowed to fail
5845 **/
5846int i40e_close(struct net_device *netdev)
5847{
5848 struct i40e_netdev_priv *np = netdev_priv(netdev);
5849 struct i40e_vsi *vsi = np->vsi;
5850
5851 i40e_vsi_close(vsi);
5852
5853 return 0;
5854}
5855
5856/**
5857 * i40e_do_reset - Start a PF or Core Reset sequence
5858 * @pf: board private structure
5859 * @reset_flags: which reset is requested
5860 * @lock_acquired: indicates whether or not the lock has been acquired
5861 * before this function was called.
5862 *
5863 * The essential difference in resets is that the PF Reset
5864 * doesn't clear the packet buffers, doesn't reset the PE
5865 * firmware, and doesn't bother the other PFs on the chip.
5866 **/
5867void i40e_do_reset(struct i40e_pf *pf, u32 reset_flags, bool lock_acquired)
5868{
5869 u32 val;
5870
5871 WARN_ON(in_interrupt());
5872
5873
5874 /* do the biggest reset indicated */
5875 if (reset_flags & BIT_ULL(__I40E_GLOBAL_RESET_REQUESTED)) {
5876
5877 /* Request a Global Reset
5878 *
5879 * This will start the chip's countdown to the actual full
5880 * chip reset event, and a warning interrupt to be sent
5881 * to all PFs, including the requestor. Our handler
5882 * for the warning interrupt will deal with the shutdown
5883 * and recovery of the switch setup.
5884 */
5885 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev, "GlobalR requested\n");
5886 val = rd32(&pf->hw, I40E_GLGEN_RTRIG);
5887 val |= I40E_GLGEN_RTRIG_GLOBR_MASK;
5888 wr32(&pf->hw, I40E_GLGEN_RTRIG, val);
5889
5890 } else if (reset_flags & BIT_ULL(__I40E_CORE_RESET_REQUESTED)) {
5891
5892 /* Request a Core Reset
5893 *
5894 * Same as Global Reset, except does *not* include the MAC/PHY
5895 */
5896 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev, "CoreR requested\n");
5897 val = rd32(&pf->hw, I40E_GLGEN_RTRIG);
5898 val |= I40E_GLGEN_RTRIG_CORER_MASK;
5899 wr32(&pf->hw, I40E_GLGEN_RTRIG, val);
5900 i40e_flush(&pf->hw);
5901
5902 } else if (reset_flags & BIT_ULL(__I40E_PF_RESET_REQUESTED)) {
5903
5904 /* Request a PF Reset
5905 *
5906 * Resets only the PF-specific registers
5907 *
5908 * This goes directly to the tear-down and rebuild of
5909 * the switch, since we need to do all the recovery as
5910 * for the Core Reset.
5911 */
5912 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev, "PFR requested\n");
5913 i40e_handle_reset_warning(pf, lock_acquired);
5914
5915 } else if (reset_flags & BIT_ULL(__I40E_REINIT_REQUESTED)) {
5916 int v;
5917
5918 /* Find the VSI(s) that requested a re-init */
5919 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
5920 "VSI reinit requested\n");
5921 for (v = 0; v < pf->num_alloc_vsi; v++) {
5922 struct i40e_vsi *vsi = pf->vsi[v];
5923
5924 if (vsi != NULL &&
5925 test_and_clear_bit(__I40E_VSI_REINIT_REQUESTED,
5926 vsi->state))
5927 i40e_vsi_reinit_locked(pf->vsi[v]);
5928 }
5929 } else if (reset_flags & BIT_ULL(__I40E_DOWN_REQUESTED)) {
5930 int v;
5931
5932 /* Find the VSI(s) that needs to be brought down */
5933 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "VSI down requested\n");
5934 for (v = 0; v < pf->num_alloc_vsi; v++) {
5935 struct i40e_vsi *vsi = pf->vsi[v];
5936
5937 if (vsi != NULL &&
5938 test_and_clear_bit(__I40E_VSI_DOWN_REQUESTED,
5939 vsi->state)) {
5940 set_bit(__I40E_VSI_DOWN, vsi->state);
5941 i40e_down(vsi);
5942 }
5943 }
5944 } else {
5945 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
5946 "bad reset request 0x%08x\n", reset_flags);
5947 }
5948}
5949
5950#ifdef CONFIG_I40E_DCB
5951/**
5952 * i40e_dcb_need_reconfig - Check if DCB needs reconfig
5953 * @pf: board private structure
5954 * @old_cfg: current DCB config
5955 * @new_cfg: new DCB config
5956 **/
5957bool i40e_dcb_need_reconfig(struct i40e_pf *pf,
5958 struct i40e_dcbx_config *old_cfg,
5959 struct i40e_dcbx_config *new_cfg)
5960{
5961 bool need_reconfig = false;
5962
5963 /* Check if ETS configuration has changed */
5964 if (memcmp(&new_cfg->etscfg,
5965 &old_cfg->etscfg,
5966 sizeof(new_cfg->etscfg))) {
5967 /* If Priority Table has changed reconfig is needed */
5968 if (memcmp(&new_cfg->etscfg.prioritytable,
5969 &old_cfg->etscfg.prioritytable,
5970 sizeof(new_cfg->etscfg.prioritytable))) {
5971 need_reconfig = true;
5972 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev, "ETS UP2TC changed.\n");
5973 }
5974
5975 if (memcmp(&new_cfg->etscfg.tcbwtable,
5976 &old_cfg->etscfg.tcbwtable,
5977 sizeof(new_cfg->etscfg.tcbwtable)))
5978 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev, "ETS TC BW Table changed.\n");
5979
5980 if (memcmp(&new_cfg->etscfg.tsatable,
5981 &old_cfg->etscfg.tsatable,
5982 sizeof(new_cfg->etscfg.tsatable)))
5983 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev, "ETS TSA Table changed.\n");
5984 }
5985
5986 /* Check if PFC configuration has changed */
5987 if (memcmp(&new_cfg->pfc,
5988 &old_cfg->pfc,
5989 sizeof(new_cfg->pfc))) {
5990 need_reconfig = true;
5991 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev, "PFC config change detected.\n");
5992 }
5993
5994 /* Check if APP Table has changed */
5995 if (memcmp(&new_cfg->app,
5996 &old_cfg->app,
5997 sizeof(new_cfg->app))) {
5998 need_reconfig = true;
5999 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev, "APP Table change detected.\n");
6000 }
6001
6002 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev, "dcb need_reconfig=%d\n", need_reconfig);
6003 return need_reconfig;
6004}
6005
6006/**
6007 * i40e_handle_lldp_event - Handle LLDP Change MIB event
6008 * @pf: board private structure
6009 * @e: event info posted on ARQ
6010 **/
6011static int i40e_handle_lldp_event(struct i40e_pf *pf,
6012 struct i40e_arq_event_info *e)
6013{
6014 struct i40e_aqc_lldp_get_mib *mib =
6015 (struct i40e_aqc_lldp_get_mib *)&e->desc.params.raw;
6016 struct i40e_hw *hw = &pf->hw;
6017 struct i40e_dcbx_config tmp_dcbx_cfg;
6018 bool need_reconfig = false;
6019 int ret = 0;
6020 u8 type;
6021
6022 /* Not DCB capable or capability disabled */
6023 if (!(pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_DCB_CAPABLE))
6024 return ret;
6025
6026 /* Ignore if event is not for Nearest Bridge */
6027 type = ((mib->type >> I40E_AQ_LLDP_BRIDGE_TYPE_SHIFT)
6028 & I40E_AQ_LLDP_BRIDGE_TYPE_MASK);
6029 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev, "LLDP event mib bridge type 0x%x\n", type);
6030 if (type != I40E_AQ_LLDP_BRIDGE_TYPE_NEAREST_BRIDGE)
6031 return ret;
6032
6033 /* Check MIB Type and return if event for Remote MIB update */
6034 type = mib->type & I40E_AQ_LLDP_MIB_TYPE_MASK;
6035 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev,
6036 "LLDP event mib type %s\n", type ? "remote" : "local");
6037 if (type == I40E_AQ_LLDP_MIB_REMOTE) {
6038 /* Update the remote cached instance and return */
6039 ret = i40e_aq_get_dcb_config(hw, I40E_AQ_LLDP_MIB_REMOTE,
6040 I40E_AQ_LLDP_BRIDGE_TYPE_NEAREST_BRIDGE,
6041 &hw->remote_dcbx_config);
6042 goto exit;
6043 }
6044
6045 /* Store the old configuration */
6046 tmp_dcbx_cfg = hw->local_dcbx_config;
6047
6048 /* Reset the old DCBx configuration data */
6049 memset(&hw->local_dcbx_config, 0, sizeof(hw->local_dcbx_config));
6050 /* Get updated DCBX data from firmware */
6051 ret = i40e_get_dcb_config(&pf->hw);
6052 if (ret) {
6053 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
6054 "Failed querying DCB configuration data from firmware, err %s aq_err %s\n",
6055 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
6056 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw, pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
6057 goto exit;
6058 }
6059
6060 /* No change detected in DCBX configs */
6061 if (!memcmp(&tmp_dcbx_cfg, &hw->local_dcbx_config,
6062 sizeof(tmp_dcbx_cfg))) {
6063 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev, "No change detected in DCBX configuration.\n");
6064 goto exit;
6065 }
6066
6067 need_reconfig = i40e_dcb_need_reconfig(pf, &tmp_dcbx_cfg,
6068 &hw->local_dcbx_config);
6069
6070 i40e_dcbnl_flush_apps(pf, &tmp_dcbx_cfg, &hw->local_dcbx_config);
6071
6072 if (!need_reconfig)
6073 goto exit;
6074
6075 /* Enable DCB tagging only when more than one TC */
6076 if (i40e_dcb_get_num_tc(&hw->local_dcbx_config) > 1)
6077 pf->flags |= I40E_FLAG_DCB_ENABLED;
6078 else
6079 pf->flags &= ~I40E_FLAG_DCB_ENABLED;
6080
6081 set_bit(__I40E_PORT_SUSPENDED, pf->state);
6082 /* Reconfiguration needed quiesce all VSIs */
6083 i40e_pf_quiesce_all_vsi(pf);
6084
6085 /* Changes in configuration update VEB/VSI */
6086 i40e_dcb_reconfigure(pf);
6087
6088 ret = i40e_resume_port_tx(pf);
6089
6090 clear_bit(__I40E_PORT_SUSPENDED, pf->state);
6091 /* In case of error no point in resuming VSIs */
6092 if (ret)
6093 goto exit;
6094
6095 /* Wait for the PF's queues to be disabled */
6096 ret = i40e_pf_wait_queues_disabled(pf);
6097 if (ret) {
6098 /* Schedule PF reset to recover */
6099 set_bit(__I40E_PF_RESET_REQUESTED, pf->state);
6100 i40e_service_event_schedule(pf);
6101 } else {
6102 i40e_pf_unquiesce_all_vsi(pf);
6103 pf->flags |= (I40E_FLAG_SERVICE_CLIENT_REQUESTED |
6104 I40E_FLAG_CLIENT_L2_CHANGE);
6105 }
6106
6107exit:
6108 return ret;
6109}
6110#endif /* CONFIG_I40E_DCB */
6111
6112/**
6113 * i40e_do_reset_safe - Protected reset path for userland calls.
6114 * @pf: board private structure
6115 * @reset_flags: which reset is requested
6116 *
6117 **/
6118void i40e_do_reset_safe(struct i40e_pf *pf, u32 reset_flags)
6119{
6120 rtnl_lock();
6121 i40e_do_reset(pf, reset_flags, true);
6122 rtnl_unlock();
6123}
6124
6125/**
6126 * i40e_handle_lan_overflow_event - Handler for LAN queue overflow event
6127 * @pf: board private structure
6128 * @e: event info posted on ARQ
6129 *
6130 * Handler for LAN Queue Overflow Event generated by the firmware for PF
6131 * and VF queues
6132 **/
6133static void i40e_handle_lan_overflow_event(struct i40e_pf *pf,
6134 struct i40e_arq_event_info *e)
6135{
6136 struct i40e_aqc_lan_overflow *data =
6137 (struct i40e_aqc_lan_overflow *)&e->desc.params.raw;
6138 u32 queue = le32_to_cpu(data->prtdcb_rupto);
6139 u32 qtx_ctl = le32_to_cpu(data->otx_ctl);
6140 struct i40e_hw *hw = &pf->hw;
6141 struct i40e_vf *vf;
6142 u16 vf_id;
6143
6144 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev, "overflow Rx Queue Number = %d QTX_CTL=0x%08x\n",
6145 queue, qtx_ctl);
6146
6147 /* Queue belongs to VF, find the VF and issue VF reset */
6148 if (((qtx_ctl & I40E_QTX_CTL_PFVF_Q_MASK)
6149 >> I40E_QTX_CTL_PFVF_Q_SHIFT) == I40E_QTX_CTL_VF_QUEUE) {
6150 vf_id = (u16)((qtx_ctl & I40E_QTX_CTL_VFVM_INDX_MASK)
6151 >> I40E_QTX_CTL_VFVM_INDX_SHIFT);
6152 vf_id -= hw->func_caps.vf_base_id;
6153 vf = &pf->vf[vf_id];
6154 i40e_vc_notify_vf_reset(vf);
6155 /* Allow VF to process pending reset notification */
6156 msleep(20);
6157 i40e_reset_vf(vf, false);
6158 }
6159}
6160
6161/**
6162 * i40e_get_cur_guaranteed_fd_count - Get the consumed guaranteed FD filters
6163 * @pf: board private structure
6164 **/
6165u32 i40e_get_cur_guaranteed_fd_count(struct i40e_pf *pf)
6166{
6167 u32 val, fcnt_prog;
6168
6169 val = rd32(&pf->hw, I40E_PFQF_FDSTAT);
6170 fcnt_prog = (val & I40E_PFQF_FDSTAT_GUARANT_CNT_MASK);
6171 return fcnt_prog;
6172}
6173
6174/**
6175 * i40e_get_current_fd_count - Get total FD filters programmed for this PF
6176 * @pf: board private structure
6177 **/
6178u32 i40e_get_current_fd_count(struct i40e_pf *pf)
6179{
6180 u32 val, fcnt_prog;
6181
6182 val = rd32(&pf->hw, I40E_PFQF_FDSTAT);
6183 fcnt_prog = (val & I40E_PFQF_FDSTAT_GUARANT_CNT_MASK) +
6184 ((val & I40E_PFQF_FDSTAT_BEST_CNT_MASK) >>
6185 I40E_PFQF_FDSTAT_BEST_CNT_SHIFT);
6186 return fcnt_prog;
6187}
6188
6189/**
6190 * i40e_get_global_fd_count - Get total FD filters programmed on device
6191 * @pf: board private structure
6192 **/
6193u32 i40e_get_global_fd_count(struct i40e_pf *pf)
6194{
6195 u32 val, fcnt_prog;
6196
6197 val = rd32(&pf->hw, I40E_GLQF_FDCNT_0);
6198 fcnt_prog = (val & I40E_GLQF_FDCNT_0_GUARANT_CNT_MASK) +
6199 ((val & I40E_GLQF_FDCNT_0_BESTCNT_MASK) >>
6200 I40E_GLQF_FDCNT_0_BESTCNT_SHIFT);
6201 return fcnt_prog;
6202}
6203
6204/**
6205 * i40e_fdir_check_and_reenable - Function to reenabe FD ATR or SB if disabled
6206 * @pf: board private structure
6207 **/
6208void i40e_fdir_check_and_reenable(struct i40e_pf *pf)
6209{
6210 struct i40e_fdir_filter *filter;
6211 u32 fcnt_prog, fcnt_avail;
6212 struct hlist_node *node;
6213
6214 if (test_bit(__I40E_FD_FLUSH_REQUESTED, pf->state))
6215 return;
6216
6217 /* Check if we have enough room to re-enable FDir SB capability. */
6218 fcnt_prog = i40e_get_global_fd_count(pf);
6219 fcnt_avail = pf->fdir_pf_filter_count;
6220 if ((fcnt_prog < (fcnt_avail - I40E_FDIR_BUFFER_HEAD_ROOM)) ||
6221 (pf->fd_add_err == 0) ||
6222 (i40e_get_current_atr_cnt(pf) < pf->fd_atr_cnt)) {
6223 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_FD_SB_AUTO_DISABLED) {
6224 pf->flags &= ~I40E_FLAG_FD_SB_AUTO_DISABLED;
6225 if ((pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_FD_SB_ENABLED) &&
6226 (I40E_DEBUG_FD & pf->hw.debug_mask))
6227 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "FD Sideband/ntuple is being enabled since we have space in the table now\n");
6228 }
6229 }
6230
6231 /* We should wait for even more space before re-enabling ATR.
6232 * Additionally, we cannot enable ATR as long as we still have TCP SB
6233 * rules active.
6234 */
6235 if ((fcnt_prog < (fcnt_avail - I40E_FDIR_BUFFER_HEAD_ROOM_FOR_ATR)) &&
6236 (pf->fd_tcp4_filter_cnt == 0)) {
6237 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_FD_ATR_AUTO_DISABLED) {
6238 pf->flags &= ~I40E_FLAG_FD_ATR_AUTO_DISABLED;
6239 if ((pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_FD_ATR_ENABLED) &&
6240 (I40E_DEBUG_FD & pf->hw.debug_mask))
6241 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "ATR is being enabled since we have space in the table and there are no conflicting ntuple rules\n");
6242 }
6243 }
6244
6245 /* if hw had a problem adding a filter, delete it */
6246 if (pf->fd_inv > 0) {
6247 hlist_for_each_entry_safe(filter, node,
6248 &pf->fdir_filter_list, fdir_node) {
6249 if (filter->fd_id == pf->fd_inv) {
6250 hlist_del(&filter->fdir_node);
6251 kfree(filter);
6252 pf->fdir_pf_active_filters--;
6253 }
6254 }
6255 }
6256}
6257
6258#define I40E_MIN_FD_FLUSH_INTERVAL 10
6259#define I40E_MIN_FD_FLUSH_SB_ATR_UNSTABLE 30
6260/**
6261 * i40e_fdir_flush_and_replay - Function to flush all FD filters and replay SB
6262 * @pf: board private structure
6263 **/
6264static void i40e_fdir_flush_and_replay(struct i40e_pf *pf)
6265{
6266 unsigned long min_flush_time;
6267 int flush_wait_retry = 50;
6268 bool disable_atr = false;
6269 int fd_room;
6270 int reg;
6271
6272 if (!time_after(jiffies, pf->fd_flush_timestamp +
6273 (I40E_MIN_FD_FLUSH_INTERVAL * HZ)))
6274 return;
6275
6276 /* If the flush is happening too quick and we have mostly SB rules we
6277 * should not re-enable ATR for some time.
6278 */
6279 min_flush_time = pf->fd_flush_timestamp +
6280 (I40E_MIN_FD_FLUSH_SB_ATR_UNSTABLE * HZ);
6281 fd_room = pf->fdir_pf_filter_count - pf->fdir_pf_active_filters;
6282
6283 if (!(time_after(jiffies, min_flush_time)) &&
6284 (fd_room < I40E_FDIR_BUFFER_HEAD_ROOM_FOR_ATR)) {
6285 if (I40E_DEBUG_FD & pf->hw.debug_mask)
6286 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "ATR disabled, not enough FD filter space.\n");
6287 disable_atr = true;
6288 }
6289
6290 pf->fd_flush_timestamp = jiffies;
6291 pf->flags |= I40E_FLAG_FD_ATR_AUTO_DISABLED;
6292 /* flush all filters */
6293 wr32(&pf->hw, I40E_PFQF_CTL_1,
6294 I40E_PFQF_CTL_1_CLEARFDTABLE_MASK);
6295 i40e_flush(&pf->hw);
6296 pf->fd_flush_cnt++;
6297 pf->fd_add_err = 0;
6298 do {
6299 /* Check FD flush status every 5-6msec */
6300 usleep_range(5000, 6000);
6301 reg = rd32(&pf->hw, I40E_PFQF_CTL_1);
6302 if (!(reg & I40E_PFQF_CTL_1_CLEARFDTABLE_MASK))
6303 break;
6304 } while (flush_wait_retry--);
6305 if (reg & I40E_PFQF_CTL_1_CLEARFDTABLE_MASK) {
6306 dev_warn(&pf->pdev->dev, "FD table did not flush, needs more time\n");
6307 } else {
6308 /* replay sideband filters */
6309 i40e_fdir_filter_restore(pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi]);
6310 if (!disable_atr && !pf->fd_tcp4_filter_cnt)
6311 pf->flags &= ~I40E_FLAG_FD_ATR_AUTO_DISABLED;
6312 clear_bit(__I40E_FD_FLUSH_REQUESTED, pf->state);
6313 if (I40E_DEBUG_FD & pf->hw.debug_mask)
6314 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "FD Filter table flushed and FD-SB replayed.\n");
6315 }
6316}
6317
6318/**
6319 * i40e_get_current_atr_count - Get the count of total FD ATR filters programmed
6320 * @pf: board private structure
6321 **/
6322u32 i40e_get_current_atr_cnt(struct i40e_pf *pf)
6323{
6324 return i40e_get_current_fd_count(pf) - pf->fdir_pf_active_filters;
6325}
6326
6327/* We can see up to 256 filter programming desc in transit if the filters are
6328 * being applied really fast; before we see the first
6329 * filter miss error on Rx queue 0. Accumulating enough error messages before
6330 * reacting will make sure we don't cause flush too often.
6331 */
6332#define I40E_MAX_FD_PROGRAM_ERROR 256
6333
6334/**
6335 * i40e_fdir_reinit_subtask - Worker thread to reinit FDIR filter table
6336 * @pf: board private structure
6337 **/
6338static void i40e_fdir_reinit_subtask(struct i40e_pf *pf)
6339{
6340
6341 /* if interface is down do nothing */
6342 if (test_bit(__I40E_DOWN, pf->state))
6343 return;
6344
6345 if (test_bit(__I40E_FD_FLUSH_REQUESTED, pf->state))
6346 i40e_fdir_flush_and_replay(pf);
6347
6348 i40e_fdir_check_and_reenable(pf);
6349
6350}
6351
6352/**
6353 * i40e_vsi_link_event - notify VSI of a link event
6354 * @vsi: vsi to be notified
6355 * @link_up: link up or down
6356 **/
6357static void i40e_vsi_link_event(struct i40e_vsi *vsi, bool link_up)
6358{
6359 if (!vsi || test_bit(__I40E_VSI_DOWN, vsi->state))
6360 return;
6361
6362 switch (vsi->type) {
6363 case I40E_VSI_MAIN:
6364 if (!vsi->netdev || !vsi->netdev_registered)
6365 break;
6366
6367 if (link_up) {
6368 netif_carrier_on(vsi->netdev);
6369 netif_tx_wake_all_queues(vsi->netdev);
6370 } else {
6371 netif_carrier_off(vsi->netdev);
6372 netif_tx_stop_all_queues(vsi->netdev);
6373 }
6374 break;
6375
6376 case I40E_VSI_SRIOV:
6377 case I40E_VSI_VMDQ2:
6378 case I40E_VSI_CTRL:
6379 case I40E_VSI_IWARP:
6380 case I40E_VSI_MIRROR:
6381 default:
6382 /* there is no notification for other VSIs */
6383 break;
6384 }
6385}
6386
6387/**
6388 * i40e_veb_link_event - notify elements on the veb of a link event
6389 * @veb: veb to be notified
6390 * @link_up: link up or down
6391 **/
6392static void i40e_veb_link_event(struct i40e_veb *veb, bool link_up)
6393{
6394 struct i40e_pf *pf;
6395 int i;
6396
6397 if (!veb || !veb->pf)
6398 return;
6399 pf = veb->pf;
6400
6401 /* depth first... */
6402 for (i = 0; i < I40E_MAX_VEB; i++)
6403 if (pf->veb[i] && (pf->veb[i]->uplink_seid == veb->seid))
6404 i40e_veb_link_event(pf->veb[i], link_up);
6405
6406 /* ... now the local VSIs */
6407 for (i = 0; i < pf->num_alloc_vsi; i++)
6408 if (pf->vsi[i] && (pf->vsi[i]->uplink_seid == veb->seid))
6409 i40e_vsi_link_event(pf->vsi[i], link_up);
6410}
6411
6412/**
6413 * i40e_link_event - Update netif_carrier status
6414 * @pf: board private structure
6415 **/
6416static void i40e_link_event(struct i40e_pf *pf)
6417{
6418 struct i40e_vsi *vsi = pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi];
6419 u8 new_link_speed, old_link_speed;
6420 i40e_status status;
6421 bool new_link, old_link;
6422
6423 /* save off old link status information */
6424 pf->hw.phy.link_info_old = pf->hw.phy.link_info;
6425
6426 /* set this to force the get_link_status call to refresh state */
6427 pf->hw.phy.get_link_info = true;
6428
6429 old_link = (pf->hw.phy.link_info_old.link_info & I40E_AQ_LINK_UP);
6430
6431 status = i40e_get_link_status(&pf->hw, &new_link);
6432
6433 /* On success, disable temp link polling */
6434 if (status == I40E_SUCCESS) {
6435 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_TEMP_LINK_POLLING)
6436 pf->flags &= ~I40E_FLAG_TEMP_LINK_POLLING;
6437 } else {
6438 /* Enable link polling temporarily until i40e_get_link_status
6439 * returns I40E_SUCCESS
6440 */
6441 pf->flags |= I40E_FLAG_TEMP_LINK_POLLING;
6442 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev, "couldn't get link state, status: %d\n",
6443 status);
6444 return;
6445 }
6446
6447 old_link_speed = pf->hw.phy.link_info_old.link_speed;
6448 new_link_speed = pf->hw.phy.link_info.link_speed;
6449
6450 if (new_link == old_link &&
6451 new_link_speed == old_link_speed &&
6452 (test_bit(__I40E_VSI_DOWN, vsi->state) ||
6453 new_link == netif_carrier_ok(vsi->netdev)))
6454 return;
6455
6456 if (!test_bit(__I40E_VSI_DOWN, vsi->state))
6457 i40e_print_link_message(vsi, new_link);
6458
6459 /* Notify the base of the switch tree connected to
6460 * the link. Floating VEBs are not notified.
6461 */
6462 if (pf->lan_veb != I40E_NO_VEB && pf->veb[pf->lan_veb])
6463 i40e_veb_link_event(pf->veb[pf->lan_veb], new_link);
6464 else
6465 i40e_vsi_link_event(vsi, new_link);
6466
6467 if (pf->vf)
6468 i40e_vc_notify_link_state(pf);
6469
6470 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_PTP)
6471 i40e_ptp_set_increment(pf);
6472}
6473
6474/**
6475 * i40e_watchdog_subtask - periodic checks not using event driven response
6476 * @pf: board private structure
6477 **/
6478static void i40e_watchdog_subtask(struct i40e_pf *pf)
6479{
6480 int i;
6481
6482 /* if interface is down do nothing */
6483 if (test_bit(__I40E_DOWN, pf->state) ||
6484 test_bit(__I40E_CONFIG_BUSY, pf->state))
6485 return;
6486
6487 /* make sure we don't do these things too often */
6488 if (time_before(jiffies, (pf->service_timer_previous +
6489 pf->service_timer_period)))
6490 return;
6491 pf->service_timer_previous = jiffies;
6492
6493 if ((pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_LINK_POLLING_ENABLED) ||
6494 (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_TEMP_LINK_POLLING))
6495 i40e_link_event(pf);
6496
6497 /* Update the stats for active netdevs so the network stack
6498 * can look at updated numbers whenever it cares to
6499 */
6500 for (i = 0; i < pf->num_alloc_vsi; i++)
6501 if (pf->vsi[i] && pf->vsi[i]->netdev)
6502 i40e_update_stats(pf->vsi[i]);
6503
6504 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_VEB_STATS_ENABLED) {
6505 /* Update the stats for the active switching components */
6506 for (i = 0; i < I40E_MAX_VEB; i++)
6507 if (pf->veb[i])
6508 i40e_update_veb_stats(pf->veb[i]);
6509 }
6510
6511 i40e_ptp_rx_hang(pf);
6512 i40e_ptp_tx_hang(pf);
6513}
6514
6515/**
6516 * i40e_reset_subtask - Set up for resetting the device and driver
6517 * @pf: board private structure
6518 **/
6519static void i40e_reset_subtask(struct i40e_pf *pf)
6520{
6521 u32 reset_flags = 0;
6522
6523 if (test_bit(__I40E_REINIT_REQUESTED, pf->state)) {
6524 reset_flags |= BIT(__I40E_REINIT_REQUESTED);
6525 clear_bit(__I40E_REINIT_REQUESTED, pf->state);
6526 }
6527 if (test_bit(__I40E_PF_RESET_REQUESTED, pf->state)) {
6528 reset_flags |= BIT(__I40E_PF_RESET_REQUESTED);
6529 clear_bit(__I40E_PF_RESET_REQUESTED, pf->state);
6530 }
6531 if (test_bit(__I40E_CORE_RESET_REQUESTED, pf->state)) {
6532 reset_flags |= BIT(__I40E_CORE_RESET_REQUESTED);
6533 clear_bit(__I40E_CORE_RESET_REQUESTED, pf->state);
6534 }
6535 if (test_bit(__I40E_GLOBAL_RESET_REQUESTED, pf->state)) {
6536 reset_flags |= BIT(__I40E_GLOBAL_RESET_REQUESTED);
6537 clear_bit(__I40E_GLOBAL_RESET_REQUESTED, pf->state);
6538 }
6539 if (test_bit(__I40E_DOWN_REQUESTED, pf->state)) {
6540 reset_flags |= BIT(__I40E_DOWN_REQUESTED);
6541 clear_bit(__I40E_DOWN_REQUESTED, pf->state);
6542 }
6543
6544 /* If there's a recovery already waiting, it takes
6545 * precedence before starting a new reset sequence.
6546 */
6547 if (test_bit(__I40E_RESET_INTR_RECEIVED, pf->state)) {
6548 i40e_prep_for_reset(pf, false);
6549 i40e_reset(pf);
6550 i40e_rebuild(pf, false, false);
6551 }
6552
6553 /* If we're already down or resetting, just bail */
6554 if (reset_flags &&
6555 !test_bit(__I40E_DOWN, pf->state) &&
6556 !test_bit(__I40E_CONFIG_BUSY, pf->state)) {
6557 i40e_do_reset(pf, reset_flags, false);
6558 }
6559}
6560
6561/**
6562 * i40e_handle_link_event - Handle link event
6563 * @pf: board private structure
6564 * @e: event info posted on ARQ
6565 **/
6566static void i40e_handle_link_event(struct i40e_pf *pf,
6567 struct i40e_arq_event_info *e)
6568{
6569 struct i40e_aqc_get_link_status *status =
6570 (struct i40e_aqc_get_link_status *)&e->desc.params.raw;
6571
6572 /* Do a new status request to re-enable LSE reporting
6573 * and load new status information into the hw struct
6574 * This completely ignores any state information
6575 * in the ARQ event info, instead choosing to always
6576 * issue the AQ update link status command.
6577 */
6578 i40e_link_event(pf);
6579
6580 /* check for unqualified module, if link is down */
6581 if ((status->link_info & I40E_AQ_MEDIA_AVAILABLE) &&
6582 (!(status->an_info & I40E_AQ_QUALIFIED_MODULE)) &&
6583 (!(status->link_info & I40E_AQ_LINK_UP)))
6584 dev_err(&pf->pdev->dev,
6585 "The driver failed to link because an unqualified module was detected.\n");
6586}
6587
6588/**
6589 * i40e_clean_adminq_subtask - Clean the AdminQ rings
6590 * @pf: board private structure
6591 **/
6592static void i40e_clean_adminq_subtask(struct i40e_pf *pf)
6593{
6594 struct i40e_arq_event_info event;
6595 struct i40e_hw *hw = &pf->hw;
6596 u16 pending, i = 0;
6597 i40e_status ret;
6598 u16 opcode;
6599 u32 oldval;
6600 u32 val;
6601
6602 /* Do not run clean AQ when PF reset fails */
6603 if (test_bit(__I40E_RESET_FAILED, pf->state))
6604 return;
6605
6606 /* check for error indications */
6607 val = rd32(&pf->hw, pf->hw.aq.arq.len);
6608 oldval = val;
6609 if (val & I40E_PF_ARQLEN_ARQVFE_MASK) {
6610 if (hw->debug_mask & I40E_DEBUG_AQ)
6611 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "ARQ VF Error detected\n");
6612 val &= ~I40E_PF_ARQLEN_ARQVFE_MASK;
6613 }
6614 if (val & I40E_PF_ARQLEN_ARQOVFL_MASK) {
6615 if (hw->debug_mask & I40E_DEBUG_AQ)
6616 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "ARQ Overflow Error detected\n");
6617 val &= ~I40E_PF_ARQLEN_ARQOVFL_MASK;
6618 pf->arq_overflows++;
6619 }
6620 if (val & I40E_PF_ARQLEN_ARQCRIT_MASK) {
6621 if (hw->debug_mask & I40E_DEBUG_AQ)
6622 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "ARQ Critical Error detected\n");
6623 val &= ~I40E_PF_ARQLEN_ARQCRIT_MASK;
6624 }
6625 if (oldval != val)
6626 wr32(&pf->hw, pf->hw.aq.arq.len, val);
6627
6628 val = rd32(&pf->hw, pf->hw.aq.asq.len);
6629 oldval = val;
6630 if (val & I40E_PF_ATQLEN_ATQVFE_MASK) {
6631 if (pf->hw.debug_mask & I40E_DEBUG_AQ)
6632 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "ASQ VF Error detected\n");
6633 val &= ~I40E_PF_ATQLEN_ATQVFE_MASK;
6634 }
6635 if (val & I40E_PF_ATQLEN_ATQOVFL_MASK) {
6636 if (pf->hw.debug_mask & I40E_DEBUG_AQ)
6637 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "ASQ Overflow Error detected\n");
6638 val &= ~I40E_PF_ATQLEN_ATQOVFL_MASK;
6639 }
6640 if (val & I40E_PF_ATQLEN_ATQCRIT_MASK) {
6641 if (pf->hw.debug_mask & I40E_DEBUG_AQ)
6642 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "ASQ Critical Error detected\n");
6643 val &= ~I40E_PF_ATQLEN_ATQCRIT_MASK;
6644 }
6645 if (oldval != val)
6646 wr32(&pf->hw, pf->hw.aq.asq.len, val);
6647
6648 event.buf_len = I40E_MAX_AQ_BUF_SIZE;
6649 event.msg_buf = kzalloc(event.buf_len, GFP_KERNEL);
6650 if (!event.msg_buf)
6651 return;
6652
6653 do {
6654 ret = i40e_clean_arq_element(hw, &event, &pending);
6655 if (ret == I40E_ERR_ADMIN_QUEUE_NO_WORK)
6656 break;
6657 else if (ret) {
6658 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "ARQ event error %d\n", ret);
6659 break;
6660 }
6661
6662 opcode = le16_to_cpu(event.desc.opcode);
6663 switch (opcode) {
6664
6665 case i40e_aqc_opc_get_link_status:
6666 i40e_handle_link_event(pf, &event);
6667 break;
6668 case i40e_aqc_opc_send_msg_to_pf:
6669 ret = i40e_vc_process_vf_msg(pf,
6670 le16_to_cpu(event.desc.retval),
6671 le32_to_cpu(event.desc.cookie_high),
6672 le32_to_cpu(event.desc.cookie_low),
6673 event.msg_buf,
6674 event.msg_len);
6675 break;
6676 case i40e_aqc_opc_lldp_update_mib:
6677 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev, "ARQ: Update LLDP MIB event received\n");
6678#ifdef CONFIG_I40E_DCB
6679 rtnl_lock();
6680 ret = i40e_handle_lldp_event(pf, &event);
6681 rtnl_unlock();
6682#endif /* CONFIG_I40E_DCB */
6683 break;
6684 case i40e_aqc_opc_event_lan_overflow:
6685 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev, "ARQ LAN queue overflow event received\n");
6686 i40e_handle_lan_overflow_event(pf, &event);
6687 break;
6688 case i40e_aqc_opc_send_msg_to_peer:
6689 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "ARQ: Msg from other pf\n");
6690 break;
6691 case i40e_aqc_opc_nvm_erase:
6692 case i40e_aqc_opc_nvm_update:
6693 case i40e_aqc_opc_oem_post_update:
6694 i40e_debug(&pf->hw, I40E_DEBUG_NVM,
6695 "ARQ NVM operation 0x%04x completed\n",
6696 opcode);
6697 break;
6698 default:
6699 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
6700 "ARQ: Unknown event 0x%04x ignored\n",
6701 opcode);
6702 break;
6703 }
6704 } while (i++ < pf->adminq_work_limit);
6705
6706 if (i < pf->adminq_work_limit)
6707 clear_bit(__I40E_ADMINQ_EVENT_PENDING, pf->state);
6708
6709 /* re-enable Admin queue interrupt cause */
6710 val = rd32(hw, I40E_PFINT_ICR0_ENA);
6711 val |= I40E_PFINT_ICR0_ENA_ADMINQ_MASK;
6712 wr32(hw, I40E_PFINT_ICR0_ENA, val);
6713 i40e_flush(hw);
6714
6715 kfree(event.msg_buf);
6716}
6717
6718/**
6719 * i40e_verify_eeprom - make sure eeprom is good to use
6720 * @pf: board private structure
6721 **/
6722static void i40e_verify_eeprom(struct i40e_pf *pf)
6723{
6724 int err;
6725
6726 err = i40e_diag_eeprom_test(&pf->hw);
6727 if (err) {
6728 /* retry in case of garbage read */
6729 err = i40e_diag_eeprom_test(&pf->hw);
6730 if (err) {
6731 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "eeprom check failed (%d), Tx/Rx traffic disabled\n",
6732 err);
6733 set_bit(__I40E_BAD_EEPROM, pf->state);
6734 }
6735 }
6736
6737 if (!err && test_bit(__I40E_BAD_EEPROM, pf->state)) {
6738 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "eeprom check passed, Tx/Rx traffic enabled\n");
6739 clear_bit(__I40E_BAD_EEPROM, pf->state);
6740 }
6741}
6742
6743/**
6744 * i40e_enable_pf_switch_lb
6745 * @pf: pointer to the PF structure
6746 *
6747 * enable switch loop back or die - no point in a return value
6748 **/
6749static void i40e_enable_pf_switch_lb(struct i40e_pf *pf)
6750{
6751 struct i40e_vsi *vsi = pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi];
6752 struct i40e_vsi_context ctxt;
6753 int ret;
6754
6755 ctxt.seid = pf->main_vsi_seid;
6756 ctxt.pf_num = pf->hw.pf_id;
6757 ctxt.vf_num = 0;
6758 ret = i40e_aq_get_vsi_params(&pf->hw, &ctxt, NULL);
6759 if (ret) {
6760 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
6761 "couldn't get PF vsi config, err %s aq_err %s\n",
6762 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
6763 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw, pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
6764 return;
6765 }
6766 ctxt.flags = I40E_AQ_VSI_TYPE_PF;
6767 ctxt.info.valid_sections = cpu_to_le16(I40E_AQ_VSI_PROP_SWITCH_VALID);
6768 ctxt.info.switch_id |= cpu_to_le16(I40E_AQ_VSI_SW_ID_FLAG_ALLOW_LB);
6769
6770 ret = i40e_aq_update_vsi_params(&vsi->back->hw, &ctxt, NULL);
6771 if (ret) {
6772 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
6773 "update vsi switch failed, err %s aq_err %s\n",
6774 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
6775 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw, pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
6776 }
6777}
6778
6779/**
6780 * i40e_disable_pf_switch_lb
6781 * @pf: pointer to the PF structure
6782 *
6783 * disable switch loop back or die - no point in a return value
6784 **/
6785static void i40e_disable_pf_switch_lb(struct i40e_pf *pf)
6786{
6787 struct i40e_vsi *vsi = pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi];
6788 struct i40e_vsi_context ctxt;
6789 int ret;
6790
6791 ctxt.seid = pf->main_vsi_seid;
6792 ctxt.pf_num = pf->hw.pf_id;
6793 ctxt.vf_num = 0;
6794 ret = i40e_aq_get_vsi_params(&pf->hw, &ctxt, NULL);
6795 if (ret) {
6796 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
6797 "couldn't get PF vsi config, err %s aq_err %s\n",
6798 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
6799 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw, pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
6800 return;
6801 }
6802 ctxt.flags = I40E_AQ_VSI_TYPE_PF;
6803 ctxt.info.valid_sections = cpu_to_le16(I40E_AQ_VSI_PROP_SWITCH_VALID);
6804 ctxt.info.switch_id &= ~cpu_to_le16(I40E_AQ_VSI_SW_ID_FLAG_ALLOW_LB);
6805
6806 ret = i40e_aq_update_vsi_params(&vsi->back->hw, &ctxt, NULL);
6807 if (ret) {
6808 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
6809 "update vsi switch failed, err %s aq_err %s\n",
6810 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
6811 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw, pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
6812 }
6813}
6814
6815/**
6816 * i40e_config_bridge_mode - Configure the HW bridge mode
6817 * @veb: pointer to the bridge instance
6818 *
6819 * Configure the loop back mode for the LAN VSI that is downlink to the
6820 * specified HW bridge instance. It is expected this function is called
6821 * when a new HW bridge is instantiated.
6822 **/
6823static void i40e_config_bridge_mode(struct i40e_veb *veb)
6824{
6825 struct i40e_pf *pf = veb->pf;
6826
6827 if (pf->hw.debug_mask & I40E_DEBUG_LAN)
6828 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "enabling bridge mode: %s\n",
6829 veb->bridge_mode == BRIDGE_MODE_VEPA ? "VEPA" : "VEB");
6830 if (veb->bridge_mode & BRIDGE_MODE_VEPA)
6831 i40e_disable_pf_switch_lb(pf);
6832 else
6833 i40e_enable_pf_switch_lb(pf);
6834}
6835
6836/**
6837 * i40e_reconstitute_veb - rebuild the VEB and anything connected to it
6838 * @veb: pointer to the VEB instance
6839 *
6840 * This is a recursive function that first builds the attached VSIs then
6841 * recurses in to build the next layer of VEB. We track the connections
6842 * through our own index numbers because the seid's from the HW could
6843 * change across the reset.
6844 **/
6845static int i40e_reconstitute_veb(struct i40e_veb *veb)
6846{
6847 struct i40e_vsi *ctl_vsi = NULL;
6848 struct i40e_pf *pf = veb->pf;
6849 int v, veb_idx;
6850 int ret;
6851
6852 /* build VSI that owns this VEB, temporarily attached to base VEB */
6853 for (v = 0; v < pf->num_alloc_vsi && !ctl_vsi; v++) {
6854 if (pf->vsi[v] &&
6855 pf->vsi[v]->veb_idx == veb->idx &&
6856 pf->vsi[v]->flags & I40E_VSI_FLAG_VEB_OWNER) {
6857 ctl_vsi = pf->vsi[v];
6858 break;
6859 }
6860 }
6861 if (!ctl_vsi) {
6862 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
6863 "missing owner VSI for veb_idx %d\n", veb->idx);
6864 ret = -ENOENT;
6865 goto end_reconstitute;
6866 }
6867 if (ctl_vsi != pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi])
6868 ctl_vsi->uplink_seid = pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi]->uplink_seid;
6869 ret = i40e_add_vsi(ctl_vsi);
6870 if (ret) {
6871 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
6872 "rebuild of veb_idx %d owner VSI failed: %d\n",
6873 veb->idx, ret);
6874 goto end_reconstitute;
6875 }
6876 i40e_vsi_reset_stats(ctl_vsi);
6877
6878 /* create the VEB in the switch and move the VSI onto the VEB */
6879 ret = i40e_add_veb(veb, ctl_vsi);
6880 if (ret)
6881 goto end_reconstitute;
6882
6883 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_VEB_MODE_ENABLED)
6884 veb->bridge_mode = BRIDGE_MODE_VEB;
6885 else
6886 veb->bridge_mode = BRIDGE_MODE_VEPA;
6887 i40e_config_bridge_mode(veb);
6888
6889 /* create the remaining VSIs attached to this VEB */
6890 for (v = 0; v < pf->num_alloc_vsi; v++) {
6891 if (!pf->vsi[v] || pf->vsi[v] == ctl_vsi)
6892 continue;
6893
6894 if (pf->vsi[v]->veb_idx == veb->idx) {
6895 struct i40e_vsi *vsi = pf->vsi[v];
6896
6897 vsi->uplink_seid = veb->seid;
6898 ret = i40e_add_vsi(vsi);
6899 if (ret) {
6900 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
6901 "rebuild of vsi_idx %d failed: %d\n",
6902 v, ret);
6903 goto end_reconstitute;
6904 }
6905 i40e_vsi_reset_stats(vsi);
6906 }
6907 }
6908
6909 /* create any VEBs attached to this VEB - RECURSION */
6910 for (veb_idx = 0; veb_idx < I40E_MAX_VEB; veb_idx++) {
6911 if (pf->veb[veb_idx] && pf->veb[veb_idx]->veb_idx == veb->idx) {
6912 pf->veb[veb_idx]->uplink_seid = veb->seid;
6913 ret = i40e_reconstitute_veb(pf->veb[veb_idx]);
6914 if (ret)
6915 break;
6916 }
6917 }
6918
6919end_reconstitute:
6920 return ret;
6921}
6922
6923/**
6924 * i40e_get_capabilities - get info about the HW
6925 * @pf: the PF struct
6926 **/
6927static int i40e_get_capabilities(struct i40e_pf *pf)
6928{
6929 struct i40e_aqc_list_capabilities_element_resp *cap_buf;
6930 u16 data_size;
6931 int buf_len;
6932 int err;
6933
6934 buf_len = 40 * sizeof(struct i40e_aqc_list_capabilities_element_resp);
6935 do {
6936 cap_buf = kzalloc(buf_len, GFP_KERNEL);
6937 if (!cap_buf)
6938 return -ENOMEM;
6939
6940 /* this loads the data into the hw struct for us */
6941 err = i40e_aq_discover_capabilities(&pf->hw, cap_buf, buf_len,
6942 &data_size,
6943 i40e_aqc_opc_list_func_capabilities,
6944 NULL);
6945 /* data loaded, buffer no longer needed */
6946 kfree(cap_buf);
6947
6948 if (pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status == I40E_AQ_RC_ENOMEM) {
6949 /* retry with a larger buffer */
6950 buf_len = data_size;
6951 } else if (pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status != I40E_AQ_RC_OK) {
6952 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
6953 "capability discovery failed, err %s aq_err %s\n",
6954 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, err),
6955 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw,
6956 pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
6957 return -ENODEV;
6958 }
6959 } while (err);
6960
6961 if (pf->hw.debug_mask & I40E_DEBUG_USER)
6962 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
6963 "pf=%d, num_vfs=%d, msix_pf=%d, msix_vf=%d, fd_g=%d, fd_b=%d, pf_max_q=%d num_vsi=%d\n",
6964 pf->hw.pf_id, pf->hw.func_caps.num_vfs,
6965 pf->hw.func_caps.num_msix_vectors,
6966 pf->hw.func_caps.num_msix_vectors_vf,
6967 pf->hw.func_caps.fd_filters_guaranteed,
6968 pf->hw.func_caps.fd_filters_best_effort,
6969 pf->hw.func_caps.num_tx_qp,
6970 pf->hw.func_caps.num_vsis);
6971
6972#define DEF_NUM_VSI (1 + (pf->hw.func_caps.fcoe ? 1 : 0) \
6973 + pf->hw.func_caps.num_vfs)
6974 if (pf->hw.revision_id == 0 && (DEF_NUM_VSI > pf->hw.func_caps.num_vsis)) {
6975 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
6976 "got num_vsis %d, setting num_vsis to %d\n",
6977 pf->hw.func_caps.num_vsis, DEF_NUM_VSI);
6978 pf->hw.func_caps.num_vsis = DEF_NUM_VSI;
6979 }
6980
6981 return 0;
6982}
6983
6984static int i40e_vsi_clear(struct i40e_vsi *vsi);
6985
6986/**
6987 * i40e_fdir_sb_setup - initialize the Flow Director resources for Sideband
6988 * @pf: board private structure
6989 **/
6990static void i40e_fdir_sb_setup(struct i40e_pf *pf)
6991{
6992 struct i40e_vsi *vsi;
6993
6994 /* quick workaround for an NVM issue that leaves a critical register
6995 * uninitialized
6996 */
6997 if (!rd32(&pf->hw, I40E_GLQF_HKEY(0))) {
6998 static const u32 hkey[] = {
6999 0xe640d33f, 0xcdfe98ab, 0x73fa7161, 0x0d7a7d36,
7000 0xeacb7d61, 0xaa4f05b6, 0x9c5c89ed, 0xfc425ddb,
7001 0xa4654832, 0xfc7461d4, 0x8f827619, 0xf5c63c21,
7002 0x95b3a76d};
7003 int i;
7004
7005 for (i = 0; i <= I40E_GLQF_HKEY_MAX_INDEX; i++)
7006 wr32(&pf->hw, I40E_GLQF_HKEY(i), hkey[i]);
7007 }
7008
7009 if (!(pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_FD_SB_ENABLED))
7010 return;
7011
7012 /* find existing VSI and see if it needs configuring */
7013 vsi = i40e_find_vsi_by_type(pf, I40E_VSI_FDIR);
7014
7015 /* create a new VSI if none exists */
7016 if (!vsi) {
7017 vsi = i40e_vsi_setup(pf, I40E_VSI_FDIR,
7018 pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi]->seid, 0);
7019 if (!vsi) {
7020 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "Couldn't create FDir VSI\n");
7021 pf->flags &= ~I40E_FLAG_FD_SB_ENABLED;
7022 return;
7023 }
7024 }
7025
7026 i40e_vsi_setup_irqhandler(vsi, i40e_fdir_clean_ring);
7027}
7028
7029/**
7030 * i40e_fdir_teardown - release the Flow Director resources
7031 * @pf: board private structure
7032 **/
7033static void i40e_fdir_teardown(struct i40e_pf *pf)
7034{
7035 struct i40e_vsi *vsi;
7036
7037 i40e_fdir_filter_exit(pf);
7038 vsi = i40e_find_vsi_by_type(pf, I40E_VSI_FDIR);
7039 if (vsi)
7040 i40e_vsi_release(vsi);
7041}
7042
7043/**
7044 * i40e_prep_for_reset - prep for the core to reset
7045 * @pf: board private structure
7046 * @lock_acquired: indicates whether or not the lock has been acquired
7047 * before this function was called.
7048 *
7049 * Close up the VFs and other things in prep for PF Reset.
7050 **/
7051static void i40e_prep_for_reset(struct i40e_pf *pf, bool lock_acquired)
7052{
7053 struct i40e_hw *hw = &pf->hw;
7054 i40e_status ret = 0;
7055 u32 v;
7056
7057 clear_bit(__I40E_RESET_INTR_RECEIVED, pf->state);
7058 if (test_and_set_bit(__I40E_RESET_RECOVERY_PENDING, pf->state))
7059 return;
7060 if (i40e_check_asq_alive(&pf->hw))
7061 i40e_vc_notify_reset(pf);
7062
7063 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev, "Tearing down internal switch for reset\n");
7064
7065 /* quiesce the VSIs and their queues that are not already DOWN */
7066 /* pf_quiesce_all_vsi modifies netdev structures -rtnl_lock needed */
7067 if (!lock_acquired)
7068 rtnl_lock();
7069 i40e_pf_quiesce_all_vsi(pf);
7070 if (!lock_acquired)
7071 rtnl_unlock();
7072
7073 for (v = 0; v < pf->num_alloc_vsi; v++) {
7074 if (pf->vsi[v])
7075 pf->vsi[v]->seid = 0;
7076 }
7077
7078 i40e_shutdown_adminq(&pf->hw);
7079
7080 /* call shutdown HMC */
7081 if (hw->hmc.hmc_obj) {
7082 ret = i40e_shutdown_lan_hmc(hw);
7083 if (ret)
7084 dev_warn(&pf->pdev->dev,
7085 "shutdown_lan_hmc failed: %d\n", ret);
7086 }
7087}
7088
7089/**
7090 * i40e_send_version - update firmware with driver version
7091 * @pf: PF struct
7092 */
7093static void i40e_send_version(struct i40e_pf *pf)
7094{
7095 struct i40e_driver_version dv;
7096
7097 dv.major_version = DRV_VERSION_MAJOR;
7098 dv.minor_version = DRV_VERSION_MINOR;
7099 dv.build_version = DRV_VERSION_BUILD;
7100 dv.subbuild_version = 0;
7101 strlcpy(dv.driver_string, DRV_VERSION, sizeof(dv.driver_string));
7102 i40e_aq_send_driver_version(&pf->hw, &dv, NULL);
7103}
7104
7105/**
7106 * i40e_get_oem_version - get OEM specific version information
7107 * @hw: pointer to the hardware structure
7108 **/
7109static void i40e_get_oem_version(struct i40e_hw *hw)
7110{
7111 u16 block_offset = 0xffff;
7112 u16 block_length = 0;
7113 u16 capabilities = 0;
7114 u16 gen_snap = 0;
7115 u16 release = 0;
7116
7117#define I40E_SR_NVM_OEM_VERSION_PTR 0x1B
7118#define I40E_NVM_OEM_LENGTH_OFFSET 0x00
7119#define I40E_NVM_OEM_CAPABILITIES_OFFSET 0x01
7120#define I40E_NVM_OEM_GEN_OFFSET 0x02
7121#define I40E_NVM_OEM_RELEASE_OFFSET 0x03
7122#define I40E_NVM_OEM_CAPABILITIES_MASK 0x000F
7123#define I40E_NVM_OEM_LENGTH 3
7124
7125 /* Check if pointer to OEM version block is valid. */
7126 i40e_read_nvm_word(hw, I40E_SR_NVM_OEM_VERSION_PTR, &block_offset);
7127 if (block_offset == 0xffff)
7128 return;
7129
7130 /* Check if OEM version block has correct length. */
7131 i40e_read_nvm_word(hw, block_offset + I40E_NVM_OEM_LENGTH_OFFSET,
7132 &block_length);
7133 if (block_length < I40E_NVM_OEM_LENGTH)
7134 return;
7135
7136 /* Check if OEM version format is as expected. */
7137 i40e_read_nvm_word(hw, block_offset + I40E_NVM_OEM_CAPABILITIES_OFFSET,
7138 &capabilities);
7139 if ((capabilities & I40E_NVM_OEM_CAPABILITIES_MASK) != 0)
7140 return;
7141
7142 i40e_read_nvm_word(hw, block_offset + I40E_NVM_OEM_GEN_OFFSET,
7143 &gen_snap);
7144 i40e_read_nvm_word(hw, block_offset + I40E_NVM_OEM_RELEASE_OFFSET,
7145 &release);
7146 hw->nvm.oem_ver = (gen_snap << I40E_OEM_SNAP_SHIFT) | release;
7147 hw->nvm.eetrack = I40E_OEM_EETRACK_ID;
7148}
7149
7150/**
7151 * i40e_reset - wait for core reset to finish reset, reset pf if corer not seen
7152 * @pf: board private structure
7153 **/
7154static int i40e_reset(struct i40e_pf *pf)
7155{
7156 struct i40e_hw *hw = &pf->hw;
7157 i40e_status ret;
7158
7159 ret = i40e_pf_reset(hw);
7160 if (ret) {
7161 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "PF reset failed, %d\n", ret);
7162 set_bit(__I40E_RESET_FAILED, pf->state);
7163 clear_bit(__I40E_RESET_RECOVERY_PENDING, pf->state);
7164 } else {
7165 pf->pfr_count++;
7166 }
7167 return ret;
7168}
7169
7170/**
7171 * i40e_rebuild - rebuild using a saved config
7172 * @pf: board private structure
7173 * @reinit: if the Main VSI needs to re-initialized.
7174 * @lock_acquired: indicates whether or not the lock has been acquired
7175 * before this function was called.
7176 **/
7177static void i40e_rebuild(struct i40e_pf *pf, bool reinit, bool lock_acquired)
7178{
7179 struct i40e_hw *hw = &pf->hw;
7180 u8 set_fc_aq_fail = 0;
7181 i40e_status ret;
7182 u32 val;
7183 int v;
7184
7185 if (test_bit(__I40E_DOWN, pf->state))
7186 goto clear_recovery;
7187 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev, "Rebuilding internal switch\n");
7188
7189 /* rebuild the basics for the AdminQ, HMC, and initial HW switch */
7190 ret = i40e_init_adminq(&pf->hw);
7191 if (ret) {
7192 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "Rebuild AdminQ failed, err %s aq_err %s\n",
7193 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
7194 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw, pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
7195 goto clear_recovery;
7196 }
7197 i40e_get_oem_version(&pf->hw);
7198
7199 if (test_bit(__I40E_EMP_RESET_INTR_RECEIVED, pf->state) &&
7200 ((hw->aq.fw_maj_ver == 4 && hw->aq.fw_min_ver <= 33) ||
7201 hw->aq.fw_maj_ver < 4) && hw->mac.type == I40E_MAC_XL710) {
7202 /* The following delay is necessary for 4.33 firmware and older
7203 * to recover after EMP reset. 200 ms should suffice but we
7204 * put here 300 ms to be sure that FW is ready to operate
7205 * after reset.
7206 */
7207 mdelay(300);
7208 }
7209
7210 /* re-verify the eeprom if we just had an EMP reset */
7211 if (test_and_clear_bit(__I40E_EMP_RESET_INTR_RECEIVED, pf->state))
7212 i40e_verify_eeprom(pf);
7213
7214 i40e_clear_pxe_mode(hw);
7215 ret = i40e_get_capabilities(pf);
7216 if (ret)
7217 goto end_core_reset;
7218
7219 ret = i40e_init_lan_hmc(hw, hw->func_caps.num_tx_qp,
7220 hw->func_caps.num_rx_qp, 0, 0);
7221 if (ret) {
7222 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "init_lan_hmc failed: %d\n", ret);
7223 goto end_core_reset;
7224 }
7225 ret = i40e_configure_lan_hmc(hw, I40E_HMC_MODEL_DIRECT_ONLY);
7226 if (ret) {
7227 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "configure_lan_hmc failed: %d\n", ret);
7228 goto end_core_reset;
7229 }
7230
7231#ifdef CONFIG_I40E_DCB
7232 ret = i40e_init_pf_dcb(pf);
7233 if (ret) {
7234 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "DCB init failed %d, disabled\n", ret);
7235 pf->flags &= ~I40E_FLAG_DCB_CAPABLE;
7236 /* Continue without DCB enabled */
7237 }
7238#endif /* CONFIG_I40E_DCB */
7239 /* do basic switch setup */
7240 if (!lock_acquired)
7241 rtnl_lock();
7242 ret = i40e_setup_pf_switch(pf, reinit);
7243 if (ret)
7244 goto end_unlock;
7245
7246 /* The driver only wants link up/down and module qualification
7247 * reports from firmware. Note the negative logic.
7248 */
7249 ret = i40e_aq_set_phy_int_mask(&pf->hw,
7250 ~(I40E_AQ_EVENT_LINK_UPDOWN |
7251 I40E_AQ_EVENT_MEDIA_NA |
7252 I40E_AQ_EVENT_MODULE_QUAL_FAIL), NULL);
7253 if (ret)
7254 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "set phy mask fail, err %s aq_err %s\n",
7255 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
7256 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw, pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
7257
7258 /* make sure our flow control settings are restored */
7259 ret = i40e_set_fc(&pf->hw, &set_fc_aq_fail, true);
7260 if (ret)
7261 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev, "setting flow control: ret = %s last_status = %s\n",
7262 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
7263 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw, pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
7264
7265 /* Rebuild the VSIs and VEBs that existed before reset.
7266 * They are still in our local switch element arrays, so only
7267 * need to rebuild the switch model in the HW.
7268 *
7269 * If there were VEBs but the reconstitution failed, we'll try
7270 * try to recover minimal use by getting the basic PF VSI working.
7271 */
7272 if (pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi]->uplink_seid != pf->mac_seid) {
7273 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev, "attempting to rebuild switch\n");
7274 /* find the one VEB connected to the MAC, and find orphans */
7275 for (v = 0; v < I40E_MAX_VEB; v++) {
7276 if (!pf->veb[v])
7277 continue;
7278
7279 if (pf->veb[v]->uplink_seid == pf->mac_seid ||
7280 pf->veb[v]->uplink_seid == 0) {
7281 ret = i40e_reconstitute_veb(pf->veb[v]);
7282
7283 if (!ret)
7284 continue;
7285
7286 /* If Main VEB failed, we're in deep doodoo,
7287 * so give up rebuilding the switch and set up
7288 * for minimal rebuild of PF VSI.
7289 * If orphan failed, we'll report the error
7290 * but try to keep going.
7291 */
7292 if (pf->veb[v]->uplink_seid == pf->mac_seid) {
7293 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
7294 "rebuild of switch failed: %d, will try to set up simple PF connection\n",
7295 ret);
7296 pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi]->uplink_seid
7297 = pf->mac_seid;
7298 break;
7299 } else if (pf->veb[v]->uplink_seid == 0) {
7300 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
7301 "rebuild of orphan VEB failed: %d\n",
7302 ret);
7303 }
7304 }
7305 }
7306 }
7307
7308 if (pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi]->uplink_seid == pf->mac_seid) {
7309 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev, "attempting to rebuild PF VSI\n");
7310 /* no VEB, so rebuild only the Main VSI */
7311 ret = i40e_add_vsi(pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi]);
7312 if (ret) {
7313 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
7314 "rebuild of Main VSI failed: %d\n", ret);
7315 goto end_unlock;
7316 }
7317 }
7318
7319 /* Reconfigure hardware for allowing smaller MSS in the case
7320 * of TSO, so that we avoid the MDD being fired and causing
7321 * a reset in the case of small MSS+TSO.
7322 */
7323#define I40E_REG_MSS 0x000E64DC
7324#define I40E_REG_MSS_MIN_MASK 0x3FF0000
7325#define I40E_64BYTE_MSS 0x400000
7326 val = rd32(hw, I40E_REG_MSS);
7327 if ((val & I40E_REG_MSS_MIN_MASK) > I40E_64BYTE_MSS) {
7328 val &= ~I40E_REG_MSS_MIN_MASK;
7329 val |= I40E_64BYTE_MSS;
7330 wr32(hw, I40E_REG_MSS, val);
7331 }
7332
7333 if (pf->hw_features & I40E_HW_RESTART_AUTONEG) {
7334 msleep(75);
7335 ret = i40e_aq_set_link_restart_an(&pf->hw, true, NULL);
7336 if (ret)
7337 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "link restart failed, err %s aq_err %s\n",
7338 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
7339 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw,
7340 pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
7341 }
7342 /* reinit the misc interrupt */
7343 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_MSIX_ENABLED)
7344 ret = i40e_setup_misc_vector(pf);
7345
7346 /* Add a filter to drop all Flow control frames from any VSI from being
7347 * transmitted. By doing so we stop a malicious VF from sending out
7348 * PAUSE or PFC frames and potentially controlling traffic for other
7349 * PF/VF VSIs.
7350 * The FW can still send Flow control frames if enabled.
7351 */
7352 i40e_add_filter_to_drop_tx_flow_control_frames(&pf->hw,
7353 pf->main_vsi_seid);
7354
7355 /* restart the VSIs that were rebuilt and running before the reset */
7356 i40e_pf_unquiesce_all_vsi(pf);
7357
7358 /* Release the RTNL lock before we start resetting VFs */
7359 if (!lock_acquired)
7360 rtnl_unlock();
7361
7362 i40e_reset_all_vfs(pf, true);
7363
7364 /* tell the firmware that we're starting */
7365 i40e_send_version(pf);
7366
7367 /* We've already released the lock, so don't do it again */
7368 goto end_core_reset;
7369
7370end_unlock:
7371 if (!lock_acquired)
7372 rtnl_unlock();
7373end_core_reset:
7374 clear_bit(__I40E_RESET_FAILED, pf->state);
7375clear_recovery:
7376 clear_bit(__I40E_RESET_RECOVERY_PENDING, pf->state);
7377}
7378
7379/**
7380 * i40e_reset_and_rebuild - reset and rebuild using a saved config
7381 * @pf: board private structure
7382 * @reinit: if the Main VSI needs to re-initialized.
7383 * @lock_acquired: indicates whether or not the lock has been acquired
7384 * before this function was called.
7385 **/
7386static void i40e_reset_and_rebuild(struct i40e_pf *pf, bool reinit,
7387 bool lock_acquired)
7388{
7389 int ret;
7390 /* Now we wait for GRST to settle out.
7391 * We don't have to delete the VEBs or VSIs from the hw switch
7392 * because the reset will make them disappear.
7393 */
7394 ret = i40e_reset(pf);
7395 if (!ret)
7396 i40e_rebuild(pf, reinit, lock_acquired);
7397}
7398
7399/**
7400 * i40e_handle_reset_warning - prep for the PF to reset, reset and rebuild
7401 * @pf: board private structure
7402 *
7403 * Close up the VFs and other things in prep for a Core Reset,
7404 * then get ready to rebuild the world.
7405 * @lock_acquired: indicates whether or not the lock has been acquired
7406 * before this function was called.
7407 **/
7408static void i40e_handle_reset_warning(struct i40e_pf *pf, bool lock_acquired)
7409{
7410 i40e_prep_for_reset(pf, lock_acquired);
7411 i40e_reset_and_rebuild(pf, false, lock_acquired);
7412}
7413
7414/**
7415 * i40e_handle_mdd_event
7416 * @pf: pointer to the PF structure
7417 *
7418 * Called from the MDD irq handler to identify possibly malicious vfs
7419 **/
7420static void i40e_handle_mdd_event(struct i40e_pf *pf)
7421{
7422 struct i40e_hw *hw = &pf->hw;
7423 bool mdd_detected = false;
7424 bool pf_mdd_detected = false;
7425 struct i40e_vf *vf;
7426 u32 reg;
7427 int i;
7428
7429 if (!test_bit(__I40E_MDD_EVENT_PENDING, pf->state))
7430 return;
7431
7432 /* find what triggered the MDD event */
7433 reg = rd32(hw, I40E_GL_MDET_TX);
7434 if (reg & I40E_GL_MDET_TX_VALID_MASK) {
7435 u8 pf_num = (reg & I40E_GL_MDET_TX_PF_NUM_MASK) >>
7436 I40E_GL_MDET_TX_PF_NUM_SHIFT;
7437 u16 vf_num = (reg & I40E_GL_MDET_TX_VF_NUM_MASK) >>
7438 I40E_GL_MDET_TX_VF_NUM_SHIFT;
7439 u8 event = (reg & I40E_GL_MDET_TX_EVENT_MASK) >>
7440 I40E_GL_MDET_TX_EVENT_SHIFT;
7441 u16 queue = ((reg & I40E_GL_MDET_TX_QUEUE_MASK) >>
7442 I40E_GL_MDET_TX_QUEUE_SHIFT) -
7443 pf->hw.func_caps.base_queue;
7444 if (netif_msg_tx_err(pf))
7445 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "Malicious Driver Detection event 0x%02x on TX queue %d PF number 0x%02x VF number 0x%02x\n",
7446 event, queue, pf_num, vf_num);
7447 wr32(hw, I40E_GL_MDET_TX, 0xffffffff);
7448 mdd_detected = true;
7449 }
7450 reg = rd32(hw, I40E_GL_MDET_RX);
7451 if (reg & I40E_GL_MDET_RX_VALID_MASK) {
7452 u8 func = (reg & I40E_GL_MDET_RX_FUNCTION_MASK) >>
7453 I40E_GL_MDET_RX_FUNCTION_SHIFT;
7454 u8 event = (reg & I40E_GL_MDET_RX_EVENT_MASK) >>
7455 I40E_GL_MDET_RX_EVENT_SHIFT;
7456 u16 queue = ((reg & I40E_GL_MDET_RX_QUEUE_MASK) >>
7457 I40E_GL_MDET_RX_QUEUE_SHIFT) -
7458 pf->hw.func_caps.base_queue;
7459 if (netif_msg_rx_err(pf))
7460 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "Malicious Driver Detection event 0x%02x on RX queue %d of function 0x%02x\n",
7461 event, queue, func);
7462 wr32(hw, I40E_GL_MDET_RX, 0xffffffff);
7463 mdd_detected = true;
7464 }
7465
7466 if (mdd_detected) {
7467 reg = rd32(hw, I40E_PF_MDET_TX);
7468 if (reg & I40E_PF_MDET_TX_VALID_MASK) {
7469 wr32(hw, I40E_PF_MDET_TX, 0xFFFF);
7470 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "TX driver issue detected, PF reset issued\n");
7471 pf_mdd_detected = true;
7472 }
7473 reg = rd32(hw, I40E_PF_MDET_RX);
7474 if (reg & I40E_PF_MDET_RX_VALID_MASK) {
7475 wr32(hw, I40E_PF_MDET_RX, 0xFFFF);
7476 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "RX driver issue detected, PF reset issued\n");
7477 pf_mdd_detected = true;
7478 }
7479 /* Queue belongs to the PF, initiate a reset */
7480 if (pf_mdd_detected) {
7481 set_bit(__I40E_PF_RESET_REQUESTED, pf->state);
7482 i40e_service_event_schedule(pf);
7483 }
7484 }
7485
7486 /* see if one of the VFs needs its hand slapped */
7487 for (i = 0; i < pf->num_alloc_vfs && mdd_detected; i++) {
7488 vf = &(pf->vf[i]);
7489 reg = rd32(hw, I40E_VP_MDET_TX(i));
7490 if (reg & I40E_VP_MDET_TX_VALID_MASK) {
7491 wr32(hw, I40E_VP_MDET_TX(i), 0xFFFF);
7492 vf->num_mdd_events++;
7493 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "TX driver issue detected on VF %d\n",
7494 i);
7495 }
7496
7497 reg = rd32(hw, I40E_VP_MDET_RX(i));
7498 if (reg & I40E_VP_MDET_RX_VALID_MASK) {
7499 wr32(hw, I40E_VP_MDET_RX(i), 0xFFFF);
7500 vf->num_mdd_events++;
7501 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "RX driver issue detected on VF %d\n",
7502 i);
7503 }
7504
7505 if (vf->num_mdd_events > I40E_DEFAULT_NUM_MDD_EVENTS_ALLOWED) {
7506 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
7507 "Too many MDD events on VF %d, disabled\n", i);
7508 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
7509 "Use PF Control I/F to re-enable the VF\n");
7510 set_bit(I40E_VF_STATE_DISABLED, &vf->vf_states);
7511 }
7512 }
7513
7514 /* re-enable mdd interrupt cause */
7515 clear_bit(__I40E_MDD_EVENT_PENDING, pf->state);
7516 reg = rd32(hw, I40E_PFINT_ICR0_ENA);
7517 reg |= I40E_PFINT_ICR0_ENA_MAL_DETECT_MASK;
7518 wr32(hw, I40E_PFINT_ICR0_ENA, reg);
7519 i40e_flush(hw);
7520}
7521
7522static const char *i40e_tunnel_name(struct i40e_udp_port_config *port)
7523{
7524 switch (port->type) {
7525 case UDP_TUNNEL_TYPE_VXLAN:
7526 return "vxlan";
7527 case UDP_TUNNEL_TYPE_GENEVE:
7528 return "geneve";
7529 default:
7530 return "unknown";
7531 }
7532}
7533
7534/**
7535 * i40e_sync_udp_filters - Trigger a sync event for existing UDP filters
7536 * @pf: board private structure
7537 **/
7538static void i40e_sync_udp_filters(struct i40e_pf *pf)
7539{
7540 int i;
7541
7542 /* loop through and set pending bit for all active UDP filters */
7543 for (i = 0; i < I40E_MAX_PF_UDP_OFFLOAD_PORTS; i++) {
7544 if (pf->udp_ports[i].port)
7545 pf->pending_udp_bitmap |= BIT_ULL(i);
7546 }
7547
7548 pf->flags |= I40E_FLAG_UDP_FILTER_SYNC;
7549}
7550
7551/**
7552 * i40e_sync_udp_filters_subtask - Sync the VSI filter list with HW
7553 * @pf: board private structure
7554 **/
7555static void i40e_sync_udp_filters_subtask(struct i40e_pf *pf)
7556{
7557 struct i40e_hw *hw = &pf->hw;
7558 i40e_status ret;
7559 u16 port;
7560 int i;
7561
7562 if (!(pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_UDP_FILTER_SYNC))
7563 return;
7564
7565 pf->flags &= ~I40E_FLAG_UDP_FILTER_SYNC;
7566
7567 for (i = 0; i < I40E_MAX_PF_UDP_OFFLOAD_PORTS; i++) {
7568 if (pf->pending_udp_bitmap & BIT_ULL(i)) {
7569 pf->pending_udp_bitmap &= ~BIT_ULL(i);
7570 port = pf->udp_ports[i].port;
7571 if (port)
7572 ret = i40e_aq_add_udp_tunnel(hw, port,
7573 pf->udp_ports[i].type,
7574 NULL, NULL);
7575 else
7576 ret = i40e_aq_del_udp_tunnel(hw, i, NULL);
7577
7578 if (ret) {
7579 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
7580 "%s %s port %d, index %d failed, err %s aq_err %s\n",
7581 i40e_tunnel_name(&pf->udp_ports[i]),
7582 port ? "add" : "delete",
7583 port, i,
7584 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
7585 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw,
7586 pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
7587 pf->udp_ports[i].port = 0;
7588 }
7589 }
7590 }
7591}
7592
7593/**
7594 * i40e_service_task - Run the driver's async subtasks
7595 * @work: pointer to work_struct containing our data
7596 **/
7597static void i40e_service_task(struct work_struct *work)
7598{
7599 struct i40e_pf *pf = container_of(work,
7600 struct i40e_pf,
7601 service_task);
7602 unsigned long start_time = jiffies;
7603
7604 /* don't bother with service tasks if a reset is in progress */
7605 if (test_bit(__I40E_RESET_RECOVERY_PENDING, pf->state))
7606 return;
7607
7608 if (test_and_set_bit(__I40E_SERVICE_SCHED, pf->state))
7609 return;
7610
7611 i40e_detect_recover_hung(pf);
7612 i40e_sync_filters_subtask(pf);
7613 i40e_reset_subtask(pf);
7614 i40e_handle_mdd_event(pf);
7615 i40e_vc_process_vflr_event(pf);
7616 i40e_watchdog_subtask(pf);
7617 i40e_fdir_reinit_subtask(pf);
7618 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_CLIENT_RESET) {
7619 /* Client subtask will reopen next time through. */
7620 i40e_notify_client_of_netdev_close(pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi], true);
7621 pf->flags &= ~I40E_FLAG_CLIENT_RESET;
7622 } else {
7623 i40e_client_subtask(pf);
7624 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_CLIENT_L2_CHANGE) {
7625 i40e_notify_client_of_l2_param_changes(
7626 pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi]);
7627 pf->flags &= ~I40E_FLAG_CLIENT_L2_CHANGE;
7628 }
7629 }
7630 i40e_sync_filters_subtask(pf);
7631 i40e_sync_udp_filters_subtask(pf);
7632 i40e_clean_adminq_subtask(pf);
7633
7634 /* flush memory to make sure state is correct before next watchdog */
7635 smp_mb__before_atomic();
7636 clear_bit(__I40E_SERVICE_SCHED, pf->state);
7637
7638 /* If the tasks have taken longer than one timer cycle or there
7639 * is more work to be done, reschedule the service task now
7640 * rather than wait for the timer to tick again.
7641 */
7642 if (time_after(jiffies, (start_time + pf->service_timer_period)) ||
7643 test_bit(__I40E_ADMINQ_EVENT_PENDING, pf->state) ||
7644 test_bit(__I40E_MDD_EVENT_PENDING, pf->state) ||
7645 test_bit(__I40E_VFLR_EVENT_PENDING, pf->state))
7646 i40e_service_event_schedule(pf);
7647}
7648
7649/**
7650 * i40e_service_timer - timer callback
7651 * @data: pointer to PF struct
7652 **/
7653static void i40e_service_timer(unsigned long data)
7654{
7655 struct i40e_pf *pf = (struct i40e_pf *)data;
7656
7657 mod_timer(&pf->service_timer,
7658 round_jiffies(jiffies + pf->service_timer_period));
7659 i40e_service_event_schedule(pf);
7660}
7661
7662/**
7663 * i40e_set_num_rings_in_vsi - Determine number of rings in the VSI
7664 * @vsi: the VSI being configured
7665 **/
7666static int i40e_set_num_rings_in_vsi(struct i40e_vsi *vsi)
7667{
7668 struct i40e_pf *pf = vsi->back;
7669
7670 switch (vsi->type) {
7671 case I40E_VSI_MAIN:
7672 vsi->alloc_queue_pairs = pf->num_lan_qps;
7673 vsi->num_desc = ALIGN(I40E_DEFAULT_NUM_DESCRIPTORS,
7674 I40E_REQ_DESCRIPTOR_MULTIPLE);
7675 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_MSIX_ENABLED)
7676 vsi->num_q_vectors = pf->num_lan_msix;
7677 else
7678 vsi->num_q_vectors = 1;
7679
7680 break;
7681
7682 case I40E_VSI_FDIR:
7683 vsi->alloc_queue_pairs = 1;
7684 vsi->num_desc = ALIGN(I40E_FDIR_RING_COUNT,
7685 I40E_REQ_DESCRIPTOR_MULTIPLE);
7686 vsi->num_q_vectors = pf->num_fdsb_msix;
7687 break;
7688
7689 case I40E_VSI_VMDQ2:
7690 vsi->alloc_queue_pairs = pf->num_vmdq_qps;
7691 vsi->num_desc = ALIGN(I40E_DEFAULT_NUM_DESCRIPTORS,
7692 I40E_REQ_DESCRIPTOR_MULTIPLE);
7693 vsi->num_q_vectors = pf->num_vmdq_msix;
7694 break;
7695
7696 case I40E_VSI_SRIOV:
7697 vsi->alloc_queue_pairs = pf->num_vf_qps;
7698 vsi->num_desc = ALIGN(I40E_DEFAULT_NUM_DESCRIPTORS,
7699 I40E_REQ_DESCRIPTOR_MULTIPLE);
7700 break;
7701
7702 default:
7703 WARN_ON(1);
7704 return -ENODATA;
7705 }
7706
7707 return 0;
7708}
7709
7710/**
7711 * i40e_vsi_alloc_arrays - Allocate queue and vector pointer arrays for the vsi
7712 * @type: VSI pointer
7713 * @alloc_qvectors: a bool to specify if q_vectors need to be allocated.
7714 *
7715 * On error: returns error code (negative)
7716 * On success: returns 0
7717 **/
7718static int i40e_vsi_alloc_arrays(struct i40e_vsi *vsi, bool alloc_qvectors)
7719{
7720 struct i40e_ring **next_rings;
7721 int size;
7722 int ret = 0;
7723
7724 /* allocate memory for both Tx, XDP Tx and Rx ring pointers */
7725 size = sizeof(struct i40e_ring *) * vsi->alloc_queue_pairs *
7726 (i40e_enabled_xdp_vsi(vsi) ? 3 : 2);
7727 vsi->tx_rings = kzalloc(size, GFP_KERNEL);
7728 if (!vsi->tx_rings)
7729 return -ENOMEM;
7730 next_rings = vsi->tx_rings + vsi->alloc_queue_pairs;
7731 if (i40e_enabled_xdp_vsi(vsi)) {
7732 vsi->xdp_rings = next_rings;
7733 next_rings += vsi->alloc_queue_pairs;
7734 }
7735 vsi->rx_rings = next_rings;
7736
7737 if (alloc_qvectors) {
7738 /* allocate memory for q_vector pointers */
7739 size = sizeof(struct i40e_q_vector *) * vsi->num_q_vectors;
7740 vsi->q_vectors = kzalloc(size, GFP_KERNEL);
7741 if (!vsi->q_vectors) {
7742 ret = -ENOMEM;
7743 goto err_vectors;
7744 }
7745 }
7746 return ret;
7747
7748err_vectors:
7749 kfree(vsi->tx_rings);
7750 return ret;
7751}
7752
7753/**
7754 * i40e_vsi_mem_alloc - Allocates the next available struct vsi in the PF
7755 * @pf: board private structure
7756 * @type: type of VSI
7757 *
7758 * On error: returns error code (negative)
