7759 * On success: returns vsi index in PF (positive)
7760 **/
7761static int i40e_vsi_mem_alloc(struct i40e_pf *pf, enum i40e_vsi_type type)
7762{
7763 int ret = -ENODEV;
7764 struct i40e_vsi *vsi;
7765 int vsi_idx;
7766 int i;
7767
7768 /* Need to protect the allocation of the VSIs at the PF level */
7769 mutex_lock(&pf->switch_mutex);
7770
7771 /* VSI list may be fragmented if VSI creation/destruction has
7772 * been happening. We can afford to do a quick scan to look
7773 * for any free VSIs in the list.
7774 *
7775 * find next empty vsi slot, looping back around if necessary
7776 */
7777 i = pf->next_vsi;
7778 while (i < pf->num_alloc_vsi && pf->vsi[i])
7779 i++;
7780 if (i >= pf->num_alloc_vsi) {
7781 i = 0;
7782 while (i < pf->next_vsi && pf->vsi[i])
7783 i++;
7784 }
7785
7786 if (i < pf->num_alloc_vsi && !pf->vsi[i]) {
7787 vsi_idx = i; /* Found one! */
7788 } else {
7789 ret = -ENODEV;
7790 goto unlock_pf; /* out of VSI slots! */
7791 }
7792 pf->next_vsi = ++i;
7793
7794 vsi = kzalloc(sizeof(*vsi), GFP_KERNEL);
7795 if (!vsi) {
7796 ret = -ENOMEM;
7797 goto unlock_pf;
7798 }
7799 vsi->type = type;
7800 vsi->back = pf;
7801 set_bit(__I40E_VSI_DOWN, vsi->state);
7802 vsi->flags = 0;
7803 vsi->idx = vsi_idx;
7804 vsi->int_rate_limit = 0;
7805 vsi->rss_table_size = (vsi->type == I40E_VSI_MAIN) ?
7806 pf->rss_table_size : 64;
7807 vsi->netdev_registered = false;
7808 vsi->work_limit = I40E_DEFAULT_IRQ_WORK;
7809 hash_init(vsi->mac_filter_hash);
7810 vsi->irqs_ready = false;
7811
7812 ret = i40e_set_num_rings_in_vsi(vsi);
7813 if (ret)
7814 goto err_rings;
7815
7816 ret = i40e_vsi_alloc_arrays(vsi, true);
7817 if (ret)
7818 goto err_rings;
7819
7820 /* Setup default MSIX irq handler for VSI */
7821 i40e_vsi_setup_irqhandler(vsi, i40e_msix_clean_rings);
7822
7823 /* Initialize VSI lock */
7824 spin_lock_init(&vsi->mac_filter_hash_lock);
7825 pf->vsi[vsi_idx] = vsi;
7826 ret = vsi_idx;
7827 goto unlock_pf;
7828
7829err_rings:
7830 pf->next_vsi = i - 1;
7831 kfree(vsi);
7832unlock_pf:
7833 mutex_unlock(&pf->switch_mutex);
7834 return ret;
7835}
7836
7837/**
7838 * i40e_vsi_free_arrays - Free queue and vector pointer arrays for the VSI
7839 * @type: VSI pointer
7840 * @free_qvectors: a bool to specify if q_vectors need to be freed.
7841 *
7842 * On error: returns error code (negative)
7843 * On success: returns 0
7844 **/
7845static void i40e_vsi_free_arrays(struct i40e_vsi *vsi, bool free_qvectors)
7846{
7847 /* free the ring and vector containers */
7848 if (free_qvectors) {
7849 kfree(vsi->q_vectors);
7850 vsi->q_vectors = NULL;
7851 }
7852 kfree(vsi->tx_rings);
7853 vsi->tx_rings = NULL;
7854 vsi->rx_rings = NULL;
7855 vsi->xdp_rings = NULL;
7856}
7857
7858/**
7859 * i40e_clear_rss_config_user - clear the user configured RSS hash keys
7860 * and lookup table
7861 * @vsi: Pointer to VSI structure
7862 */
7863static void i40e_clear_rss_config_user(struct i40e_vsi *vsi)
7864{
7865 if (!vsi)
7866 return;
7867
7868 kfree(vsi->rss_hkey_user);
7869 vsi->rss_hkey_user = NULL;
7870
7871 kfree(vsi->rss_lut_user);
7872 vsi->rss_lut_user = NULL;
7873}
7874
7875/**
7876 * i40e_vsi_clear - Deallocate the VSI provided
7877 * @vsi: the VSI being un-configured
7878 **/
7879static int i40e_vsi_clear(struct i40e_vsi *vsi)
7880{
7881 struct i40e_pf *pf;
7882
7883 if (!vsi)
7884 return 0;
7885
7886 if (!vsi->back)
7887 goto free_vsi;
7888 pf = vsi->back;
7889
7890 mutex_lock(&pf->switch_mutex);
7891 if (!pf->vsi[vsi->idx]) {
7892 dev_err(&pf->pdev->dev, "pf->vsi[%d] is NULL, just free vsi[%d](%p,type %d)\n",
7893 vsi->idx, vsi->idx, vsi, vsi->type);
7894 goto unlock_vsi;
7895 }
7896
7897 if (pf->vsi[vsi->idx] != vsi) {
7898 dev_err(&pf->pdev->dev,
7899 "pf->vsi[%d](%p, type %d) != vsi[%d](%p,type %d): no free!\n",
7900 pf->vsi[vsi->idx]->idx,
7901 pf->vsi[vsi->idx],
7902 pf->vsi[vsi->idx]->type,
7903 vsi->idx, vsi, vsi->type);
7904 goto unlock_vsi;
7905 }
7906
7907 /* updates the PF for this cleared vsi */
7908 i40e_put_lump(pf->qp_pile, vsi->base_queue, vsi->idx);
7909 i40e_put_lump(pf->irq_pile, vsi->base_vector, vsi->idx);
7910
7911 i40e_vsi_free_arrays(vsi, true);
7912 i40e_clear_rss_config_user(vsi);
7913
7914 pf->vsi[vsi->idx] = NULL;
7915 if (vsi->idx < pf->next_vsi)
7916 pf->next_vsi = vsi->idx;
7917
7918unlock_vsi:
7919 mutex_unlock(&pf->switch_mutex);
7920free_vsi:
7921 kfree(vsi);
7922
7923 return 0;
7924}
7925
7926/**
7927 * i40e_vsi_clear_rings - Deallocates the Rx and Tx rings for the provided VSI
7928 * @vsi: the VSI being cleaned
7929 **/
7930static void i40e_vsi_clear_rings(struct i40e_vsi *vsi)
7931{
7932 int i;
7933
7934 if (vsi->tx_rings && vsi->tx_rings[0]) {
7935 for (i = 0; i < vsi->alloc_queue_pairs; i++) {
7936 kfree_rcu(vsi->tx_rings[i], rcu);
7937 vsi->tx_rings[i] = NULL;
7938 vsi->rx_rings[i] = NULL;
7939 if (vsi->xdp_rings)
7940 vsi->xdp_rings[i] = NULL;
7941 }
7942 }
7943}
7944
7945/**
7946 * i40e_alloc_rings - Allocates the Rx and Tx rings for the provided VSI
7947 * @vsi: the VSI being configured
7948 **/
7949static int i40e_alloc_rings(struct i40e_vsi *vsi)
7950{
7951 int i, qpv = i40e_enabled_xdp_vsi(vsi) ? 3 : 2;
7952 struct i40e_pf *pf = vsi->back;
7953 struct i40e_ring *ring;
7954
7955 /* Set basic values in the rings to be used later during open() */
7956 for (i = 0; i < vsi->alloc_queue_pairs; i++) {
7957 /* allocate space for both Tx and Rx in one shot */
7958 ring = kcalloc(qpv, sizeof(struct i40e_ring), GFP_KERNEL);
7959 if (!ring)
7960 goto err_out;
7961
7962 ring->queue_index = i;
7963 ring->reg_idx = vsi->base_queue + i;
7964 ring->ring_active = false;
7965 ring->vsi = vsi;
7966 ring->netdev = vsi->netdev;
7967 ring->dev = &pf->pdev->dev;
7968 ring->count = vsi->num_desc;
7969 ring->size = 0;
7970 ring->dcb_tc = 0;
7971 if (vsi->back->hw_features & I40E_HW_WB_ON_ITR_CAPABLE)
7972 ring->flags = I40E_TXR_FLAGS_WB_ON_ITR;
7973 ring->tx_itr_setting = pf->tx_itr_default;
7974 vsi->tx_rings[i] = ring++;
7975
7976 if (!i40e_enabled_xdp_vsi(vsi))
7977 goto setup_rx;
7978
7979 ring->queue_index = vsi->alloc_queue_pairs + i;
7980 ring->reg_idx = vsi->base_queue + ring->queue_index;
7981 ring->ring_active = false;
7982 ring->vsi = vsi;
7983 ring->netdev = NULL;
7984 ring->dev = &pf->pdev->dev;
7985 ring->count = vsi->num_desc;
7986 ring->size = 0;
7987 ring->dcb_tc = 0;
7988 if (vsi->back->hw_features & I40E_HW_WB_ON_ITR_CAPABLE)
7989 ring->flags = I40E_TXR_FLAGS_WB_ON_ITR;
7990 set_ring_xdp(ring);
7991 ring->tx_itr_setting = pf->tx_itr_default;
7992 vsi->xdp_rings[i] = ring++;
7993
7994setup_rx:
7995 ring->queue_index = i;
7996 ring->reg_idx = vsi->base_queue + i;
7997 ring->ring_active = false;
7998 ring->vsi = vsi;
7999 ring->netdev = vsi->netdev;
8000 ring->dev = &pf->pdev->dev;
8001 ring->count = vsi->num_desc;
8002 ring->size = 0;
8003 ring->dcb_tc = 0;
8004 ring->rx_itr_setting = pf->rx_itr_default;
8005 vsi->rx_rings[i] = ring;
8006 }
8007
8008 return 0;
8009
8010err_out:
8011 i40e_vsi_clear_rings(vsi);
8012 return -ENOMEM;
8013}
8014
8015/**
8016 * i40e_reserve_msix_vectors - Reserve MSI-X vectors in the kernel
8017 * @pf: board private structure
8018 * @vectors: the number of MSI-X vectors to request
8019 *
8020 * Returns the number of vectors reserved, or error
8021 **/
8022static int i40e_reserve_msix_vectors(struct i40e_pf *pf, int vectors)
8023{
8024 vectors = pci_enable_msix_range(pf->pdev, pf->msix_entries,
8025 I40E_MIN_MSIX, vectors);
8026 if (vectors < 0) {
8027 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
8028 "MSI-X vector reservation failed: %d\n", vectors);
8029 vectors = 0;
8030 }
8031
8032 return vectors;
8033}
8034
8035/**
8036 * i40e_init_msix - Setup the MSIX capability
8037 * @pf: board private structure
8038 *
8039 * Work with the OS to set up the MSIX vectors needed.
8040 *
8041 * Returns the number of vectors reserved or negative on failure
8042 **/
8043static int i40e_init_msix(struct i40e_pf *pf)
8044{
8045 struct i40e_hw *hw = &pf->hw;
8046 int cpus, extra_vectors;
8047 int vectors_left;
8048 int v_budget, i;
8049 int v_actual;
8050 int iwarp_requested = 0;
8051
8052 if (!(pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_MSIX_ENABLED))
8053 return -ENODEV;
8054
8055 /* The number of vectors we'll request will be comprised of:
8056 * - Add 1 for "other" cause for Admin Queue events, etc.
8057 * - The number of LAN queue pairs
8058 * - Queues being used for RSS.
8059 * We don't need as many as max_rss_size vectors.
8060 * use rss_size instead in the calculation since that
8061 * is governed by number of cpus in the system.
8062 * - assumes symmetric Tx/Rx pairing
8063 * - The number of VMDq pairs
8064 * - The CPU count within the NUMA node if iWARP is enabled
8065 * Once we count this up, try the request.
8066 *
8067 * If we can't get what we want, we'll simplify to nearly nothing
8068 * and try again. If that still fails, we punt.
8069 */
8070 vectors_left = hw->func_caps.num_msix_vectors;
8071 v_budget = 0;
8072
8073 /* reserve one vector for miscellaneous handler */
8074 if (vectors_left) {
8075 v_budget++;
8076 vectors_left--;
8077 }
8078
8079 /* reserve some vectors for the main PF traffic queues. Initially we
8080 * only reserve at most 50% of the available vectors, in the case that
8081 * the number of online CPUs is large. This ensures that we can enable
8082 * extra features as well. Once we've enabled the other features, we
8083 * will use any remaining vectors to reach as close as we can to the
8084 * number of online CPUs.
8085 */
8086 cpus = num_online_cpus();
8087 pf->num_lan_msix = min_t(int, cpus, vectors_left / 2);
8088 vectors_left -= pf->num_lan_msix;
8089
8090 /* reserve one vector for sideband flow director */
8091 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_FD_SB_ENABLED) {
8092 if (vectors_left) {
8093 pf->num_fdsb_msix = 1;
8094 v_budget++;
8095 vectors_left--;
8096 } else {
8097 pf->num_fdsb_msix = 0;
8098 }
8099 }
8100
8101 /* can we reserve enough for iWARP? */
8102 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_IWARP_ENABLED) {
8103 iwarp_requested = pf->num_iwarp_msix;
8104
8105 if (!vectors_left)
8106 pf->num_iwarp_msix = 0;
8107 else if (vectors_left < pf->num_iwarp_msix)
8108 pf->num_iwarp_msix = 1;
8109 v_budget += pf->num_iwarp_msix;
8110 vectors_left -= pf->num_iwarp_msix;
8111 }
8112
8113 /* any vectors left over go for VMDq support */
8114 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_VMDQ_ENABLED) {
8115 int vmdq_vecs_wanted = pf->num_vmdq_vsis * pf->num_vmdq_qps;
8116 int vmdq_vecs = min_t(int, vectors_left, vmdq_vecs_wanted);
8117
8118 if (!vectors_left) {
8119 pf->num_vmdq_msix = 0;
8120 pf->num_vmdq_qps = 0;
8121 } else {
8122 /* if we're short on vectors for what's desired, we limit
8123 * the queues per vmdq. If this is still more than are
8124 * available, the user will need to change the number of
8125 * queues/vectors used by the PF later with the ethtool
8126 * channels command
8127 */
8128 if (vmdq_vecs < vmdq_vecs_wanted)
8129 pf->num_vmdq_qps = 1;
8130 pf->num_vmdq_msix = pf->num_vmdq_qps;
8131
8132 v_budget += vmdq_vecs;
8133 vectors_left -= vmdq_vecs;
8134 }
8135 }
8136
8137 /* On systems with a large number of SMP cores, we previously limited
8138 * the number of vectors for num_lan_msix to be at most 50% of the
8139 * available vectors, to allow for other features. Now, we add back
8140 * the remaining vectors. However, we ensure that the total
8141 * num_lan_msix will not exceed num_online_cpus(). To do this, we
8142 * calculate the number of vectors we can add without going over the
8143 * cap of CPUs. For systems with a small number of CPUs this will be
8144 * zero.
8145 */
8146 extra_vectors = min_t(int, cpus - pf->num_lan_msix, vectors_left);
8147 pf->num_lan_msix += extra_vectors;
8148 vectors_left -= extra_vectors;
8149
8150 WARN(vectors_left < 0,
8151 "Calculation of remaining vectors underflowed. This is an accounting bug when determining total MSI-X vectors.\n");
8152
8153 v_budget += pf->num_lan_msix;
8154 pf->msix_entries = kcalloc(v_budget, sizeof(struct msix_entry),
8155 GFP_KERNEL);
8156 if (!pf->msix_entries)
8157 return -ENOMEM;
8158
8159 for (i = 0; i < v_budget; i++)
8160 pf->msix_entries[i].entry = i;
8161 v_actual = i40e_reserve_msix_vectors(pf, v_budget);
8162
8163 if (v_actual < I40E_MIN_MSIX) {
8164 pf->flags &= ~I40E_FLAG_MSIX_ENABLED;
8165 kfree(pf->msix_entries);
8166 pf->msix_entries = NULL;
8167 pci_disable_msix(pf->pdev);
8168 return -ENODEV;
8169
8170 } else if (v_actual == I40E_MIN_MSIX) {
8171 /* Adjust for minimal MSIX use */
8172 pf->num_vmdq_vsis = 0;
8173 pf->num_vmdq_qps = 0;
8174 pf->num_lan_qps = 1;
8175 pf->num_lan_msix = 1;
8176
8177 } else if (!vectors_left) {
8178 /* If we have limited resources, we will start with no vectors
8179 * for the special features and then allocate vectors to some
8180 * of these features based on the policy and at the end disable
8181 * the features that did not get any vectors.
8182 */
8183 int vec;
8184
8185 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
8186 "MSI-X vector limit reached, attempting to redistribute vectors\n");
8187 /* reserve the misc vector */
8188 vec = v_actual - 1;
8189
8190 /* Scale vector usage down */
8191 pf->num_vmdq_msix = 1; /* force VMDqs to only one vector */
8192 pf->num_vmdq_vsis = 1;
8193 pf->num_vmdq_qps = 1;
8194
8195 /* partition out the remaining vectors */
8196 switch (vec) {
8197 case 2:
8198 pf->num_lan_msix = 1;
8199 break;
8200 case 3:
8201 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_IWARP_ENABLED) {
8202 pf->num_lan_msix = 1;
8203 pf->num_iwarp_msix = 1;
8204 } else {
8205 pf->num_lan_msix = 2;
8206 }
8207 break;
8208 default:
8209 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_IWARP_ENABLED) {
8210 pf->num_iwarp_msix = min_t(int, (vec / 3),
8211 iwarp_requested);
8212 pf->num_vmdq_vsis = min_t(int, (vec / 3),
8213 I40E_DEFAULT_NUM_VMDQ_VSI);
8214 } else {
8215 pf->num_vmdq_vsis = min_t(int, (vec / 2),
8216 I40E_DEFAULT_NUM_VMDQ_VSI);
8217 }
8218 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_FD_SB_ENABLED) {
8219 pf->num_fdsb_msix = 1;
8220 vec--;
8221 }
8222 pf->num_lan_msix = min_t(int,
8223 (vec - (pf->num_iwarp_msix + pf->num_vmdq_vsis)),
8224 pf->num_lan_msix);
8225 pf->num_lan_qps = pf->num_lan_msix;
8226 break;
8227 }
8228 }
8229
8230 if ((pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_FD_SB_ENABLED) &&
8231 (pf->num_fdsb_msix == 0)) {
8232 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "Sideband Flowdir disabled, not enough MSI-X vectors\n");
8233 pf->flags &= ~I40E_FLAG_FD_SB_ENABLED;
8234 }
8235 if ((pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_VMDQ_ENABLED) &&
8236 (pf->num_vmdq_msix == 0)) {
8237 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "VMDq disabled, not enough MSI-X vectors\n");
8238 pf->flags &= ~I40E_FLAG_VMDQ_ENABLED;
8239 }
8240
8241 if ((pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_IWARP_ENABLED) &&
8242 (pf->num_iwarp_msix == 0)) {
8243 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "IWARP disabled, not enough MSI-X vectors\n");
8244 pf->flags &= ~I40E_FLAG_IWARP_ENABLED;
8245 }
8246 i40e_debug(&pf->hw, I40E_DEBUG_INIT,
8247 "MSI-X vector distribution: PF %d, VMDq %d, FDSB %d, iWARP %d\n",
8248 pf->num_lan_msix,
8249 pf->num_vmdq_msix * pf->num_vmdq_vsis,
8250 pf->num_fdsb_msix,
8251 pf->num_iwarp_msix);
8252
8253 return v_actual;
8254}
8255
8256/**
8257 * i40e_vsi_alloc_q_vector - Allocate memory for a single interrupt vector
8258 * @vsi: the VSI being configured
8259 * @v_idx: index of the vector in the vsi struct
8260 * @cpu: cpu to be used on affinity_mask
8261 *
8262 * We allocate one q_vector. If allocation fails we return -ENOMEM.
8263 **/
8264static int i40e_vsi_alloc_q_vector(struct i40e_vsi *vsi, int v_idx, int cpu)
8265{
8266 struct i40e_q_vector *q_vector;
8267
8268 /* allocate q_vector */
8269 q_vector = kzalloc(sizeof(struct i40e_q_vector), GFP_KERNEL);
8270 if (!q_vector)
8271 return -ENOMEM;
8272
8273 q_vector->vsi = vsi;
8274 q_vector->v_idx = v_idx;
8275 cpumask_copy(&q_vector->affinity_mask, cpu_possible_mask);
8276
8277 if (vsi->netdev)
8278 netif_napi_add(vsi->netdev, &q_vector->napi,
8279 i40e_napi_poll, NAPI_POLL_WEIGHT);
8280
8281 q_vector->rx.latency_range = I40E_LOW_LATENCY;
8282 q_vector->tx.latency_range = I40E_LOW_LATENCY;
8283
8284 /* tie q_vector and vsi together */
8285 vsi->q_vectors[v_idx] = q_vector;
8286
8287 return 0;
8288}
8289
8290/**
8291 * i40e_vsi_alloc_q_vectors - Allocate memory for interrupt vectors
8292 * @vsi: the VSI being configured
8293 *
8294 * We allocate one q_vector per queue interrupt. If allocation fails we
8295 * return -ENOMEM.
8296 **/
8297static int i40e_vsi_alloc_q_vectors(struct i40e_vsi *vsi)
8298{
8299 struct i40e_pf *pf = vsi->back;
8300 int err, v_idx, num_q_vectors, current_cpu;
8301
8302 /* if not MSIX, give the one vector only to the LAN VSI */
8303 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_MSIX_ENABLED)
8304 num_q_vectors = vsi->num_q_vectors;
8305 else if (vsi == pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi])
8306 num_q_vectors = 1;
8307 else
8308 return -EINVAL;
8309
8310 current_cpu = cpumask_first(cpu_online_mask);
8311
8312 for (v_idx = 0; v_idx < num_q_vectors; v_idx++) {
8313 err = i40e_vsi_alloc_q_vector(vsi, v_idx, current_cpu);
8314 if (err)
8315 goto err_out;
8316 current_cpu = cpumask_next(current_cpu, cpu_online_mask);
8317 if (unlikely(current_cpu >= nr_cpu_ids))
8318 current_cpu = cpumask_first(cpu_online_mask);
8319 }
8320
8321 return 0;
8322
8323err_out:
8324 while (v_idx--)
8325 i40e_free_q_vector(vsi, v_idx);
8326
8327 return err;
8328}
8329
8330/**
8331 * i40e_init_interrupt_scheme - Determine proper interrupt scheme
8332 * @pf: board private structure to initialize
8333 **/
8334static int i40e_init_interrupt_scheme(struct i40e_pf *pf)
8335{
8336 int vectors = 0;
8337 ssize_t size;
8338
8339 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_MSIX_ENABLED) {
8340 vectors = i40e_init_msix(pf);
8341 if (vectors < 0) {
8342 pf->flags &= ~(I40E_FLAG_MSIX_ENABLED |
8343 I40E_FLAG_IWARP_ENABLED |
8344 I40E_FLAG_RSS_ENABLED |
8345 I40E_FLAG_DCB_CAPABLE |
8346 I40E_FLAG_DCB_ENABLED |
8347 I40E_FLAG_SRIOV_ENABLED |
8348 I40E_FLAG_FD_SB_ENABLED |
8349 I40E_FLAG_FD_ATR_ENABLED |
8350 I40E_FLAG_VMDQ_ENABLED);
8351
8352 /* rework the queue expectations without MSIX */
8353 i40e_determine_queue_usage(pf);
8354 }
8355 }
8356
8357 if (!(pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_MSIX_ENABLED) &&
8358 (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_MSI_ENABLED)) {
8359 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "MSI-X not available, trying MSI\n");
8360 vectors = pci_enable_msi(pf->pdev);
8361 if (vectors < 0) {
8362 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "MSI init failed - %d\n",
8363 vectors);
8364 pf->flags &= ~I40E_FLAG_MSI_ENABLED;
8365 }
8366 vectors = 1; /* one MSI or Legacy vector */
8367 }
8368
8369 if (!(pf->flags & (I40E_FLAG_MSIX_ENABLED | I40E_FLAG_MSI_ENABLED)))
8370 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "MSI-X and MSI not available, falling back to Legacy IRQ\n");
8371
8372 /* set up vector assignment tracking */
8373 size = sizeof(struct i40e_lump_tracking) + (sizeof(u16) * vectors);
8374 pf->irq_pile = kzalloc(size, GFP_KERNEL);
8375 if (!pf->irq_pile) {
8376 dev_err(&pf->pdev->dev, "error allocating irq_pile memory\n");
8377 return -ENOMEM;
8378 }
8379 pf->irq_pile->num_entries = vectors;
8380 pf->irq_pile->search_hint = 0;
8381
8382 /* track first vector for misc interrupts, ignore return */
8383 (void)i40e_get_lump(pf, pf->irq_pile, 1, I40E_PILE_VALID_BIT - 1);
8384
8385 return 0;
8386}
8387
8388/**
8389 * i40e_setup_misc_vector - Setup the misc vector to handle non queue events
8390 * @pf: board private structure
8391 *
8392 * This sets up the handler for MSIX 0, which is used to manage the
8393 * non-queue interrupts, e.g. AdminQ and errors. This is not used
8394 * when in MSI or Legacy interrupt mode.
8395 **/
8396static int i40e_setup_misc_vector(struct i40e_pf *pf)
8397{
8398 struct i40e_hw *hw = &pf->hw;
8399 int err = 0;
8400
8401 /* Only request the irq if this is the first time through, and
8402 * not when we're rebuilding after a Reset
8403 */
8404 if (!test_bit(__I40E_RESET_RECOVERY_PENDING, pf->state)) {
8405 err = request_irq(pf->msix_entries[0].vector,
8406 i40e_intr, 0, pf->int_name, pf);
8407 if (err) {
8408 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
8409 "request_irq for %s failed: %d\n",
8410 pf->int_name, err);
8411 return -EFAULT;
8412 }
8413 }
8414
8415 i40e_enable_misc_int_causes(pf);
8416
8417 /* associate no queues to the misc vector */
8418 wr32(hw, I40E_PFINT_LNKLST0, I40E_QUEUE_END_OF_LIST);
8419 wr32(hw, I40E_PFINT_ITR0(I40E_RX_ITR), I40E_ITR_8K);
8420
8421 i40e_flush(hw);
8422
8423 i40e_irq_dynamic_enable_icr0(pf, true);
8424
8425 return err;
8426}
8427
8428/**
8429 * i40e_config_rss_aq - Prepare for RSS using AQ commands
8430 * @vsi: vsi structure
8431 * @seed: RSS hash seed
8432 **/
8433static int i40e_config_rss_aq(struct i40e_vsi *vsi, const u8 *seed,
8434 u8 *lut, u16 lut_size)
8435{
8436 struct i40e_pf *pf = vsi->back;
8437 struct i40e_hw *hw = &pf->hw;
8438 int ret = 0;
8439
8440 if (seed) {
8441 struct i40e_aqc_get_set_rss_key_data *seed_dw =
8442 (struct i40e_aqc_get_set_rss_key_data *)seed;
8443 ret = i40e_aq_set_rss_key(hw, vsi->id, seed_dw);
8444 if (ret) {
8445 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
8446 "Cannot set RSS key, err %s aq_err %s\n",
8447 i40e_stat_str(hw, ret),
8448 i40e_aq_str(hw, hw->aq.asq_last_status));
8449 return ret;
8450 }
8451 }
8452 if (lut) {
8453 bool pf_lut = vsi->type == I40E_VSI_MAIN ? true : false;
8454
8455 ret = i40e_aq_set_rss_lut(hw, vsi->id, pf_lut, lut, lut_size);
8456 if (ret) {
8457 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
8458 "Cannot set RSS lut, err %s aq_err %s\n",
8459 i40e_stat_str(hw, ret),
8460 i40e_aq_str(hw, hw->aq.asq_last_status));
8461 return ret;
8462 }
8463 }
8464 return ret;
8465}
8466
8467/**
8468 * i40e_get_rss_aq - Get RSS keys and lut by using AQ commands
8469 * @vsi: Pointer to vsi structure
8470 * @seed: Buffter to store the hash keys
8471 * @lut: Buffer to store the lookup table entries
8472 * @lut_size: Size of buffer to store the lookup table entries
8473 *
8474 * Return 0 on success, negative on failure
8475 */
8476static int i40e_get_rss_aq(struct i40e_vsi *vsi, const u8 *seed,
8477 u8 *lut, u16 lut_size)
8478{
8479 struct i40e_pf *pf = vsi->back;
8480 struct i40e_hw *hw = &pf->hw;
8481 int ret = 0;
8482
8483 if (seed) {
8484 ret = i40e_aq_get_rss_key(hw, vsi->id,
8485 (struct i40e_aqc_get_set_rss_key_data *)seed);
8486 if (ret) {
8487 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
8488 "Cannot get RSS key, err %s aq_err %s\n",
8489 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
8490 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw,
8491 pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
8492 return ret;
8493 }
8494 }
8495
8496 if (lut) {
8497 bool pf_lut = vsi->type == I40E_VSI_MAIN ? true : false;
8498
8499 ret = i40e_aq_get_rss_lut(hw, vsi->id, pf_lut, lut, lut_size);
8500 if (ret) {
8501 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
8502 "Cannot get RSS lut, err %s aq_err %s\n",
8503 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
8504 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw,
8505 pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
8506 return ret;
8507 }
8508 }
8509
8510 return ret;
8511}
8512
8513/**
8514 * i40e_vsi_config_rss - Prepare for VSI(VMDq) RSS if used
8515 * @vsi: VSI structure
8516 **/
8517static int i40e_vsi_config_rss(struct i40e_vsi *vsi)
8518{
8519 u8 seed[I40E_HKEY_ARRAY_SIZE];
8520 struct i40e_pf *pf = vsi->back;
8521 u8 *lut;
8522 int ret;
8523
8524 if (!(pf->hw_features & I40E_HW_RSS_AQ_CAPABLE))
8525 return 0;
8526
8527 if (!vsi->rss_size)
8528 vsi->rss_size = min_t(int, pf->alloc_rss_size,
8529 vsi->num_queue_pairs);
8530 if (!vsi->rss_size)
8531 return -EINVAL;
8532
8533 lut = kzalloc(vsi->rss_table_size, GFP_KERNEL);
8534 if (!lut)
8535 return -ENOMEM;
8536 /* Use the user configured hash keys and lookup table if there is one,
8537 * otherwise use default
8538 */
8539 if (vsi->rss_lut_user)
8540 memcpy(lut, vsi->rss_lut_user, vsi->rss_table_size);
8541 else
8542 i40e_fill_rss_lut(pf, lut, vsi->rss_table_size, vsi->rss_size);
8543 if (vsi->rss_hkey_user)
8544 memcpy(seed, vsi->rss_hkey_user, I40E_HKEY_ARRAY_SIZE);
8545 else
8546 netdev_rss_key_fill((void *)seed, I40E_HKEY_ARRAY_SIZE);
8547 ret = i40e_config_rss_aq(vsi, seed, lut, vsi->rss_table_size);
8548 kfree(lut);
8549
8550 return ret;
8551}
8552
8553/**
8554 * i40e_config_rss_reg - Configure RSS keys and lut by writing registers
8555 * @vsi: Pointer to vsi structure
8556 * @seed: RSS hash seed
8557 * @lut: Lookup table
8558 * @lut_size: Lookup table size
8559 *
8560 * Returns 0 on success, negative on failure
8561 **/
8562static int i40e_config_rss_reg(struct i40e_vsi *vsi, const u8 *seed,
8563 const u8 *lut, u16 lut_size)
8564{
8565 struct i40e_pf *pf = vsi->back;
8566 struct i40e_hw *hw = &pf->hw;
8567 u16 vf_id = vsi->vf_id;
8568 u8 i;
8569
8570 /* Fill out hash function seed */
8571 if (seed) {
8572 u32 *seed_dw = (u32 *)seed;
8573
8574 if (vsi->type == I40E_VSI_MAIN) {
8575 for (i = 0; i <= I40E_PFQF_HKEY_MAX_INDEX; i++)
8576 wr32(hw, I40E_PFQF_HKEY(i), seed_dw[i]);
8577 } else if (vsi->type == I40E_VSI_SRIOV) {
8578 for (i = 0; i <= I40E_VFQF_HKEY1_MAX_INDEX; i++)
8579 wr32(hw, I40E_VFQF_HKEY1(i, vf_id), seed_dw[i]);
8580 } else {
8581 dev_err(&pf->pdev->dev, "Cannot set RSS seed - invalid VSI type\n");
8582 }
8583 }
8584
8585 if (lut) {
8586 u32 *lut_dw = (u32 *)lut;
8587
8588 if (vsi->type == I40E_VSI_MAIN) {
8589 if (lut_size != I40E_HLUT_ARRAY_SIZE)
8590 return -EINVAL;
8591 for (i = 0; i <= I40E_PFQF_HLUT_MAX_INDEX; i++)
8592 wr32(hw, I40E_PFQF_HLUT(i), lut_dw[i]);
8593 } else if (vsi->type == I40E_VSI_SRIOV) {
8594 if (lut_size != I40E_VF_HLUT_ARRAY_SIZE)
8595 return -EINVAL;
8596 for (i = 0; i <= I40E_VFQF_HLUT_MAX_INDEX; i++)
8597 wr32(hw, I40E_VFQF_HLUT1(i, vf_id), lut_dw[i]);
8598 } else {
8599 dev_err(&pf->pdev->dev, "Cannot set RSS LUT - invalid VSI type\n");
8600 }
8601 }
8602 i40e_flush(hw);
8603
8604 return 0;
8605}
8606
8607/**
8608 * i40e_get_rss_reg - Get the RSS keys and lut by reading registers
8609 * @vsi: Pointer to VSI structure
8610 * @seed: Buffer to store the keys
8611 * @lut: Buffer to store the lookup table entries
8612 * @lut_size: Size of buffer to store the lookup table entries
8613 *
8614 * Returns 0 on success, negative on failure
8615 */
8616static int i40e_get_rss_reg(struct i40e_vsi *vsi, u8 *seed,
8617 u8 *lut, u16 lut_size)
8618{
8619 struct i40e_pf *pf = vsi->back;
8620 struct i40e_hw *hw = &pf->hw;
8621 u16 i;
8622
8623 if (seed) {
8624 u32 *seed_dw = (u32 *)seed;
8625
8626 for (i = 0; i <= I40E_PFQF_HKEY_MAX_INDEX; i++)
8627 seed_dw[i] = i40e_read_rx_ctl(hw, I40E_PFQF_HKEY(i));
8628 }
8629 if (lut) {
8630 u32 *lut_dw = (u32 *)lut;
8631
8632 if (lut_size != I40E_HLUT_ARRAY_SIZE)
8633 return -EINVAL;
8634 for (i = 0; i <= I40E_PFQF_HLUT_MAX_INDEX; i++)
8635 lut_dw[i] = rd32(hw, I40E_PFQF_HLUT(i));
8636 }
8637
8638 return 0;
8639}
8640
8641/**
8642 * i40e_config_rss - Configure RSS keys and lut
8643 * @vsi: Pointer to VSI structure
8644 * @seed: RSS hash seed
8645 * @lut: Lookup table
8646 * @lut_size: Lookup table size
8647 *
8648 * Returns 0 on success, negative on failure
8649 */
8650int i40e_config_rss(struct i40e_vsi *vsi, u8 *seed, u8 *lut, u16 lut_size)
8651{
8652 struct i40e_pf *pf = vsi->back;
8653
8654 if (pf->hw_features & I40E_HW_RSS_AQ_CAPABLE)
8655 return i40e_config_rss_aq(vsi, seed, lut, lut_size);
8656 else
8657 return i40e_config_rss_reg(vsi, seed, lut, lut_size);
8658}
8659
8660/**
8661 * i40e_get_rss - Get RSS keys and lut
8662 * @vsi: Pointer to VSI structure
8663 * @seed: Buffer to store the keys
8664 * @lut: Buffer to store the lookup table entries
8665 * lut_size: Size of buffer to store the lookup table entries
8666 *
8667 * Returns 0 on success, negative on failure
8668 */
8669int i40e_get_rss(struct i40e_vsi *vsi, u8 *seed, u8 *lut, u16 lut_size)
8670{
8671 struct i40e_pf *pf = vsi->back;
8672
8673 if (pf->hw_features & I40E_HW_RSS_AQ_CAPABLE)
8674 return i40e_get_rss_aq(vsi, seed, lut, lut_size);
8675 else
8676 return i40e_get_rss_reg(vsi, seed, lut, lut_size);
8677}
8678
8679/**
8680 * i40e_fill_rss_lut - Fill the RSS lookup table with default values
8681 * @pf: Pointer to board private structure
8682 * @lut: Lookup table
8683 * @rss_table_size: Lookup table size
8684 * @rss_size: Range of queue number for hashing
8685 */
8686void i40e_fill_rss_lut(struct i40e_pf *pf, u8 *lut,
8687 u16 rss_table_size, u16 rss_size)
8688{
8689 u16 i;
8690
8691 for (i = 0; i < rss_table_size; i++)
8692 lut[i] = i % rss_size;
8693}
8694
8695/**
8696 * i40e_pf_config_rss - Prepare for RSS if used
8697 * @pf: board private structure
8698 **/
8699static int i40e_pf_config_rss(struct i40e_pf *pf)
8700{
8701 struct i40e_vsi *vsi = pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi];
8702 u8 seed[I40E_HKEY_ARRAY_SIZE];
8703 u8 *lut;
8704 struct i40e_hw *hw = &pf->hw;
8705 u32 reg_val;
8706 u64 hena;
8707 int ret;
8708
8709 /* By default we enable TCP/UDP with IPv4/IPv6 ptypes */
8710 hena = (u64)i40e_read_rx_ctl(hw, I40E_PFQF_HENA(0)) |
8711 ((u64)i40e_read_rx_ctl(hw, I40E_PFQF_HENA(1)) << 32);
8712 hena |= i40e_pf_get_default_rss_hena(pf);
8713
8714 i40e_write_rx_ctl(hw, I40E_PFQF_HENA(0), (u32)hena);
8715 i40e_write_rx_ctl(hw, I40E_PFQF_HENA(1), (u32)(hena >> 32));
8716
8717 /* Determine the RSS table size based on the hardware capabilities */
8718 reg_val = i40e_read_rx_ctl(hw, I40E_PFQF_CTL_0);
8719 reg_val = (pf->rss_table_size == 512) ?
8720 (reg_val | I40E_PFQF_CTL_0_HASHLUTSIZE_512) :
8721 (reg_val & ~I40E_PFQF_CTL_0_HASHLUTSIZE_512);
8722 i40e_write_rx_ctl(hw, I40E_PFQF_CTL_0, reg_val);
8723
8724 /* Determine the RSS size of the VSI */
8725 if (!vsi->rss_size) {
8726 u16 qcount;
8727
8728 qcount = vsi->num_queue_pairs / vsi->tc_config.numtc;
8729 vsi->rss_size = min_t(int, pf->alloc_rss_size, qcount);
8730 }
8731 if (!vsi->rss_size)
8732 return -EINVAL;
8733
8734 lut = kzalloc(vsi->rss_table_size, GFP_KERNEL);
8735 if (!lut)
8736 return -ENOMEM;
8737
8738 /* Use user configured lut if there is one, otherwise use default */
8739 if (vsi->rss_lut_user)
8740 memcpy(lut, vsi->rss_lut_user, vsi->rss_table_size);
8741 else
8742 i40e_fill_rss_lut(pf, lut, vsi->rss_table_size, vsi->rss_size);
8743
8744 /* Use user configured hash key if there is one, otherwise
8745 * use default.
8746 */
8747 if (vsi->rss_hkey_user)
8748 memcpy(seed, vsi->rss_hkey_user, I40E_HKEY_ARRAY_SIZE);
8749 else
8750 netdev_rss_key_fill((void *)seed, I40E_HKEY_ARRAY_SIZE);
8751 ret = i40e_config_rss(vsi, seed, lut, vsi->rss_table_size);
8752 kfree(lut);
8753
8754 return ret;
8755}
8756
8757/**
8758 * i40e_reconfig_rss_queues - change number of queues for rss and rebuild
8759 * @pf: board private structure
8760 * @queue_count: the requested queue count for rss.
8761 *
8762 * returns 0 if rss is not enabled, if enabled returns the final rss queue
8763 * count which may be different from the requested queue count.
8764 * Note: expects to be called while under rtnl_lock()
8765 **/
8766int i40e_reconfig_rss_queues(struct i40e_pf *pf, int queue_count)
8767{
8768 struct i40e_vsi *vsi = pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi];
8769 int new_rss_size;
8770
8771 if (!(pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_RSS_ENABLED))
8772 return 0;
8773
8774 new_rss_size = min_t(int, queue_count, pf->rss_size_max);
8775
8776 if (queue_count != vsi->num_queue_pairs) {
8777 u16 qcount;
8778
8779 vsi->req_queue_pairs = queue_count;
8780 i40e_prep_for_reset(pf, true);
8781
8782 pf->alloc_rss_size = new_rss_size;
8783
8784 i40e_reset_and_rebuild(pf, true, true);
8785
8786 /* Discard the user configured hash keys and lut, if less
8787 * queues are enabled.
8788 */
8789 if (queue_count < vsi->rss_size) {
8790 i40e_clear_rss_config_user(vsi);
8791 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev,
8792 "discard user configured hash keys and lut\n");
8793 }
8794
8795 /* Reset vsi->rss_size, as number of enabled queues changed */
8796 qcount = vsi->num_queue_pairs / vsi->tc_config.numtc;
8797 vsi->rss_size = min_t(int, pf->alloc_rss_size, qcount);
8798
8799 i40e_pf_config_rss(pf);
8800 }
8801 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "User requested queue count/HW max RSS count: %d/%d\n",
8802 vsi->req_queue_pairs, pf->rss_size_max);
8803 return pf->alloc_rss_size;
8804}
8805
8806/**
8807 * i40e_get_partition_bw_setting - Retrieve BW settings for this PF partition
8808 * @pf: board private structure
8809 **/
8810i40e_status i40e_get_partition_bw_setting(struct i40e_pf *pf)
8811{
8812 i40e_status status;
8813 bool min_valid, max_valid;
8814 u32 max_bw, min_bw;
8815
8816 status = i40e_read_bw_from_alt_ram(&pf->hw, &max_bw, &min_bw,
8817 &min_valid, &max_valid);
8818
8819 if (!status) {
8820 if (min_valid)
8821 pf->min_bw = min_bw;
8822 if (max_valid)
8823 pf->max_bw = max_bw;
8824 }
8825
8826 return status;
8827}
8828
8829/**
8830 * i40e_set_partition_bw_setting - Set BW settings for this PF partition
8831 * @pf: board private structure
8832 **/
8833i40e_status i40e_set_partition_bw_setting(struct i40e_pf *pf)
8834{
8835 struct i40e_aqc_configure_partition_bw_data bw_data;
8836 i40e_status status;
8837
8838 /* Set the valid bit for this PF */
8839 bw_data.pf_valid_bits = cpu_to_le16(BIT(pf->hw.pf_id));
8840 bw_data.max_bw[pf->hw.pf_id] = pf->max_bw & I40E_ALT_BW_VALUE_MASK;
8841 bw_data.min_bw[pf->hw.pf_id] = pf->min_bw & I40E_ALT_BW_VALUE_MASK;
8842
8843 /* Set the new bandwidths */
8844 status = i40e_aq_configure_partition_bw(&pf->hw, &bw_data, NULL);
8845
8846 return status;
8847}
8848
8849/**
8850 * i40e_commit_partition_bw_setting - Commit BW settings for this PF partition
8851 * @pf: board private structure
8852 **/
8853i40e_status i40e_commit_partition_bw_setting(struct i40e_pf *pf)
8854{
8855 /* Commit temporary BW setting to permanent NVM image */
8856 enum i40e_admin_queue_err last_aq_status;
8857 i40e_status ret;
8858 u16 nvm_word;
8859
8860 if (pf->hw.partition_id != 1) {
8861 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
8862 "Commit BW only works on partition 1! This is partition %d",
8863 pf->hw.partition_id);
8864 ret = I40E_NOT_SUPPORTED;
8865 goto bw_commit_out;
8866 }
8867
8868 /* Acquire NVM for read access */
8869 ret = i40e_acquire_nvm(&pf->hw, I40E_RESOURCE_READ);
8870 last_aq_status = pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status;
8871 if (ret) {
8872 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
8873 "Cannot acquire NVM for read access, err %s aq_err %s\n",
8874 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
8875 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw, last_aq_status));
8876 goto bw_commit_out;
8877 }
8878
8879 /* Read word 0x10 of NVM - SW compatibility word 1 */
8880 ret = i40e_aq_read_nvm(&pf->hw,
8881 I40E_SR_NVM_CONTROL_WORD,
8882 0x10, sizeof(nvm_word), &nvm_word,
8883 false, NULL);
8884 /* Save off last admin queue command status before releasing
8885 * the NVM
8886 */
8887 last_aq_status = pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status;
8888 i40e_release_nvm(&pf->hw);
8889 if (ret) {
8890 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "NVM read error, err %s aq_err %s\n",
8891 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
8892 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw, last_aq_status));
8893 goto bw_commit_out;
8894 }
8895
8896 /* Wait a bit for NVM release to complete */
8897 msleep(50);
8898
8899 /* Acquire NVM for write access */
8900 ret = i40e_acquire_nvm(&pf->hw, I40E_RESOURCE_WRITE);
8901 last_aq_status = pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status;
8902 if (ret) {
8903 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
8904 "Cannot acquire NVM for write access, err %s aq_err %s\n",
8905 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
8906 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw, last_aq_status));
8907 goto bw_commit_out;
8908 }
8909 /* Write it back out unchanged to initiate update NVM,
8910 * which will force a write of the shadow (alt) RAM to
8911 * the NVM - thus storing the bandwidth values permanently.
8912 */
8913 ret = i40e_aq_update_nvm(&pf->hw,
8914 I40E_SR_NVM_CONTROL_WORD,
8915 0x10, sizeof(nvm_word),
8916 &nvm_word, true, NULL);
8917 /* Save off last admin queue command status before releasing
8918 * the NVM
8919 */
8920 last_aq_status = pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status;
8921 i40e_release_nvm(&pf->hw);
8922 if (ret)
8923 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
8924 "BW settings NOT SAVED, err %s aq_err %s\n",
8925 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
8926 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw, last_aq_status));
8927bw_commit_out:
8928
8929 return ret;
8930}
8931
8932/**
8933 * i40e_sw_init - Initialize general software structures (struct i40e_pf)
8934 * @pf: board private structure to initialize
8935 *
8936 * i40e_sw_init initializes the Adapter private data structure.
8937 * Fields are initialized based on PCI device information and
8938 * OS network device settings (MTU size).
8939 **/
8940static int i40e_sw_init(struct i40e_pf *pf)
8941{
8942 int err = 0;
8943 int size;
8944
8945 /* Set default capability flags */
8946 pf->flags = I40E_FLAG_RX_CSUM_ENABLED |
8947 I40E_FLAG_MSI_ENABLED |
8948 I40E_FLAG_MSIX_ENABLED;
8949
8950 /* Set default ITR */
8951 pf->rx_itr_default = I40E_ITR_DYNAMIC | I40E_ITR_RX_DEF;
8952 pf->tx_itr_default = I40E_ITR_DYNAMIC | I40E_ITR_TX_DEF;
8953
8954 /* Depending on PF configurations, it is possible that the RSS
8955 * maximum might end up larger than the available queues
8956 */
8957 pf->rss_size_max = BIT(pf->hw.func_caps.rss_table_entry_width);
8958 pf->alloc_rss_size = 1;
8959 pf->rss_table_size = pf->hw.func_caps.rss_table_size;
8960 pf->rss_size_max = min_t(int, pf->rss_size_max,
8961 pf->hw.func_caps.num_tx_qp);
8962 if (pf->hw.func_caps.rss) {
8963 pf->flags |= I40E_FLAG_RSS_ENABLED;
8964 pf->alloc_rss_size = min_t(int, pf->rss_size_max,
8965 num_online_cpus());
8966 }
8967
8968 /* MFP mode enabled */
8969 if (pf->hw.func_caps.npar_enable || pf->hw.func_caps.flex10_enable) {
8970 pf->flags |= I40E_FLAG_MFP_ENABLED;
8971 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "MFP mode Enabled\n");
8972 if (i40e_get_partition_bw_setting(pf)) {
8973 dev_warn(&pf->pdev->dev,
8974 "Could not get partition bw settings\n");
8975 } else {
8976 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
8977 "Partition BW Min = %8.8x, Max = %8.8x\n",
8978 pf->min_bw, pf->max_bw);
8979
8980 /* nudge the Tx scheduler */
8981 i40e_set_partition_bw_setting(pf);
8982 }
8983 }
8984
8985 if ((pf->hw.func_caps.fd_filters_guaranteed > 0) ||
8986 (pf->hw.func_caps.fd_filters_best_effort > 0)) {
8987 pf->flags |= I40E_FLAG_FD_ATR_ENABLED;
8988 pf->atr_sample_rate = I40E_DEFAULT_ATR_SAMPLE_RATE;
8989 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_MFP_ENABLED &&
8990 pf->hw.num_partitions > 1)
8991 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
8992 "Flow Director Sideband mode Disabled in MFP mode\n");
8993 else
8994 pf->flags |= I40E_FLAG_FD_SB_ENABLED;
8995 pf->fdir_pf_filter_count =
8996 pf->hw.func_caps.fd_filters_guaranteed;
8997 pf->hw.fdir_shared_filter_count =
8998 pf->hw.func_caps.fd_filters_best_effort;
8999 }
9000
9001 if (pf->hw.mac.type == I40E_MAC_X722) {
9002 pf->hw_features |= (I40E_HW_RSS_AQ_CAPABLE |
9003 I40E_HW_128_QP_RSS_CAPABLE |
9004 I40E_HW_ATR_EVICT_CAPABLE |
9005 I40E_HW_WB_ON_ITR_CAPABLE |
9006 I40E_HW_MULTIPLE_TCP_UDP_RSS_PCTYPE |
9007 I40E_HW_NO_PCI_LINK_CHECK |
9008 I40E_HW_USE_SET_LLDP_MIB |
9009 I40E_HW_GENEVE_OFFLOAD_CAPABLE |
9010 I40E_HW_PTP_L4_CAPABLE |
9011 I40E_HW_WOL_MC_MAGIC_PKT_WAKE |
9012 I40E_HW_OUTER_UDP_CSUM_CAPABLE);
9013
9014#define I40E_FDEVICT_PCTYPE_DEFAULT 0xc03
9015 if (rd32(&pf->hw, I40E_GLQF_FDEVICTENA(1)) !=
9016 I40E_FDEVICT_PCTYPE_DEFAULT) {
9017 dev_warn(&pf->pdev->dev,
9018 "FD EVICT PCTYPES are not right, disable FD HW EVICT\n");
9019 pf->hw_features &= ~I40E_HW_ATR_EVICT_CAPABLE;
9020 }
9021 } else if ((pf->hw.aq.api_maj_ver > 1) ||
9022 ((pf->hw.aq.api_maj_ver == 1) &&
9023 (pf->hw.aq.api_min_ver > 4))) {
9024 /* Supported in FW API version higher than 1.4 */
9025 pf->hw_features |= I40E_HW_GENEVE_OFFLOAD_CAPABLE;
9026 }
9027
9028 /* Enable HW ATR eviction if possible */
9029 if (pf->hw_features & I40E_HW_ATR_EVICT_CAPABLE)
9030 pf->flags |= I40E_FLAG_HW_ATR_EVICT_ENABLED;
9031
9032 if ((pf->hw.mac.type == I40E_MAC_XL710) &&
9033 (((pf->hw.aq.fw_maj_ver == 4) && (pf->hw.aq.fw_min_ver < 33)) ||
9034 (pf->hw.aq.fw_maj_ver < 4))) {
9035 pf->hw_features |= I40E_HW_RESTART_AUTONEG;
9036 /* No DCB support for FW < v4.33 */
9037 pf->hw_features |= I40E_HW_NO_DCB_SUPPORT;
9038 }
9039
9040 /* Disable FW LLDP if FW < v4.3 */
9041 if ((pf->hw.mac.type == I40E_MAC_XL710) &&
9042 (((pf->hw.aq.fw_maj_ver == 4) && (pf->hw.aq.fw_min_ver < 3)) ||
9043 (pf->hw.aq.fw_maj_ver < 4)))
9044 pf->hw_features |= I40E_HW_STOP_FW_LLDP;
9045
9046 /* Use the FW Set LLDP MIB API if FW > v4.40 */
9047 if ((pf->hw.mac.type == I40E_MAC_XL710) &&
9048 (((pf->hw.aq.fw_maj_ver == 4) && (pf->hw.aq.fw_min_ver >= 40)) ||
9049 (pf->hw.aq.fw_maj_ver >= 5)))
9050 pf->hw_features |= I40E_HW_USE_SET_LLDP_MIB;
9051
9052 if (pf->hw.func_caps.vmdq) {
9053 pf->num_vmdq_vsis = I40E_DEFAULT_NUM_VMDQ_VSI;
9054 pf->flags |= I40E_FLAG_VMDQ_ENABLED;
9055 pf->num_vmdq_qps = i40e_default_queues_per_vmdq(pf);
9056 }
9057
9058 if (pf->hw.func_caps.iwarp) {
9059 pf->flags |= I40E_FLAG_IWARP_ENABLED;
9060 /* IWARP needs one extra vector for CQP just like MISC.*/
9061 pf->num_iwarp_msix = (int)num_online_cpus() + 1;
9062 }
9063
9064#ifdef CONFIG_PCI_IOV
9065 if (pf->hw.func_caps.num_vfs && pf->hw.partition_id == 1) {
9066 pf->num_vf_qps = I40E_DEFAULT_QUEUES_PER_VF;
9067 pf->flags |= I40E_FLAG_SRIOV_ENABLED;
9068 pf->num_req_vfs = min_t(int,
9069 pf->hw.func_caps.num_vfs,
9070 I40E_MAX_VF_COUNT);
9071 }
9072#endif /* CONFIG_PCI_IOV */
9073 pf->eeprom_version = 0xDEAD;
9074 pf->lan_veb = I40E_NO_VEB;
9075 pf->lan_vsi = I40E_NO_VSI;
9076
9077 /* By default FW has this off for performance reasons */
9078 pf->flags &= ~I40E_FLAG_VEB_STATS_ENABLED;
9079
9080 /* set up queue assignment tracking */
9081 size = sizeof(struct i40e_lump_tracking)
9082 + (sizeof(u16) * pf->hw.func_caps.num_tx_qp);
9083 pf->qp_pile = kzalloc(size, GFP_KERNEL);
9084 if (!pf->qp_pile) {
9085 err = -ENOMEM;
9086 goto sw_init_done;
9087 }
9088 pf->qp_pile->num_entries = pf->hw.func_caps.num_tx_qp;
9089 pf->qp_pile->search_hint = 0;
9090
9091 pf->tx_timeout_recovery_level = 1;
9092
9093 mutex_init(&pf->switch_mutex);
9094
9095sw_init_done:
9096 return err;
9097}
9098
9099/**
9100 * i40e_set_ntuple - set the ntuple feature flag and take action
9101 * @pf: board private structure to initialize
9102 * @features: the feature set that the stack is suggesting
9103 *
9104 * returns a bool to indicate if reset needs to happen
9105 **/
9106bool i40e_set_ntuple(struct i40e_pf *pf, netdev_features_t features)
9107{
9108 bool need_reset = false;
9109
9110 /* Check if Flow Director n-tuple support was enabled or disabled. If
9111 * the state changed, we need to reset.
9112 */
9113 if (features & NETIF_F_NTUPLE) {
9114 /* Enable filters and mark for reset */
9115 if (!(pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_FD_SB_ENABLED))
9116 need_reset = true;
9117 /* enable FD_SB only if there is MSI-X vector */
9118 if (pf->num_fdsb_msix > 0)
9119 pf->flags |= I40E_FLAG_FD_SB_ENABLED;
9120 } else {
9121 /* turn off filters, mark for reset and clear SW filter list */
9122 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_FD_SB_ENABLED) {
9123 need_reset = true;
9124 i40e_fdir_filter_exit(pf);
9125 }
9126 pf->flags &= ~(I40E_FLAG_FD_SB_ENABLED |
9127 I40E_FLAG_FD_SB_AUTO_DISABLED);
9128 /* reset fd counters */
9129 pf->fd_add_err = 0;
9130 pf->fd_atr_cnt = 0;
9131 /* if ATR was auto disabled it can be re-enabled. */
9132 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_FD_ATR_AUTO_DISABLED) {
9133 pf->flags &= ~I40E_FLAG_FD_ATR_AUTO_DISABLED;
9134 if ((pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_FD_ATR_ENABLED) &&
9135 (I40E_DEBUG_FD & pf->hw.debug_mask))
9136 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "ATR re-enabled.\n");
9137 }
9138 }
9139 return need_reset;
9140}
9141
9142/**
9143 * i40e_clear_rss_lut - clear the rx hash lookup table
9144 * @vsi: the VSI being configured
9145 **/
9146static void i40e_clear_rss_lut(struct i40e_vsi *vsi)
9147{
9148 struct i40e_pf *pf = vsi->back;
9149 struct i40e_hw *hw = &pf->hw;
9150 u16 vf_id = vsi->vf_id;
9151 u8 i;
9152
9153 if (vsi->type == I40E_VSI_MAIN) {
9154 for (i = 0; i <= I40E_PFQF_HLUT_MAX_INDEX; i++)
9155 wr32(hw, I40E_PFQF_HLUT(i), 0);
9156 } else if (vsi->type == I40E_VSI_SRIOV) {
9157 for (i = 0; i <= I40E_VFQF_HLUT_MAX_INDEX; i++)
9158 i40e_write_rx_ctl(hw, I40E_VFQF_HLUT1(i, vf_id), 0);
9159 } else {
9160 dev_err(&pf->pdev->dev, "Cannot set RSS LUT - invalid VSI type\n");
9161 }
9162}
9163
9164/**
9165 * i40e_set_features - set the netdev feature flags
9166 * @netdev: ptr to the netdev being adjusted
9167 * @features: the feature set that the stack is suggesting
9168 * Note: expects to be called while under rtnl_lock()
9169 **/
9170static int i40e_set_features(struct net_device *netdev,
9171 netdev_features_t features)
9172{
9173 struct i40e_netdev_priv *np = netdev_priv(netdev);
9174 struct i40e_vsi *vsi = np->vsi;
9175 struct i40e_pf *pf = vsi->back;
9176 bool need_reset;
9177
9178 if (features & NETIF_F_RXHASH && !(netdev->features & NETIF_F_RXHASH))
9179 i40e_pf_config_rss(pf);
9180 else if (!(features & NETIF_F_RXHASH) &&
9181 netdev->features & NETIF_F_RXHASH)
9182 i40e_clear_rss_lut(vsi);
9183
9184 if (features & NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX)
9185 i40e_vlan_stripping_enable(vsi);
9186 else
9187 i40e_vlan_stripping_disable(vsi);
9188
9189 need_reset = i40e_set_ntuple(pf, features);
9190
9191 if (need_reset)
9192 i40e_do_reset(pf, BIT_ULL(__I40E_PF_RESET_REQUESTED), true);
9193
9194 return 0;
9195}
9196
9197/**
9198 * i40e_get_udp_port_idx - Lookup a possibly offloaded for Rx UDP port
9199 * @pf: board private structure
9200 * @port: The UDP port to look up
9201 *
9202 * Returns the index number or I40E_MAX_PF_UDP_OFFLOAD_PORTS if port not found
9203 **/
9204static u8 i40e_get_udp_port_idx(struct i40e_pf *pf, u16 port)
9205{
9206 u8 i;
9207
9208 for (i = 0; i < I40E_MAX_PF_UDP_OFFLOAD_PORTS; i++) {
9209 if (pf->udp_ports[i].port == port)
9210 return i;
9211 }
9212
9213 return i;
9214}
9215
9216/**
9217 * i40e_udp_tunnel_add - Get notifications about UDP tunnel ports that come up
9218 * @netdev: This physical port's netdev
9219 * @ti: Tunnel endpoint information
9220 **/
9221static void i40e_udp_tunnel_add(struct net_device *netdev,
9222 struct udp_tunnel_info *ti)
9223{
9224 struct i40e_netdev_priv *np = netdev_priv(netdev);
9225 struct i40e_vsi *vsi = np->vsi;
9226 struct i40e_pf *pf = vsi->back;
9227 u16 port = ntohs(ti->port);
9228 u8 next_idx;
9229 u8 idx;
9230
9231 idx = i40e_get_udp_port_idx(pf, port);
9232
9233 /* Check if port already exists */
9234 if (idx < I40E_MAX_PF_UDP_OFFLOAD_PORTS) {
9235 netdev_info(netdev, "port %d already offloaded\n", port);
9236 return;
9237 }
9238
9239 /* Now check if there is space to add the new port */
9240 next_idx = i40e_get_udp_port_idx(pf, 0);
9241
9242 if (next_idx == I40E_MAX_PF_UDP_OFFLOAD_PORTS) {
9243 netdev_info(netdev, "maximum number of offloaded UDP ports reached, not adding port %d\n",
9244 port);
9245 return;
9246 }
9247
9248 switch (ti->type) {
9249 case UDP_TUNNEL_TYPE_VXLAN:
9250 pf->udp_ports[next_idx].type = I40E_AQC_TUNNEL_TYPE_VXLAN;
9251 break;
9252 case UDP_TUNNEL_TYPE_GENEVE:
9253 if (!(pf->hw_features & I40E_HW_GENEVE_OFFLOAD_CAPABLE))
9254 return;
9255 pf->udp_ports[next_idx].type = I40E_AQC_TUNNEL_TYPE_NGE;
9256 break;
9257 default:
9258 return;
9259 }
9260
9261 /* New port: add it and mark its index in the bitmap */
9262 pf->udp_ports[next_idx].port = port;
9263 pf->pending_udp_bitmap |= BIT_ULL(next_idx);
9264 pf->flags |= I40E_FLAG_UDP_FILTER_SYNC;
9265}
9266
9267/**
9268 * i40e_udp_tunnel_del - Get notifications about UDP tunnel ports that go away
9269 * @netdev: This physical port's netdev
9270 * @ti: Tunnel endpoint information
9271 **/
9272static void i40e_udp_tunnel_del(struct net_device *netdev,
9273 struct udp_tunnel_info *ti)
9274{
9275 struct i40e_netdev_priv *np = netdev_priv(netdev);
9276 struct i40e_vsi *vsi = np->vsi;
9277 struct i40e_pf *pf = vsi->back;
9278 u16 port = ntohs(ti->port);
9279 u8 idx;
9280
9281 idx = i40e_get_udp_port_idx(pf, port);
9282
9283 /* Check if port already exists */
9284 if (idx >= I40E_MAX_PF_UDP_OFFLOAD_PORTS)
9285 goto not_found;
9286
9287 switch (ti->type) {
9288 case UDP_TUNNEL_TYPE_VXLAN:
9289 if (pf->udp_ports[idx].type != I40E_AQC_TUNNEL_TYPE_VXLAN)
9290 goto not_found;
9291 break;
9292 case UDP_TUNNEL_TYPE_GENEVE:
9293 if (pf->udp_ports[idx].type != I40E_AQC_TUNNEL_TYPE_NGE)
9294 goto not_found;
9295 break;
9296 default:
9297 goto not_found;
9298 }
9299
9300 /* if port exists, set it to 0 (mark for deletion)
9301 * and make it pending
9302 */
9303 pf->udp_ports[idx].port = 0;
9304 pf->pending_udp_bitmap |= BIT_ULL(idx);
9305 pf->flags |= I40E_FLAG_UDP_FILTER_SYNC;
9306
9307 return;
9308not_found:
9309 netdev_warn(netdev, "UDP port %d was not found, not deleting\n",
9310 port);
9311}
9312
9313static int i40e_get_phys_port_id(struct net_device *netdev,
9314 struct netdev_phys_item_id *ppid)
9315{
9316 struct i40e_netdev_priv *np = netdev_priv(netdev);
9317 struct i40e_pf *pf = np->vsi->back;
9318 struct i40e_hw *hw = &pf->hw;
9319
9320 if (!(pf->hw_features & I40E_HW_PORT_ID_VALID))
9321 return -EOPNOTSUPP;
9322
9323 ppid->id_len = min_t(int, sizeof(hw->mac.port_addr), sizeof(ppid->id));
9324 memcpy(ppid->id, hw->mac.port_addr, ppid->id_len);
9325
9326 return 0;
9327}
9328
9329/**
9330 * i40e_ndo_fdb_add - add an entry to the hardware database
9331 * @ndm: the input from the stack
9332 * @tb: pointer to array of nladdr (unused)
9333 * @dev: the net device pointer
9334 * @addr: the MAC address entry being added
9335 * @flags: instructions from stack about fdb operation
9336 */
9337static int i40e_ndo_fdb_add(struct ndmsg *ndm, struct nlattr *tb[],
9338 struct net_device *dev,
9339 const unsigned char *addr, u16 vid,
9340 u16 flags)
9341{
9342 struct i40e_netdev_priv *np = netdev_priv(dev);
9343 struct i40e_pf *pf = np->vsi->back;
9344 int err = 0;
9345
9346 if (!(pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_SRIOV_ENABLED))
9347 return -EOPNOTSUPP;
9348
9349 if (vid) {
9350 pr_info("%s: vlans aren't supported yet for dev_uc|mc_add()\n", dev->name);
9351 return -EINVAL;
9352 }
9353
9354 /* Hardware does not support aging addresses so if a
9355 * ndm_state is given only allow permanent addresses
9356 */
9357 if (ndm->ndm_state && !(ndm->ndm_state & NUD_PERMANENT)) {
9358 netdev_info(dev, "FDB only supports static addresses\n");
9359 return -EINVAL;
9360 }
9361
9362 if (is_unicast_ether_addr(addr) || is_link_local_ether_addr(addr))
9363 err = dev_uc_add_excl(dev, addr);
9364 else if (is_multicast_ether_addr(addr))
9365 err = dev_mc_add_excl(dev, addr);
9366 else
9367 err = -EINVAL;
9368
9369 /* Only return duplicate errors if NLM_F_EXCL is set */
9370 if (err == -EEXIST && !(flags & NLM_F_EXCL))
9371 err = 0;
9372
9373 return err;
9374}
9375
9376/**
9377 * i40e_ndo_bridge_setlink - Set the hardware bridge mode
9378 * @dev: the netdev being configured
9379 * @nlh: RTNL message
9380 *
9381 * Inserts a new hardware bridge if not already created and
9382 * enables the bridging mode requested (VEB or VEPA). If the
9383 * hardware bridge has already been inserted and the request
9384 * is to change the mode then that requires a PF reset to
9385 * allow rebuild of the components with required hardware
9386 * bridge mode enabled.
9387 *
9388 * Note: expects to be called while under rtnl_lock()
9389 **/
9390static int i40e_ndo_bridge_setlink(struct net_device *dev,
9391 struct nlmsghdr *nlh,
9392 u16 flags)
9393{
9394 struct i40e_netdev_priv *np = netdev_priv(dev);
9395 struct i40e_vsi *vsi = np->vsi;
9396 struct i40e_pf *pf = vsi->back;
9397 struct i40e_veb *veb = NULL;
9398 struct nlattr *attr, *br_spec;
9399 int i, rem;
9400
9401 /* Only for PF VSI for now */
9402 if (vsi->seid != pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi]->seid)
9403 return -EOPNOTSUPP;
9404
9405 /* Find the HW bridge for PF VSI */
9406 for (i = 0; i < I40E_MAX_VEB && !veb; i++) {
9407 if (pf->veb[i] && pf->veb[i]->seid == vsi->uplink_seid)
9408 veb = pf->veb[i];
9409 }
9410
9411 br_spec = nlmsg_find_attr(nlh, sizeof(struct ifinfomsg), IFLA_AF_SPEC);
9412
9413 nla_for_each_nested(attr, br_spec, rem) {
9414 __u16 mode;
9415
9416 if (nla_type(attr) != IFLA_BRIDGE_MODE)
9417 continue;
9418
9419 mode = nla_get_u16(attr);
9420 if ((mode != BRIDGE_MODE_VEPA) &&
9421 (mode != BRIDGE_MODE_VEB))
9422 return -EINVAL;
9423
9424 /* Insert a new HW bridge */
9425 if (!veb) {
9426 veb = i40e_veb_setup(pf, 0, vsi->uplink_seid, vsi->seid,
9427 vsi->tc_config.enabled_tc);
9428 if (veb) {
9429 veb->bridge_mode = mode;
9430 i40e_config_bridge_mode(veb);
9431 } else {
9432 /* No Bridge HW offload available */
9433 return -ENOENT;
9434 }
9435 break;
9436 } else if (mode != veb->bridge_mode) {
9437 /* Existing HW bridge but different mode needs reset */
9438 veb->bridge_mode = mode;
9439 /* TODO: If no VFs or VMDq VSIs, disallow VEB mode */
9440 if (mode == BRIDGE_MODE_VEB)
9441 pf->flags |= I40E_FLAG_VEB_MODE_ENABLED;
9442 else
9443 pf->flags &= ~I40E_FLAG_VEB_MODE_ENABLED;
9444 i40e_do_reset(pf, BIT_ULL(__I40E_PF_RESET_REQUESTED),
9445 true);
9446 break;
9447 }
9448 }
9449
9450 return 0;
9451}
9452
9453/**
9454 * i40e_ndo_bridge_getlink - Get the hardware bridge mode
9455 * @skb: skb buff
9456 * @pid: process id
9457 * @seq: RTNL message seq #
9458 * @dev: the netdev being configured
9459 * @filter_mask: unused
9460 * @nlflags: netlink flags passed in
9461 *
9462 * Return the mode in which the hardware bridge is operating in
9463 * i.e VEB or VEPA.
9464 **/
9465static int i40e_ndo_bridge_getlink(struct sk_buff *skb, u32 pid, u32 seq,
9466 struct net_device *dev,
9467 u32 __always_unused filter_mask,
9468 int nlflags)
9469{
9470 struct i40e_netdev_priv *np = netdev_priv(dev);
9471 struct i40e_vsi *vsi = np->vsi;
9472 struct i40e_pf *pf = vsi->back;
9473 struct i40e_veb *veb = NULL;
9474 int i;
9475
9476 /* Only for PF VSI for now */
9477 if (vsi->seid != pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi]->seid)
9478 return -EOPNOTSUPP;
9479
9480 /* Find the HW bridge for the PF VSI */
9481 for (i = 0; i < I40E_MAX_VEB && !veb; i++) {
9482 if (pf->veb[i] && pf->veb[i]->seid == vsi->uplink_seid)
9483 veb = pf->veb[i];
9484 }
9485
9486 if (!veb)
9487 return 0;
9488
9489 return ndo_dflt_bridge_getlink(skb, pid, seq, dev, veb->bridge_mode,
9490 0, 0, nlflags, filter_mask, NULL);
9491}
9492
9493/**
9494 * i40e_features_check - Validate encapsulated packet conforms to limits
9495 * @skb: skb buff
9496 * @dev: This physical port's netdev
9497 * @features: Offload features that the stack believes apply
9498 **/
9499static netdev_features_t i40e_features_check(struct sk_buff *skb,
9500 struct net_device *dev,
9501 netdev_features_t features)
9502{
9503 size_t len;
9504
9505 /* No point in doing any of this if neither checksum nor GSO are
9506 * being requested for this frame. We can rule out both by just
9507 * checking for CHECKSUM_PARTIAL
9508 */
9509 if (skb->ip_summed != CHECKSUM_PARTIAL)
9510 return features;
9511
9512 /* We cannot support GSO if the MSS is going to be less than
9513 * 64 bytes. If it is then we need to drop support for GSO.
9514 */
9515 if (skb_is_gso(skb) && (skb_shinfo(skb)->gso_size < 64))
9516 features &= ~NETIF_F_GSO_MASK;
9517
9518 /* MACLEN can support at most 63 words */
9519 len = skb_network_header(skb) - skb->data;
9520 if (len & ~(63 * 2))
9521 goto out_err;
9522
9523 /* IPLEN and EIPLEN can support at most 127 dwords */
9524 len = skb_transport_header(skb) - skb_network_header(skb);
9525 if (len & ~(127 * 4))
9526 goto out_err;
9527
9528 if (skb->encapsulation) {
9529 /* L4TUNLEN can support 127 words */
9530 len = skb_inner_network_header(skb) - skb_transport_header(skb);
9531 if (len & ~(127 * 2))
9532 goto out_err;
9533
9534 /* IPLEN can support at most 127 dwords */
9535 len = skb_inner_transport_header(skb) -
9536 skb_inner_network_header(skb);
9537 if (len & ~(127 * 4))
9538 goto out_err;
9539 }
9540
9541 /* No need to validate L4LEN as TCP is the only protocol with a
9542 * a flexible value and we support all possible values supported
9543 * by TCP, which is at most 15 dwords
9544 */
9545
9546 return features;
9547out_err:
9548 return features & ~(NETIF_F_CSUM_MASK | NETIF_F_GSO_MASK);
9549}
9550
9551/**
9552 * i40e_xdp_setup - add/remove an XDP program
9553 * @vsi: VSI to changed
9554 * @prog: XDP program
9555 **/
9556static int i40e_xdp_setup(struct i40e_vsi *vsi,
9557 struct bpf_prog *prog)
9558{
9559 int frame_size = vsi->netdev->mtu + ETH_HLEN + ETH_FCS_LEN + VLAN_HLEN;
9560 struct i40e_pf *pf = vsi->back;
9561 struct bpf_prog *old_prog;
9562 bool need_reset;
9563 int i;
9564
9565 /* Don't allow frames that span over multiple buffers */
9566 if (frame_size > vsi->rx_buf_len)
9567 return -EINVAL;
9568
9569 if (!i40e_enabled_xdp_vsi(vsi) && !prog)
9570 return 0;
9571
9572 /* When turning XDP on->off/off->on we reset and rebuild the rings. */
9573 need_reset = (i40e_enabled_xdp_vsi(vsi) != !!prog);
9574
9575 if (need_reset)
9576 i40e_prep_for_reset(pf, true);
9577
9578 old_prog = xchg(&vsi->xdp_prog, prog);
9579
9580 if (need_reset)
9581 i40e_reset_and_rebuild(pf, true, true);
9582
9583 for (i = 0; i < vsi->num_queue_pairs; i++)
9584 WRITE_ONCE(vsi->rx_rings[i]->xdp_prog, vsi->xdp_prog);
9585
9586 if (old_prog)
9587 bpf_prog_put(old_prog);
9588
9589 return 0;
9590}
9591
9592/**
9593 * i40e_xdp - implements ndo_xdp for i40e
9594 * @dev: netdevice
9595 * @xdp: XDP command
9596 **/
9597static int i40e_xdp(struct net_device *dev,
9598 struct netdev_xdp *xdp)
9599{
9600 struct i40e_netdev_priv *np = netdev_priv(dev);
9601 struct i40e_vsi *vsi = np->vsi;
9602
9603 if (vsi->type != I40E_VSI_MAIN)
9604 return -EINVAL;
9605
9606 switch (xdp->command) {
9607 case XDP_SETUP_PROG:
9608 return i40e_xdp_setup(vsi, xdp->prog);
9609 case XDP_QUERY_PROG:
9610 xdp->prog_attached = i40e_enabled_xdp_vsi(vsi);
9611 xdp->prog_id = vsi->xdp_prog ? vsi->xdp_prog->aux->id : 0;
9612 return 0;
9613 default:
9614 return -EINVAL;
9615 }
9616}

9653/**
9654 * i40e_config_netdev - Setup the netdev flags
9655 * @vsi: the VSI being configured
9656 *
9657 * Returns 0 on success, negative value on failure
9658 **/
9659static int i40e_config_netdev(struct i40e_vsi *vsi)
9660{
9661 struct i40e_pf *pf = vsi->back;
9662 struct i40e_hw *hw = &pf->hw;
9663 struct i40e_netdev_priv *np;
9664 struct net_device *netdev;
9665 u8 broadcast[ETH_ALEN];
9666 u8 mac_addr[ETH_ALEN];
9667 int etherdev_size;
9668 netdev_features_t hw_enc_features;
9669 netdev_features_t hw_features;
9670
9671 etherdev_size = sizeof(struct i40e_netdev_priv);
9672 netdev = alloc_etherdev_mq(etherdev_size, vsi->alloc_queue_pairs);
9673 if (!netdev)
9674 return -ENOMEM;
9675
9676 vsi->netdev = netdev;
9677 np = netdev_priv(netdev);
9678 np->vsi = vsi;
9679
9680 hw_enc_features = NETIF_F_SG |
9681 NETIF_F_IP_CSUM |
9682 NETIF_F_IPV6_CSUM |
9683 NETIF_F_HIGHDMA |
9684 NETIF_F_SOFT_FEATURES |
9685 NETIF_F_TSO |
9686 NETIF_F_TSO_ECN |
9687 NETIF_F_TSO6 |
9688 NETIF_F_GSO_GRE |
9689 NETIF_F_GSO_GRE_CSUM |
9690 NETIF_F_GSO_PARTIAL |
9691 NETIF_F_GSO_UDP_TUNNEL |
9692 NETIF_F_GSO_UDP_TUNNEL_CSUM |
9693 NETIF_F_SCTP_CRC |
9694 NETIF_F_RXHASH |
9695 NETIF_F_RXCSUM |
9696 0;
9697
9698 if (!(pf->hw_features & I40E_HW_OUTER_UDP_CSUM_CAPABLE))
9699 netdev->gso_partial_features |= NETIF_F_GSO_UDP_TUNNEL_CSUM;
9700
9701 netdev->gso_partial_features |= NETIF_F_GSO_GRE_CSUM;
9702
9703 netdev->hw_enc_features |= hw_enc_features;
9704
9705 /* record features VLANs can make use of */
9706 netdev->vlan_features |= hw_enc_features | NETIF_F_TSO_MANGLEID;
9707
9708 if (!(pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_MFP_ENABLED))
9709 netdev->hw_features |= NETIF_F_NTUPLE;
9710 hw_features = hw_enc_features |
9711 NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_TX |
9712 NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX;
9713
9714 netdev->hw_features |= hw_features;
9715
9716 netdev->features |= hw_features | NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_FILTER;
9717 netdev->hw_enc_features |= NETIF_F_TSO_MANGLEID;
9718
9719 if (vsi->type == I40E_VSI_MAIN) {
9720 SET_NETDEV_DEV(netdev, &pf->pdev->dev);
9721 ether_addr_copy(mac_addr, hw->mac.perm_addr);
9722 /* The following steps are necessary for two reasons. First,
9723 * some older NVM configurations load a default MAC-VLAN
9724 * filter that will accept any tagged packet, and we want to
9725 * replace this with a normal filter. Additionally, it is
9726 * possible our MAC address was provided by the platform using
9727 * Open Firmware or similar.
9728 *
9729 * Thus, we need to remove the default filter and install one
9730 * specific to the MAC address.
9731 */
9732 i40e_rm_default_mac_filter(vsi, mac_addr);
9733 spin_lock_bh(&vsi->mac_filter_hash_lock);
9734 i40e_add_mac_filter(vsi, mac_addr);
9735 spin_unlock_bh(&vsi->mac_filter_hash_lock);
9736 } else {
9737 /* Relate the VSI_VMDQ name to the VSI_MAIN name. Note that we
9738 * are still limited by IFNAMSIZ, but we're adding 'v%d\0' to
9739 * the end, which is 4 bytes long, so force truncation of the
9740 * original name by IFNAMSIZ - 4
9741 */
9742 snprintf(netdev->name, IFNAMSIZ, "%.*sv%%d",
9743 IFNAMSIZ - 4,
9744 pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi]->netdev->name);
9745 random_ether_addr(mac_addr);
9746
9747 spin_lock_bh(&vsi->mac_filter_hash_lock);
9748 i40e_add_mac_filter(vsi, mac_addr);
9749 spin_unlock_bh(&vsi->mac_filter_hash_lock);
9750 }
9751
9752 /* Add the broadcast filter so that we initially will receive
9753 * broadcast packets. Note that when a new VLAN is first added the
9754 * driver will convert all filters marked I40E_VLAN_ANY into VLAN
9755 * specific filters as part of transitioning into "vlan" operation.
9756 * When more VLANs are added, the driver will copy each existing MAC
9757 * filter and add it for the new VLAN.
9758 *
9759 * Broadcast filters are handled specially by
9760 * i40e_sync_filters_subtask, as the driver must to set the broadcast
9761 * promiscuous bit instead of adding this directly as a MAC/VLAN
9762 * filter. The subtask will update the correct broadcast promiscuous
9763 * bits as VLANs become active or inactive.
9764 */
9765 eth_broadcast_addr(broadcast);
9766 spin_lock_bh(&vsi->mac_filter_hash_lock);
9767 i40e_add_mac_filter(vsi, broadcast);
9768 spin_unlock_bh(&vsi->mac_filter_hash_lock);
9769
9770 ether_addr_copy(netdev->dev_addr, mac_addr);
9771 ether_addr_copy(netdev->perm_addr, mac_addr);
9772
9773 netdev->priv_flags |= IFF_UNICAST_FLT;
9774 netdev->priv_flags |= IFF_SUPP_NOFCS;
9775 /* Setup netdev TC information */
9776 i40e_vsi_config_netdev_tc(vsi, vsi->tc_config.enabled_tc);
9777
9778 netdev->netdev_ops = &i40e_netdev_ops;
9779 netdev->watchdog_timeo = 5 * HZ;
9780 i40e_set_ethtool_ops(netdev);
9781
9782 /* MTU range: 68 - 9706 */
9783 netdev->min_mtu = ETH_MIN_MTU;
9784 netdev->max_mtu = I40E_MAX_RXBUFFER - I40E_PACKET_HDR_PAD;
9785
9786 return 0;
9787}
9788
9789/**
9790 * i40e_vsi_delete - Delete a VSI from the switch
9791 * @vsi: the VSI being removed
9792 *
9793 * Returns 0 on success, negative value on failure
9794 **/
9795static void i40e_vsi_delete(struct i40e_vsi *vsi)
9796{
9797 /* remove default VSI is not allowed */
9798 if (vsi == vsi->back->vsi[vsi->back->lan_vsi])
9799 return;
9800
9801 i40e_aq_delete_element(&vsi->back->hw, vsi->seid, NULL);
9802}
9803
9804/**
9805 * i40e_is_vsi_uplink_mode_veb - Check if the VSI's uplink bridge mode is VEB
9806 * @vsi: the VSI being queried
9807 *
9808 * Returns 1 if HW bridge mode is VEB and return 0 in case of VEPA mode
9809 **/
9810int i40e_is_vsi_uplink_mode_veb(struct i40e_vsi *vsi)
9811{
9812 struct i40e_veb *veb;
9813 struct i40e_pf *pf = vsi->back;
9814
9815 /* Uplink is not a bridge so default to VEB */
9816 if (vsi->veb_idx == I40E_NO_VEB)
9817 return 1;
9818
9819 veb = pf->veb[vsi->veb_idx];
9820 if (!veb) {
9821 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
9822 "There is no veb associated with the bridge\n");
9823 return -ENOENT;
9824 }
9825
9826 /* Uplink is a bridge in VEPA mode */
9827 if (veb->bridge_mode & BRIDGE_MODE_VEPA) {
9828 return 0;
9829 } else {
9830 /* Uplink is a bridge in VEB mode */
9831 return 1;
9832 }
9833
9834 /* VEPA is now default bridge, so return 0 */
9835 return 0;
9836}
9837
9838/**
9839 * i40e_add_vsi - Add a VSI to the switch
9840 * @vsi: the VSI being configured
9841 *
9842 * This initializes a VSI context depending on the VSI type to be added and
9843 * passes it down to the add_vsi aq command.
9844 **/
9845static int i40e_add_vsi(struct i40e_vsi *vsi)
9846{
9847 int ret = -ENODEV;
9848 struct i40e_pf *pf = vsi->back;
9849 struct i40e_hw *hw = &pf->hw;
9850 struct i40e_vsi_context ctxt;
9851 struct i40e_mac_filter *f;
9852 struct hlist_node *h;
9853 int bkt;
9854
9855 u8 enabled_tc = 0x1; /* TC0 enabled */
9856 int f_count = 0;
9857
9858 memset(&ctxt, 0, sizeof(ctxt));
9859 switch (vsi->type) {
9860 case I40E_VSI_MAIN:
9861 /* The PF's main VSI is already setup as part of the
9862 * device initialization, so we'll not bother with
9863 * the add_vsi call, but we will retrieve the current
9864 * VSI context.
9865 */
9866 ctxt.seid = pf->main_vsi_seid;
9867 ctxt.pf_num = pf->hw.pf_id;
9868 ctxt.vf_num = 0;
9869 ret = i40e_aq_get_vsi_params(&pf->hw, &ctxt, NULL);
9870 ctxt.flags = I40E_AQ_VSI_TYPE_PF;
9871 if (ret) {
9872 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
9873 "couldn't get PF vsi config, err %s aq_err %s\n",
9874 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
9875 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw,
9876 pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
9877 return -ENOENT;
9878 }
9879 vsi->info = ctxt.info;
9880 vsi->info.valid_sections = 0;
9881
9882 vsi->seid = ctxt.seid;
9883 vsi->id = ctxt.vsi_number;
9884
9885 enabled_tc = i40e_pf_get_tc_map(pf);
9886
9887 /* MFP mode setup queue map and update VSI */
9888 if ((pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_MFP_ENABLED) &&
9889 !(pf->hw.func_caps.iscsi)) { /* NIC type PF */
9890 memset(&ctxt, 0, sizeof(ctxt));
9891 ctxt.seid = pf->main_vsi_seid;
9892 ctxt.pf_num = pf->hw.pf_id;
9893 ctxt.vf_num = 0;
9894 i40e_vsi_setup_queue_map(vsi, &ctxt, enabled_tc, false);
9895 ret = i40e_aq_update_vsi_params(hw, &ctxt, NULL);
9896 if (ret) {
9897 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
9898 "update vsi failed, err %s aq_err %s\n",
9899 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
9900 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw,
9901 pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
9902 ret = -ENOENT;
9903 goto err;
9904 }
9905 /* update the local VSI info queue map */
9906 i40e_vsi_update_queue_map(vsi, &ctxt);
9907 vsi->info.valid_sections = 0;
9908 } else {
9909 /* Default/Main VSI is only enabled for TC0
9910 * reconfigure it to enable all TCs that are
9911 * available on the port in SFP mode.
9912 * For MFP case the iSCSI PF would use this
9913 * flow to enable LAN+iSCSI TC.
9914 */
9915 ret = i40e_vsi_config_tc(vsi, enabled_tc);
9916 if (ret) {
9917 /* Single TC condition is not fatal,
9918 * message and continue
9919 */
9920 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
9921 "failed to configure TCs for main VSI tc_map 0x%08x, err %s aq_err %s\n",
9922 enabled_tc,
9923 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
9924 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw,
9925 pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
9926 }
9927 }
9928 break;
9929
9930 case I40E_VSI_FDIR:
9931 ctxt.pf_num = hw->pf_id;
9932 ctxt.vf_num = 0;
9933 ctxt.uplink_seid = vsi->uplink_seid;
9934 ctxt.connection_type = I40E_AQ_VSI_CONN_TYPE_NORMAL;
9935 ctxt.flags = I40E_AQ_VSI_TYPE_PF;
9936 if ((pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_VEB_MODE_ENABLED) &&
9937 (i40e_is_vsi_uplink_mode_veb(vsi))) {
9938 ctxt.info.valid_sections |=
9939 cpu_to_le16(I40E_AQ_VSI_PROP_SWITCH_VALID);
9940 ctxt.info.switch_id =
9941 cpu_to_le16(I40E_AQ_VSI_SW_ID_FLAG_ALLOW_LB);
9942 }
9943 i40e_vsi_setup_queue_map(vsi, &ctxt, enabled_tc, true);
9944 break;
9945
9946 case I40E_VSI_VMDQ2:
9947 ctxt.pf_num = hw->pf_id;
9948 ctxt.vf_num = 0;
9949 ctxt.uplink_seid = vsi->uplink_seid;
9950 ctxt.connection_type = I40E_AQ_VSI_CONN_TYPE_NORMAL;
9951 ctxt.flags = I40E_AQ_VSI_TYPE_VMDQ2;
9952
9953 /* This VSI is connected to VEB so the switch_id
9954 * should be set to zero by default.
9955 */
9956 if (i40e_is_vsi_uplink_mode_veb(vsi)) {
9957 ctxt.info.valid_sections |=
9958 cpu_to_le16(I40E_AQ_VSI_PROP_SWITCH_VALID);
9959 ctxt.info.switch_id =
9960 cpu_to_le16(I40E_AQ_VSI_SW_ID_FLAG_ALLOW_LB);
9961 }
9962
9963 /* Setup the VSI tx/rx queue map for TC0 only for now */
9964 i40e_vsi_setup_queue_map(vsi, &ctxt, enabled_tc, true);
9965 break;
9966
9967 case I40E_VSI_SRIOV:
9968 ctxt.pf_num = hw->pf_id;
9969 ctxt.vf_num = vsi->vf_id + hw->func_caps.vf_base_id;
9970 ctxt.uplink_seid = vsi->uplink_seid;
9971 ctxt.connection_type = I40E_AQ_VSI_CONN_TYPE_NORMAL;
9972 ctxt.flags = I40E_AQ_VSI_TYPE_VF;
9973
9974 /* This VSI is connected to VEB so the switch_id
9975 * should be set to zero by default.
9976 */
9977 if (i40e_is_vsi_uplink_mode_veb(vsi)) {
9978 ctxt.info.valid_sections |=
9979 cpu_to_le16(I40E_AQ_VSI_PROP_SWITCH_VALID);
9980 ctxt.info.switch_id =
9981 cpu_to_le16(I40E_AQ_VSI_SW_ID_FLAG_ALLOW_LB);
9982 }
9983
9984 if (vsi->back->flags & I40E_FLAG_IWARP_ENABLED) {
9985 ctxt.info.valid_sections |=
9986 cpu_to_le16(I40E_AQ_VSI_PROP_QUEUE_OPT_VALID);
9987 ctxt.info.queueing_opt_flags |=
9988 (I40E_AQ_VSI_QUE_OPT_TCP_ENA |
9989 I40E_AQ_VSI_QUE_OPT_RSS_LUT_VSI);
9990 }
9991
9992 ctxt.info.valid_sections |= cpu_to_le16(I40E_AQ_VSI_PROP_VLAN_VALID);
9993 ctxt.info.port_vlan_flags |= I40E_AQ_VSI_PVLAN_MODE_ALL;
9994 if (pf->vf[vsi->vf_id].spoofchk) {
9995 ctxt.info.valid_sections |=
9996 cpu_to_le16(I40E_AQ_VSI_PROP_SECURITY_VALID);
9997 ctxt.info.sec_flags |=
9998 (I40E_AQ_VSI_SEC_FLAG_ENABLE_VLAN_CHK |
9999 I40E_AQ_VSI_SEC_FLAG_ENABLE_MAC_CHK);
10000 }
10001 /* Setup the VSI tx/rx queue map for TC0 only for now */
10002 i40e_vsi_setup_queue_map(vsi, &ctxt, enabled_tc, true);
10003 break;
10004
10005 case I40E_VSI_IWARP:
10006 /* send down message to iWARP */
10007 break;
10008
10009 default:
10010 return -ENODEV;
10011 }
10012
10013 if (vsi->type != I40E_VSI_MAIN) {
10014 ret = i40e_aq_add_vsi(hw, &ctxt, NULL);
10015 if (ret) {
10016 dev_info(&vsi->back->pdev->dev,
10017 "add vsi failed, err %s aq_err %s\n",
10018 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
10019 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw,
10020 pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
10021 ret = -ENOENT;
10022 goto err;
10023 }
10024 vsi->info = ctxt.info;
10025 vsi->info.valid_sections = 0;
10026 vsi->seid = ctxt.seid;
10027 vsi->id = ctxt.vsi_number;
10028 }
10029
10030 vsi->active_filters = 0;
10031 clear_bit(__I40E_VSI_OVERFLOW_PROMISC, vsi->state);
10032 spin_lock_bh(&vsi->mac_filter_hash_lock);
10033 /* If macvlan filters already exist, force them to get loaded */
10034 hash_for_each_safe(vsi->mac_filter_hash, bkt, h, f, hlist) {
10035 f->state = I40E_FILTER_NEW;
10036 f_count++;
10037 }
10038 spin_unlock_bh(&vsi->mac_filter_hash_lock);
10039
10040 if (f_count) {
10041 vsi->flags |= I40E_VSI_FLAG_FILTER_CHANGED;
10042 pf->flags |= I40E_FLAG_FILTER_SYNC;
10043 }
10044
10045 /* Update VSI BW information */
10046 ret = i40e_vsi_get_bw_info(vsi);
10047 if (ret) {
10048 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
10049 "couldn't get vsi bw info, err %s aq_err %s\n",
10050 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
10051 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw, pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
10052 /* VSI is already added so not tearing that up */
10053 ret = 0;
10054 }
10055
10056err:
10057 return ret;
10058}
10059
10060/**
10061 * i40e_vsi_release - Delete a VSI and free its resources
10062 * @vsi: the VSI being removed
10063 *
10064 * Returns 0 on success or < 0 on error
10065 **/
10066int i40e_vsi_release(struct i40e_vsi *vsi)
10067{
10068 struct i40e_mac_filter *f;
10069 struct hlist_node *h;
10070 struct i40e_veb *veb = NULL;
10071 struct i40e_pf *pf;
10072 u16 uplink_seid;
10073 int i, n, bkt;
10074
10075 pf = vsi->back;
10076
10077 /* release of a VEB-owner or last VSI is not allowed */
10078 if (vsi->flags & I40E_VSI_FLAG_VEB_OWNER) {
10079 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "VSI %d has existing VEB %d\n",
10080 vsi->seid, vsi->uplink_seid);
10081 return -ENODEV;
10082 }
10083 if (vsi == pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi] &&
10084 !test_bit(__I40E_DOWN, pf->state)) {
10085 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "Can't remove PF VSI\n");
10086 return -ENODEV;
10087 }
10088
10089 uplink_seid = vsi->uplink_seid;
10090 if (vsi->type != I40E_VSI_SRIOV) {
10091 if (vsi->netdev_registered) {
10092 vsi->netdev_registered = false;
10093 if (vsi->netdev) {
10094 /* results in a call to i40e_close() */
10095 unregister_netdev(vsi->netdev);
10096 }
10097 } else {
10098 i40e_vsi_close(vsi);
10099 }
10100 i40e_vsi_disable_irq(vsi);
10101 }
10102
10103 spin_lock_bh(&vsi->mac_filter_hash_lock);
10104
10105 /* clear the sync flag on all filters */
10106 if (vsi->netdev) {
10107 __dev_uc_unsync(vsi->netdev, NULL);
10108 __dev_mc_unsync(vsi->netdev, NULL);
10109 }
10110
10111 /* make sure any remaining filters are marked for deletion */
10112 hash_for_each_safe(vsi->mac_filter_hash, bkt, h, f, hlist)
10113 __i40e_del_filter(vsi, f);
10114
10115 spin_unlock_bh(&vsi->mac_filter_hash_lock);
10116
10117 i40e_sync_vsi_filters(vsi);
10118
10119 i40e_vsi_delete(vsi);
10120 i40e_vsi_free_q_vectors(vsi);
10121 if (vsi->netdev) {
10122 free_netdev(vsi->netdev);
10123 vsi->netdev = NULL;
10124 }
10125 i40e_vsi_clear_rings(vsi);
10126 i40e_vsi_clear(vsi);
10127
10128 /* If this was the last thing on the VEB, except for the
10129 * controlling VSI, remove the VEB, which puts the controlling
10130 * VSI onto the next level down in the switch.
10131 *
10132 * Well, okay, there's one more exception here: don't remove
10133 * the orphan VEBs yet. We'll wait for an explicit remove request
10134 * from up the network stack.
10135 */
10136 for (n = 0, i = 0; i < pf->num_alloc_vsi; i++) {
10137 if (pf->vsi[i] &&
10138 pf->vsi[i]->uplink_seid == uplink_seid &&
10139 (pf->vsi[i]->flags & I40E_VSI_FLAG_VEB_OWNER) == 0) {
10140 n++; /* count the VSIs */
10141 }
10142 }
10143 for (i = 0; i < I40E_MAX_VEB; i++) {
10144 if (!pf->veb[i])
10145 continue;
10146 if (pf->veb[i]->uplink_seid == uplink_seid)
10147 n++; /* count the VEBs */
10148 if (pf->veb[i]->seid == uplink_seid)
10149 veb = pf->veb[i];
10150 }
10151 if (n == 0 && veb && veb->uplink_seid != 0)
10152 i40e_veb_release(veb);
10153
10154 return 0;
10155}
10156
10157/**
10158 * i40e_vsi_setup_vectors - Set up the q_vectors for the given VSI
10159 * @vsi: ptr to the VSI
10160 *
10161 * This should only be called after i40e_vsi_mem_alloc() which allocates the
10162 * corresponding SW VSI structure and initializes num_queue_pairs for the
10163 * newly allocated VSI.
10164 *
10165 * Returns 0 on success or negative on failure
10166 **/
10167static int i40e_vsi_setup_vectors(struct i40e_vsi *vsi)
10168{
10169 int ret = -ENOENT;
10170 struct i40e_pf *pf = vsi->back;
10171
10172 if (vsi->q_vectors[0]) {
10173 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "VSI %d has existing q_vectors\n",
10174 vsi->seid);
10175 return -EEXIST;
10176 }
10177
10178 if (vsi->base_vector) {
10179 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "VSI %d has non-zero base vector %d\n",
10180 vsi->seid, vsi->base_vector);
10181 return -EEXIST;
10182 }
10183
10184 ret = i40e_vsi_alloc_q_vectors(vsi);
10185 if (ret) {
10186 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
10187 "failed to allocate %d q_vector for VSI %d, ret=%d\n",
10188 vsi->num_q_vectors, vsi->seid, ret);
10189 vsi->num_q_vectors = 0;
10190 goto vector_setup_out;
10191 }
10192
10193 /* In Legacy mode, we do not have to get any other vector since we
10194 * piggyback on the misc/ICR0 for queue interrupts.
10195 */
10196 if (!(pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_MSIX_ENABLED))
10197 return ret;
10198 if (vsi->num_q_vectors)
10199 vsi->base_vector = i40e_get_lump(pf, pf->irq_pile,
10200 vsi->num_q_vectors, vsi->idx);
10201 if (vsi->base_vector < 0) {
10202 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
10203 "failed to get tracking for %d vectors for VSI %d, err=%d\n",
10204 vsi->num_q_vectors, vsi->seid, vsi->base_vector);
10205 i40e_vsi_free_q_vectors(vsi);
10206 ret = -ENOENT;
10207 goto vector_setup_out;
10208 }
10209
10210vector_setup_out:
10211 return ret;
10212}
10213
10214/**
10215 * i40e_vsi_reinit_setup - return and reallocate resources for a VSI
10216 * @vsi: pointer to the vsi.
10217 *
10218 * This re-allocates a vsi's queue resources.
10219 *
10220 * Returns pointer to the successfully allocated and configured VSI sw struct
10221 * on success, otherwise returns NULL on failure.
10222 **/
10223static struct i40e_vsi *i40e_vsi_reinit_setup(struct i40e_vsi *vsi)
10224{
10225 u16 alloc_queue_pairs;
10226 struct i40e_pf *pf;
10227 u8 enabled_tc;
10228 int ret;
10229
10230 if (!vsi)
10231 return NULL;
10232
10233 pf = vsi->back;
10234
10235 i40e_put_lump(pf->qp_pile, vsi->base_queue, vsi->idx);
10236 i40e_vsi_clear_rings(vsi);
10237
10238 i40e_vsi_free_arrays(vsi, false);
10239 i40e_set_num_rings_in_vsi(vsi);
10240 ret = i40e_vsi_alloc_arrays(vsi, false);
10241 if (ret)
10242 goto err_vsi;
10243
10244 alloc_queue_pairs = vsi->alloc_queue_pairs *
10245 (i40e_enabled_xdp_vsi(vsi) ? 2 : 1);
10246
10247 ret = i40e_get_lump(pf, pf->qp_pile, alloc_queue_pairs, vsi->idx);
10248 if (ret < 0) {
10249 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
10250 "failed to get tracking for %d queues for VSI %d err %d\n",
10251 alloc_queue_pairs, vsi->seid, ret);
10252 goto err_vsi;
10253 }
10254 vsi->base_queue = ret;
10255
10256 /* Update the FW view of the VSI. Force a reset of TC and queue
10257 * layout configurations.
10258 */
10259 enabled_tc = pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi]->tc_config.enabled_tc;
10260 pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi]->tc_config.enabled_tc = 0;
10261 pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi]->seid = pf->main_vsi_seid;
10262 i40e_vsi_config_tc(pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi], enabled_tc);
10263 if (vsi->type == I40E_VSI_MAIN)
10264 i40e_rm_default_mac_filter(vsi, pf->hw.mac.perm_addr);
10265
10266 /* assign it some queues */
10267 ret = i40e_alloc_rings(vsi);
10268 if (ret)
10269 goto err_rings;
10270
10271 /* map all of the rings to the q_vectors */
10272 i40e_vsi_map_rings_to_vectors(vsi);
10273 return vsi;
10274
10275err_rings:
10276 i40e_vsi_free_q_vectors(vsi);
10277 if (vsi->netdev_registered) {
10278 vsi->netdev_registered = false;
10279 unregister_netdev(vsi->netdev);
10280 free_netdev(vsi->netdev);
10281 vsi->netdev = NULL;
10282 }
10283 i40e_aq_delete_element(&pf->hw, vsi->seid, NULL);
10284err_vsi:
10285 i40e_vsi_clear(vsi);
10286 return NULL;
10287}
10288
10289/**
10290 * i40e_vsi_setup - Set up a VSI by a given type
10291 * @pf: board private structure
10292 * @type: VSI type
10293 * @uplink_seid: the switch element to link to
10294 * @param1: usage depends upon VSI type. For VF types, indicates VF id
10295 *
10296 * This allocates the sw VSI structure and its queue resources, then add a VSI
10297 * to the identified VEB.
10298 *
10299 * Returns pointer to the successfully allocated and configure VSI sw struct on
10300 * success, otherwise returns NULL on failure.
10301 **/
10302struct i40e_vsi *i40e_vsi_setup(struct i40e_pf *pf, u8 type,
10303 u16 uplink_seid, u32 param1)
10304{
10305 struct i40e_vsi *vsi = NULL;
10306 struct i40e_veb *veb = NULL;
10307 u16 alloc_queue_pairs;
10308 int ret, i;
10309 int v_idx;
10310
10311 /* The requested uplink_seid must be either
10312 * - the PF's port seid
10313 * no VEB is needed because this is the PF
10314 * or this is a Flow Director special case VSI
10315 * - seid of an existing VEB
10316 * - seid of a VSI that owns an existing VEB
10317 * - seid of a VSI that doesn't own a VEB
10318 * a new VEB is created and the VSI becomes the owner
10319 * - seid of the PF VSI, which is what creates the first VEB
10320 * this is a special case of the previous
10321 *
10322 * Find which uplink_seid we were given and create a new VEB if needed
10323 */
10324 for (i = 0; i < I40E_MAX_VEB; i++) {
10325 if (pf->veb[i] && pf->veb[i]->seid == uplink_seid) {
10326 veb = pf->veb[i];
10327 break;
10328 }
10329 }
10330
10331 if (!veb && uplink_seid != pf->mac_seid) {
10332
10333 for (i = 0; i < pf->num_alloc_vsi; i++) {
10334 if (pf->vsi[i] && pf->vsi[i]->seid == uplink_seid) {
10335 vsi = pf->vsi[i];
10336 break;
10337 }
10338 }
10339 if (!vsi) {
10340 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "no such uplink_seid %d\n",
10341 uplink_seid);
10342 return NULL;
10343 }
10344
10345 if (vsi->uplink_seid == pf->mac_seid)
10346 veb = i40e_veb_setup(pf, 0, pf->mac_seid, vsi->seid,
10347 vsi->tc_config.enabled_tc);
10348 else if ((vsi->flags & I40E_VSI_FLAG_VEB_OWNER) == 0)
10349 veb = i40e_veb_setup(pf, 0, vsi->uplink_seid, vsi->seid,
10350 vsi->tc_config.enabled_tc);
10351 if (veb) {
10352 if (vsi->seid != pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi]->seid) {
10353 dev_info(&vsi->back->pdev->dev,
10354 "New VSI creation error, uplink seid of LAN VSI expected.\n");
10355 return NULL;
10356 }
10357 /* We come up by default in VEPA mode if SRIOV is not
10358 * already enabled, in which case we can't force VEPA
10359 * mode.
10360 */
10361 if (!(pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_VEB_MODE_ENABLED)) {
10362 veb->bridge_mode = BRIDGE_MODE_VEPA;
10363 pf->flags &= ~I40E_FLAG_VEB_MODE_ENABLED;
10364 }
10365 i40e_config_bridge_mode(veb);
10366 }
10367 for (i = 0; i < I40E_MAX_VEB && !veb; i++) {
10368 if (pf->veb[i] && pf->veb[i]->seid == vsi->uplink_seid)
10369 veb = pf->veb[i];
10370 }
10371 if (!veb) {
10372 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "couldn't add VEB\n");
10373 return NULL;
10374 }
10375
10376 vsi->flags |= I40E_VSI_FLAG_VEB_OWNER;
