10377 uplink_seid = veb->seid;
10378 }
10379
10380 /* get vsi sw struct */
10381 v_idx = i40e_vsi_mem_alloc(pf, type);
10382 if (v_idx < 0)
10383 goto err_alloc;
10384 vsi = pf->vsi[v_idx];
10385 if (!vsi)
10386 goto err_alloc;
10387 vsi->type = type;
10388 vsi->veb_idx = (veb ? veb->idx : I40E_NO_VEB);
10389
10390 if (type == I40E_VSI_MAIN)
10391 pf->lan_vsi = v_idx;
10392 else if (type == I40E_VSI_SRIOV)
10393 vsi->vf_id = param1;
10394 /* assign it some queues */
10395 alloc_queue_pairs = vsi->alloc_queue_pairs *
10396 (i40e_enabled_xdp_vsi(vsi) ? 2 : 1);
10397
10398 ret = i40e_get_lump(pf, pf->qp_pile, alloc_queue_pairs, vsi->idx);
10399 if (ret < 0) {
10400 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
10401 "failed to get tracking for %d queues for VSI %d err=%d\n",
10402 alloc_queue_pairs, vsi->seid, ret);
10403 goto err_vsi;
10404 }
10405 vsi->base_queue = ret;
10406
10407 /* get a VSI from the hardware */
10408 vsi->uplink_seid = uplink_seid;
10409 ret = i40e_add_vsi(vsi);
10410 if (ret)
10411 goto err_vsi;
10412
10413 switch (vsi->type) {
10414 /* setup the netdev if needed */
10415 case I40E_VSI_MAIN:
10416 case I40E_VSI_VMDQ2:
10417 ret = i40e_config_netdev(vsi);
10418 if (ret)
10419 goto err_netdev;
10420 ret = register_netdev(vsi->netdev);
10421 if (ret)
10422 goto err_netdev;
10423 vsi->netdev_registered = true;
10424 netif_carrier_off(vsi->netdev);
10425#ifdef CONFIG_I40E_DCB
10426 /* Setup DCB netlink interface */
10427 i40e_dcbnl_setup(vsi);
10428#endif /* CONFIG_I40E_DCB */
10429 /* fall through */
10430
10431 case I40E_VSI_FDIR:
10432 /* set up vectors and rings if needed */
10433 ret = i40e_vsi_setup_vectors(vsi);
10434 if (ret)
10435 goto err_msix;
10436
10437 ret = i40e_alloc_rings(vsi);
10438 if (ret)
10439 goto err_rings;
10440
10441 /* map all of the rings to the q_vectors */
10442 i40e_vsi_map_rings_to_vectors(vsi);
10443
10444 i40e_vsi_reset_stats(vsi);
10445 break;
10446
10447 default:
10448 /* no netdev or rings for the other VSI types */
10449 break;
10450 }
10451
10452 if ((pf->hw_features & I40E_HW_RSS_AQ_CAPABLE) &&
10453 (vsi->type == I40E_VSI_VMDQ2)) {
10454 ret = i40e_vsi_config_rss(vsi);
10455 }
10456 return vsi;
10457
10458err_rings:
10459 i40e_vsi_free_q_vectors(vsi);
10460err_msix:
10461 if (vsi->netdev_registered) {
10462 vsi->netdev_registered = false;
10463 unregister_netdev(vsi->netdev);
10464 free_netdev(vsi->netdev);
10465 vsi->netdev = NULL;
10466 }
10467err_netdev:
10468 i40e_aq_delete_element(&pf->hw, vsi->seid, NULL);
10469err_vsi:
10470 i40e_vsi_clear(vsi);
10471err_alloc:
10472 return NULL;
10473}
10474
10475/**
10476 * i40e_veb_get_bw_info - Query VEB BW information
10477 * @veb: the veb to query
10478 *
10479 * Query the Tx scheduler BW configuration data for given VEB
10480 **/
10481static int i40e_veb_get_bw_info(struct i40e_veb *veb)
10482{
10483 struct i40e_aqc_query_switching_comp_ets_config_resp ets_data;
10484 struct i40e_aqc_query_switching_comp_bw_config_resp bw_data;
10485 struct i40e_pf *pf = veb->pf;
10486 struct i40e_hw *hw = &pf->hw;
10487 u32 tc_bw_max;
10488 int ret = 0;
10489 int i;
10490
10491 ret = i40e_aq_query_switch_comp_bw_config(hw, veb->seid,
10492 &bw_data, NULL);
10493 if (ret) {
10494 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
10495 "query veb bw config failed, err %s aq_err %s\n",
10496 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
10497 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw, hw->aq.asq_last_status));
10498 goto out;
10499 }
10500
10501 ret = i40e_aq_query_switch_comp_ets_config(hw, veb->seid,
10502 &ets_data, NULL);
10503 if (ret) {
10504 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
10505 "query veb bw ets config failed, err %s aq_err %s\n",
10506 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
10507 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw, hw->aq.asq_last_status));
10508 goto out;
10509 }
10510
10511 veb->bw_limit = le16_to_cpu(ets_data.port_bw_limit);
10512 veb->bw_max_quanta = ets_data.tc_bw_max;
10513 veb->is_abs_credits = bw_data.absolute_credits_enable;
10514 veb->enabled_tc = ets_data.tc_valid_bits;
10515 tc_bw_max = le16_to_cpu(bw_data.tc_bw_max[0]) |
10516 (le16_to_cpu(bw_data.tc_bw_max[1]) << 16);
10517 for (i = 0; i < I40E_MAX_TRAFFIC_CLASS; i++) {
10518 veb->bw_tc_share_credits[i] = bw_data.tc_bw_share_credits[i];
10519 veb->bw_tc_limit_credits[i] =
10520 le16_to_cpu(bw_data.tc_bw_limits[i]);
10521 veb->bw_tc_max_quanta[i] = ((tc_bw_max >> (i*4)) & 0x7);
10522 }
10523
10524out:
10525 return ret;
10526}
10527
10528/**
10529 * i40e_veb_mem_alloc - Allocates the next available struct veb in the PF
10530 * @pf: board private structure
10531 *
10532 * On error: returns error code (negative)
10533 * On success: returns vsi index in PF (positive)
10534 **/
10535static int i40e_veb_mem_alloc(struct i40e_pf *pf)
10536{
10537 int ret = -ENOENT;
10538 struct i40e_veb *veb;
10539 int i;
10540
10541 /* Need to protect the allocation of switch elements at the PF level */
10542 mutex_lock(&pf->switch_mutex);
10543
10544 /* VEB list may be fragmented if VEB creation/destruction has
10545 * been happening. We can afford to do a quick scan to look
10546 * for any free slots in the list.
10547 *
10548 * find next empty veb slot, looping back around if necessary
10549 */
10550 i = 0;
10551 while ((i < I40E_MAX_VEB) && (pf->veb[i] != NULL))
10552 i++;
10553 if (i >= I40E_MAX_VEB) {
10554 ret = -ENOMEM;
10555 goto err_alloc_veb; /* out of VEB slots! */
10556 }
10557
10558 veb = kzalloc(sizeof(*veb), GFP_KERNEL);
10559 if (!veb) {
10560 ret = -ENOMEM;
10561 goto err_alloc_veb;
10562 }
10563 veb->pf = pf;
10564 veb->idx = i;
10565 veb->enabled_tc = 1;
10566
10567 pf->veb[i] = veb;
10568 ret = i;
10569err_alloc_veb:
10570 mutex_unlock(&pf->switch_mutex);
10571 return ret;
10572}
10573
10574/**
10575 * i40e_switch_branch_release - Delete a branch of the switch tree
10576 * @branch: where to start deleting
10577 *
10578 * This uses recursion to find the tips of the branch to be
10579 * removed, deleting until we get back to and can delete this VEB.
10580 **/
10581static void i40e_switch_branch_release(struct i40e_veb *branch)
10582{
10583 struct i40e_pf *pf = branch->pf;
10584 u16 branch_seid = branch->seid;
10585 u16 veb_idx = branch->idx;
10586 int i;
10587
10588 /* release any VEBs on this VEB - RECURSION */
10589 for (i = 0; i < I40E_MAX_VEB; i++) {
10590 if (!pf->veb[i])
10591 continue;
10592 if (pf->veb[i]->uplink_seid == branch->seid)
10593 i40e_switch_branch_release(pf->veb[i]);
10594 }
10595
10596 /* Release the VSIs on this VEB, but not the owner VSI.
10597 *
10598 * NOTE: Removing the last VSI on a VEB has the SIDE EFFECT of removing
10599 * the VEB itself, so don't use (*branch) after this loop.
10600 */
10601 for (i = 0; i < pf->num_alloc_vsi; i++) {
10602 if (!pf->vsi[i])
10603 continue;
10604 if (pf->vsi[i]->uplink_seid == branch_seid &&
10605 (pf->vsi[i]->flags & I40E_VSI_FLAG_VEB_OWNER) == 0) {
10606 i40e_vsi_release(pf->vsi[i]);
10607 }
10608 }
10609
10610 /* There's one corner case where the VEB might not have been
10611 * removed, so double check it here and remove it if needed.
10612 * This case happens if the veb was created from the debugfs
10613 * commands and no VSIs were added to it.
10614 */
10615 if (pf->veb[veb_idx])
10616 i40e_veb_release(pf->veb[veb_idx]);
10617}
10618
10619/**
10620 * i40e_veb_clear - remove veb struct
10621 * @veb: the veb to remove
10622 **/
10623static void i40e_veb_clear(struct i40e_veb *veb)
10624{
10625 if (!veb)
10626 return;
10627
10628 if (veb->pf) {
10629 struct i40e_pf *pf = veb->pf;
10630
10631 mutex_lock(&pf->switch_mutex);
10632 if (pf->veb[veb->idx] == veb)
10633 pf->veb[veb->idx] = NULL;
10634 mutex_unlock(&pf->switch_mutex);
10635 }
10636
10637 kfree(veb);
10638}
10639
10640/**
10641 * i40e_veb_release - Delete a VEB and free its resources
10642 * @veb: the VEB being removed
10643 **/
10644void i40e_veb_release(struct i40e_veb *veb)
10645{
10646 struct i40e_vsi *vsi = NULL;
10647 struct i40e_pf *pf;
10648 int i, n = 0;
10649
10650 pf = veb->pf;
10651
10652 /* find the remaining VSI and check for extras */
10653 for (i = 0; i < pf->num_alloc_vsi; i++) {
10654 if (pf->vsi[i] && pf->vsi[i]->uplink_seid == veb->seid) {
10655 n++;
10656 vsi = pf->vsi[i];
10657 }
10658 }
10659 if (n != 1) {
10660 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
10661 "can't remove VEB %d with %d VSIs left\n",
10662 veb->seid, n);
10663 return;
10664 }
10665
10666 /* move the remaining VSI to uplink veb */
10667 vsi->flags &= ~I40E_VSI_FLAG_VEB_OWNER;
10668 if (veb->uplink_seid) {
10669 vsi->uplink_seid = veb->uplink_seid;
10670 if (veb->uplink_seid == pf->mac_seid)
10671 vsi->veb_idx = I40E_NO_VEB;
10672 else
10673 vsi->veb_idx = veb->veb_idx;
10674 } else {
10675 /* floating VEB */
10676 vsi->uplink_seid = pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi]->uplink_seid;
10677 vsi->veb_idx = pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi]->veb_idx;
10678 }
10679
10680 i40e_aq_delete_element(&pf->hw, veb->seid, NULL);
10681 i40e_veb_clear(veb);
10682}
10683
10684/**
10685 * i40e_add_veb - create the VEB in the switch
10686 * @veb: the VEB to be instantiated
10687 * @vsi: the controlling VSI
10688 **/
10689static int i40e_add_veb(struct i40e_veb *veb, struct i40e_vsi *vsi)
10690{
10691 struct i40e_pf *pf = veb->pf;
10692 bool enable_stats = !!(pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_VEB_STATS_ENABLED);
10693 int ret;
10694
10695 ret = i40e_aq_add_veb(&pf->hw, veb->uplink_seid, vsi->seid,
10696 veb->enabled_tc, false,
10697 &veb->seid, enable_stats, NULL);
10698
10699 /* get a VEB from the hardware */
10700 if (ret) {
10701 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
10702 "couldn't add VEB, err %s aq_err %s\n",
10703 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
10704 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw, pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
10705 return -EPERM;
10706 }
10707
10708 /* get statistics counter */
10709 ret = i40e_aq_get_veb_parameters(&pf->hw, veb->seid, NULL, NULL,
10710 &veb->stats_idx, NULL, NULL, NULL);
10711 if (ret) {
10712 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
10713 "couldn't get VEB statistics idx, err %s aq_err %s\n",
10714 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
10715 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw, pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
10716 return -EPERM;
10717 }
10718 ret = i40e_veb_get_bw_info(veb);
10719 if (ret) {
10720 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
10721 "couldn't get VEB bw info, err %s aq_err %s\n",
10722 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
10723 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw, pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
10724 i40e_aq_delete_element(&pf->hw, veb->seid, NULL);
10725 return -ENOENT;
10726 }
10727
10728 vsi->uplink_seid = veb->seid;
10729 vsi->veb_idx = veb->idx;
10730 vsi->flags |= I40E_VSI_FLAG_VEB_OWNER;
10731
10732 return 0;
10733}
10734
10735/**
10736 * i40e_veb_setup - Set up a VEB
10737 * @pf: board private structure
10738 * @flags: VEB setup flags
10739 * @uplink_seid: the switch element to link to
10740 * @vsi_seid: the initial VSI seid
10741 * @enabled_tc: Enabled TC bit-map
10742 *
10743 * This allocates the sw VEB structure and links it into the switch
10744 * It is possible and legal for this to be a duplicate of an already
10745 * existing VEB. It is also possible for both uplink and vsi seids
10746 * to be zero, in order to create a floating VEB.
10747 *
10748 * Returns pointer to the successfully allocated VEB sw struct on
10749 * success, otherwise returns NULL on failure.
10750 **/
10751struct i40e_veb *i40e_veb_setup(struct i40e_pf *pf, u16 flags,
10752 u16 uplink_seid, u16 vsi_seid,
10753 u8 enabled_tc)
10754{
10755 struct i40e_veb *veb, *uplink_veb = NULL;
10756 int vsi_idx, veb_idx;
10757 int ret;
10758
10759 /* if one seid is 0, the other must be 0 to create a floating relay */
10760 if ((uplink_seid == 0 || vsi_seid == 0) &&
10761 (uplink_seid + vsi_seid != 0)) {
10762 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
10763 "one, not both seid's are 0: uplink=%d vsi=%d\n",
10764 uplink_seid, vsi_seid);
10765 return NULL;
10766 }
10767
10768 /* make sure there is such a vsi and uplink */
10769 for (vsi_idx = 0; vsi_idx < pf->num_alloc_vsi; vsi_idx++)
10770 if (pf->vsi[vsi_idx] && pf->vsi[vsi_idx]->seid == vsi_seid)
10771 break;
10772 if (vsi_idx >= pf->num_alloc_vsi && vsi_seid != 0) {
10773 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "vsi seid %d not found\n",
10774 vsi_seid);
10775 return NULL;
10776 }
10777
10778 if (uplink_seid && uplink_seid != pf->mac_seid) {
10779 for (veb_idx = 0; veb_idx < I40E_MAX_VEB; veb_idx++) {
10780 if (pf->veb[veb_idx] &&
10781 pf->veb[veb_idx]->seid == uplink_seid) {
10782 uplink_veb = pf->veb[veb_idx];
10783 break;
10784 }
10785 }
10786 if (!uplink_veb) {
10787 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
10788 "uplink seid %d not found\n", uplink_seid);
10789 return NULL;
10790 }
10791 }
10792
10793 /* get veb sw struct */
10794 veb_idx = i40e_veb_mem_alloc(pf);
10795 if (veb_idx < 0)
10796 goto err_alloc;
10797 veb = pf->veb[veb_idx];
10798 veb->flags = flags;
10799 veb->uplink_seid = uplink_seid;
10800 veb->veb_idx = (uplink_veb ? uplink_veb->idx : I40E_NO_VEB);
10801 veb->enabled_tc = (enabled_tc ? enabled_tc : 0x1);
10802
10803 /* create the VEB in the switch */
10804 ret = i40e_add_veb(veb, pf->vsi[vsi_idx]);
10805 if (ret)
10806 goto err_veb;
10807 if (vsi_idx == pf->lan_vsi)
10808 pf->lan_veb = veb->idx;
10809
10810 return veb;
10811
10812err_veb:
10813 i40e_veb_clear(veb);
10814err_alloc:
10815 return NULL;
10816}
10817
10818/**
10819 * i40e_setup_pf_switch_element - set PF vars based on switch type
10820 * @pf: board private structure
10821 * @ele: element we are building info from
10822 * @num_reported: total number of elements
10823 * @printconfig: should we print the contents
10824 *
10825 * helper function to assist in extracting a few useful SEID values.
10826 **/
10827static void i40e_setup_pf_switch_element(struct i40e_pf *pf,
10828 struct i40e_aqc_switch_config_element_resp *ele,
10829 u16 num_reported, bool printconfig)
10830{
10831 u16 downlink_seid = le16_to_cpu(ele->downlink_seid);
10832 u16 uplink_seid = le16_to_cpu(ele->uplink_seid);
10833 u8 element_type = ele->element_type;
10834 u16 seid = le16_to_cpu(ele->seid);
10835
10836 if (printconfig)
10837 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
10838 "type=%d seid=%d uplink=%d downlink=%d\n",
10839 element_type, seid, uplink_seid, downlink_seid);
10840
10841 switch (element_type) {
10842 case I40E_SWITCH_ELEMENT_TYPE_MAC:
10843 pf->mac_seid = seid;
10844 break;
10845 case I40E_SWITCH_ELEMENT_TYPE_VEB:
10846 /* Main VEB? */
10847 if (uplink_seid != pf->mac_seid)
10848 break;
10849 if (pf->lan_veb == I40E_NO_VEB) {
10850 int v;
10851
10852 /* find existing or else empty VEB */
10853 for (v = 0; v < I40E_MAX_VEB; v++) {
10854 if (pf->veb[v] && (pf->veb[v]->seid == seid)) {
10855 pf->lan_veb = v;
10856 break;
10857 }
10858 }
10859 if (pf->lan_veb == I40E_NO_VEB) {
10860 v = i40e_veb_mem_alloc(pf);
10861 if (v < 0)
10862 break;
10863 pf->lan_veb = v;
10864 }
10865 }
10866
10867 pf->veb[pf->lan_veb]->seid = seid;
10868 pf->veb[pf->lan_veb]->uplink_seid = pf->mac_seid;
10869 pf->veb[pf->lan_veb]->pf = pf;
10870 pf->veb[pf->lan_veb]->veb_idx = I40E_NO_VEB;
10871 break;
10872 case I40E_SWITCH_ELEMENT_TYPE_VSI:
10873 if (num_reported != 1)
10874 break;
10875 /* This is immediately after a reset so we can assume this is
10876 * the PF's VSI
10877 */
10878 pf->mac_seid = uplink_seid;
10879 pf->pf_seid = downlink_seid;
10880 pf->main_vsi_seid = seid;
10881 if (printconfig)
10882 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
10883 "pf_seid=%d main_vsi_seid=%d\n",
10884 pf->pf_seid, pf->main_vsi_seid);
10885 break;
10886 case I40E_SWITCH_ELEMENT_TYPE_PF:
10887 case I40E_SWITCH_ELEMENT_TYPE_VF:
10888 case I40E_SWITCH_ELEMENT_TYPE_EMP:
10889 case I40E_SWITCH_ELEMENT_TYPE_BMC:
10890 case I40E_SWITCH_ELEMENT_TYPE_PE:
10891 case I40E_SWITCH_ELEMENT_TYPE_PA:
10892 /* ignore these for now */
10893 break;
10894 default:
10895 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "unknown element type=%d seid=%d\n",
10896 element_type, seid);
10897 break;
10898 }
10899}
10900
10901/**
10902 * i40e_fetch_switch_configuration - Get switch config from firmware
10903 * @pf: board private structure
10904 * @printconfig: should we print the contents
10905 *
10906 * Get the current switch configuration from the device and
10907 * extract a few useful SEID values.
10908 **/
10909int i40e_fetch_switch_configuration(struct i40e_pf *pf, bool printconfig)
10910{
10911 struct i40e_aqc_get_switch_config_resp *sw_config;
10912 u16 next_seid = 0;
10913 int ret = 0;
10914 u8 *aq_buf;
10915 int i;
10916
10917 aq_buf = kzalloc(I40E_AQ_LARGE_BUF, GFP_KERNEL);
10918 if (!aq_buf)
10919 return -ENOMEM;
10920
10921 sw_config = (struct i40e_aqc_get_switch_config_resp *)aq_buf;
10922 do {
10923 u16 num_reported, num_total;
10924
10925 ret = i40e_aq_get_switch_config(&pf->hw, sw_config,
10926 I40E_AQ_LARGE_BUF,
10927 &next_seid, NULL);
10928 if (ret) {
10929 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
10930 "get switch config failed err %s aq_err %s\n",
10931 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
10932 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw,
10933 pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
10934 kfree(aq_buf);
10935 return -ENOENT;
10936 }
10937
10938 num_reported = le16_to_cpu(sw_config->header.num_reported);
10939 num_total = le16_to_cpu(sw_config->header.num_total);
10940
10941 if (printconfig)
10942 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
10943 "header: %d reported %d total\n",
10944 num_reported, num_total);
10945
10946 for (i = 0; i < num_reported; i++) {
10947 struct i40e_aqc_switch_config_element_resp *ele =
10948 &sw_config->element[i];
10949
10950 i40e_setup_pf_switch_element(pf, ele, num_reported,
10951 printconfig);
10952 }
10953 } while (next_seid != 0);
10954
10955 kfree(aq_buf);
10956 return ret;
10957}
10958
10959/**
10960 * i40e_setup_pf_switch - Setup the HW switch on startup or after reset
10961 * @pf: board private structure
10962 * @reinit: if the Main VSI needs to re-initialized.
10963 *
10964 * Returns 0 on success, negative value on failure
10965 **/
10966static int i40e_setup_pf_switch(struct i40e_pf *pf, bool reinit)
10967{
10968 u16 flags = 0;
10969 int ret;
10970
10971 /* find out what's out there already */
10972 ret = i40e_fetch_switch_configuration(pf, false);
10973 if (ret) {
10974 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
10975 "couldn't fetch switch config, err %s aq_err %s\n",
10976 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
10977 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw, pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
10978 return ret;
10979 }
10980 i40e_pf_reset_stats(pf);
10981
10982 /* set the switch config bit for the whole device to
10983 * support limited promisc or true promisc
10984 * when user requests promisc. The default is limited
10985 * promisc.
10986 */
10987
10988 if ((pf->hw.pf_id == 0) &&
10989 !(pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_TRUE_PROMISC_SUPPORT))
10990 flags = I40E_AQ_SET_SWITCH_CFG_PROMISC;
10991
10992 if (pf->hw.pf_id == 0) {
10993 u16 valid_flags;
10994
10995 valid_flags = I40E_AQ_SET_SWITCH_CFG_PROMISC;
10996 ret = i40e_aq_set_switch_config(&pf->hw, flags, valid_flags,
10997 NULL);
10998 if (ret && pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status != I40E_AQ_RC_ESRCH) {
10999 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev,
11000 "couldn't set switch config bits, err %s aq_err %s\n",
11001 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, ret),
11002 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw,
11003 pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
11004 /* not a fatal problem, just keep going */
11005 }
11006 }
11007
11008 /* first time setup */
11009 if (pf->lan_vsi == I40E_NO_VSI || reinit) {
11010 struct i40e_vsi *vsi = NULL;
11011 u16 uplink_seid;
11012
11013 /* Set up the PF VSI associated with the PF's main VSI
11014 * that is already in the HW switch
11015 */
11016 if (pf->lan_veb != I40E_NO_VEB && pf->veb[pf->lan_veb])
11017 uplink_seid = pf->veb[pf->lan_veb]->seid;
11018 else
11019 uplink_seid = pf->mac_seid;
11020 if (pf->lan_vsi == I40E_NO_VSI)
11021 vsi = i40e_vsi_setup(pf, I40E_VSI_MAIN, uplink_seid, 0);
11022 else if (reinit)
11023 vsi = i40e_vsi_reinit_setup(pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi]);
11024 if (!vsi) {
11025 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "setup of MAIN VSI failed\n");
11026 i40e_fdir_teardown(pf);
11027 return -EAGAIN;
11028 }
11029 } else {
11030 /* force a reset of TC and queue layout configurations */
11031 u8 enabled_tc = pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi]->tc_config.enabled_tc;
11032
11033 pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi]->tc_config.enabled_tc = 0;
11034 pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi]->seid = pf->main_vsi_seid;
11035 i40e_vsi_config_tc(pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi], enabled_tc);
11036 }
11037 i40e_vlan_stripping_disable(pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi]);
11038
11039 i40e_fdir_sb_setup(pf);
11040
11041 /* Setup static PF queue filter control settings */
11042 ret = i40e_setup_pf_filter_control(pf);
11043 if (ret) {
11044 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "setup_pf_filter_control failed: %d\n",
11045 ret);
11046 /* Failure here should not stop continuing other steps */
11047 }
11048
11049 /* enable RSS in the HW, even for only one queue, as the stack can use
11050 * the hash
11051 */
11052 if ((pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_RSS_ENABLED))
11053 i40e_pf_config_rss(pf);
11054
11055 /* fill in link information and enable LSE reporting */
11056 i40e_link_event(pf);
11057
11058 /* Initialize user-specific link properties */
11059 pf->fc_autoneg_status = ((pf->hw.phy.link_info.an_info &
11060 I40E_AQ_AN_COMPLETED) ? true : false);
11061
11062 i40e_ptp_init(pf);
11063
11064 /* repopulate tunnel port filters */
11065 i40e_sync_udp_filters(pf);
11066
11067 return ret;
11068}
11069
11070/**
11071 * i40e_determine_queue_usage - Work out queue distribution
11072 * @pf: board private structure
11073 **/
11074static void i40e_determine_queue_usage(struct i40e_pf *pf)
11075{
11076 int queues_left;
11077
11078 pf->num_lan_qps = 0;
11079
11080 /* Find the max queues to be put into basic use. We'll always be
11081 * using TC0, whether or not DCB is running, and TC0 will get the
11082 * big RSS set.
11083 */
11084 queues_left = pf->hw.func_caps.num_tx_qp;
11085
11086 if ((queues_left == 1) ||
11087 !(pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_MSIX_ENABLED)) {
11088 /* one qp for PF, no queues for anything else */
11089 queues_left = 0;
11090 pf->alloc_rss_size = pf->num_lan_qps = 1;
11091
11092 /* make sure all the fancies are disabled */
11093 pf->flags &= ~(I40E_FLAG_RSS_ENABLED |
11094 I40E_FLAG_IWARP_ENABLED |
11095 I40E_FLAG_FD_SB_ENABLED |
11096 I40E_FLAG_FD_ATR_ENABLED |
11097 I40E_FLAG_DCB_CAPABLE |
11098 I40E_FLAG_DCB_ENABLED |
11099 I40E_FLAG_SRIOV_ENABLED |
11100 I40E_FLAG_VMDQ_ENABLED);
11101 } else if (!(pf->flags & (I40E_FLAG_RSS_ENABLED |
11102 I40E_FLAG_FD_SB_ENABLED |
11103 I40E_FLAG_FD_ATR_ENABLED |
11104 I40E_FLAG_DCB_CAPABLE))) {
11105 /* one qp for PF */
11106 pf->alloc_rss_size = pf->num_lan_qps = 1;
11107 queues_left -= pf->num_lan_qps;
11108
11109 pf->flags &= ~(I40E_FLAG_RSS_ENABLED |
11110 I40E_FLAG_IWARP_ENABLED |
11111 I40E_FLAG_FD_SB_ENABLED |
11112 I40E_FLAG_FD_ATR_ENABLED |
11113 I40E_FLAG_DCB_ENABLED |
11114 I40E_FLAG_VMDQ_ENABLED);
11115 } else {
11116 /* Not enough queues for all TCs */
11117 if ((pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_DCB_CAPABLE) &&
11118 (queues_left < I40E_MAX_TRAFFIC_CLASS)) {
11119 pf->flags &= ~(I40E_FLAG_DCB_CAPABLE |
11120 I40E_FLAG_DCB_ENABLED);
11121 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "not enough queues for DCB. DCB is disabled.\n");
11122 }
11123 pf->num_lan_qps = max_t(int, pf->rss_size_max,
11124 num_online_cpus());
11125 pf->num_lan_qps = min_t(int, pf->num_lan_qps,
11126 pf->hw.func_caps.num_tx_qp);
11127
11128 queues_left -= pf->num_lan_qps;
11129 }
11130
11131 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_FD_SB_ENABLED) {
11132 if (queues_left > 1) {
11133 queues_left -= 1; /* save 1 queue for FD */
11134 } else {
11135 pf->flags &= ~I40E_FLAG_FD_SB_ENABLED;
11136 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "not enough queues for Flow Director. Flow Director feature is disabled\n");
11137 }
11138 }
11139
11140 if ((pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_SRIOV_ENABLED) &&
11141 pf->num_vf_qps && pf->num_req_vfs && queues_left) {
11142 pf->num_req_vfs = min_t(int, pf->num_req_vfs,
11143 (queues_left / pf->num_vf_qps));
11144 queues_left -= (pf->num_req_vfs * pf->num_vf_qps);
11145 }
11146
11147 if ((pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_VMDQ_ENABLED) &&
11148 pf->num_vmdq_vsis && pf->num_vmdq_qps && queues_left) {
11149 pf->num_vmdq_vsis = min_t(int, pf->num_vmdq_vsis,
11150 (queues_left / pf->num_vmdq_qps));
11151 queues_left -= (pf->num_vmdq_vsis * pf->num_vmdq_qps);
11152 }
11153
11154 pf->queues_left = queues_left;
11155 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev,
11156 "qs_avail=%d FD SB=%d lan_qs=%d lan_tc0=%d vf=%d*%d vmdq=%d*%d, remaining=%d\n",
11157 pf->hw.func_caps.num_tx_qp,
11158 !!(pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_FD_SB_ENABLED),
11159 pf->num_lan_qps, pf->alloc_rss_size, pf->num_req_vfs,
11160 pf->num_vf_qps, pf->num_vmdq_vsis, pf->num_vmdq_qps,
11161 queues_left);
11162}
11163
11164/**
11165 * i40e_setup_pf_filter_control - Setup PF static filter control
11166 * @pf: PF to be setup
11167 *
11168 * i40e_setup_pf_filter_control sets up a PF's initial filter control
11169 * settings. If PE/FCoE are enabled then it will also set the per PF
11170 * based filter sizes required for them. It also enables Flow director,
11171 * ethertype and macvlan type filter settings for the pf.
11172 *
11173 * Returns 0 on success, negative on failure
11174 **/
11175static int i40e_setup_pf_filter_control(struct i40e_pf *pf)
11176{
11177 struct i40e_filter_control_settings *settings = &pf->filter_settings;
11178
11179 settings->hash_lut_size = I40E_HASH_LUT_SIZE_128;
11180
11181 /* Flow Director is enabled */
11182 if (pf->flags & (I40E_FLAG_FD_SB_ENABLED | I40E_FLAG_FD_ATR_ENABLED))
11183 settings->enable_fdir = true;
11184
11185 /* Ethtype and MACVLAN filters enabled for PF */
11186 settings->enable_ethtype = true;
11187 settings->enable_macvlan = true;
11188
11189 if (i40e_set_filter_control(&pf->hw, settings))
11190 return -ENOENT;
11191
11192 return 0;
11193}
11194
11195#define INFO_STRING_LEN 255
11196#define REMAIN(__x) (INFO_STRING_LEN - (__x))
11197static void i40e_print_features(struct i40e_pf *pf)
11198{
11199 struct i40e_hw *hw = &pf->hw;
11200 char *buf;
11201 int i;
11202
11203 buf = kmalloc(INFO_STRING_LEN, GFP_KERNEL);
11204 if (!buf)
11205 return;
11206
11207 i = snprintf(buf, INFO_STRING_LEN, "Features: PF-id[%d]", hw->pf_id);
11208#ifdef CONFIG_PCI_IOV
11209 i += snprintf(&buf[i], REMAIN(i), " VFs: %d", pf->num_req_vfs);
11210#endif
11211 i += snprintf(&buf[i], REMAIN(i), " VSIs: %d QP: %d",
11212 pf->hw.func_caps.num_vsis,
11213 pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi]->num_queue_pairs);
11214 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_RSS_ENABLED)
11215 i += snprintf(&buf[i], REMAIN(i), " RSS");
11216 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_FD_ATR_ENABLED)
11217 i += snprintf(&buf[i], REMAIN(i), " FD_ATR");
11218 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_FD_SB_ENABLED) {
11219 i += snprintf(&buf[i], REMAIN(i), " FD_SB");
11220 i += snprintf(&buf[i], REMAIN(i), " NTUPLE");
11221 }
11222 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_DCB_CAPABLE)
11223 i += snprintf(&buf[i], REMAIN(i), " DCB");
11224 i += snprintf(&buf[i], REMAIN(i), " VxLAN");
11225 i += snprintf(&buf[i], REMAIN(i), " Geneve");
11226 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_PTP)
11227 i += snprintf(&buf[i], REMAIN(i), " PTP");
11228 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_VEB_MODE_ENABLED)
11229 i += snprintf(&buf[i], REMAIN(i), " VEB");
11230 else
11231 i += snprintf(&buf[i], REMAIN(i), " VEPA");
11232
11233 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "%s\n", buf);
11234 kfree(buf);
11235 WARN_ON(i > INFO_STRING_LEN);
11236}
11237
11238/**
11239 * i40e_get_platform_mac_addr - get platform-specific MAC address
11240 * @pdev: PCI device information struct
11241 * @pf: board private structure
11242 *
11243 * Look up the MAC address for the device. First we'll try
11244 * eth_platform_get_mac_address, which will check Open Firmware, or arch
11245 * specific fallback. Otherwise, we'll default to the stored value in
11246 * firmware.
11247 **/
11248static void i40e_get_platform_mac_addr(struct pci_dev *pdev, struct i40e_pf *pf)
11249{
11250 if (eth_platform_get_mac_address(&pdev->dev, pf->hw.mac.addr))
11251 i40e_get_mac_addr(&pf->hw, pf->hw.mac.addr);
11252}
11253
11254/**
11255 * i40e_probe - Device initialization routine
11256 * @pdev: PCI device information struct
11257 * @ent: entry in i40e_pci_tbl
11258 *
11259 * i40e_probe initializes a PF identified by a pci_dev structure.
11260 * The OS initialization, configuring of the PF private structure,
11261 * and a hardware reset occur.
11262 *
11263 * Returns 0 on success, negative on failure
11264 **/
11265static int i40e_probe(struct pci_dev *pdev, const struct pci_device_id *ent)
11266{
11267 struct i40e_aq_get_phy_abilities_resp abilities;
11268 struct i40e_pf *pf;
11269 struct i40e_hw *hw;
11270 static u16 pfs_found;
11271 u16 wol_nvm_bits;
11272 u16 link_status;
11273 int err;
11274 u32 val;
11275 u32 i;
11276 u8 set_fc_aq_fail;
11277
11278 err = pci_enable_device_mem(pdev);
11279 if (err)
11280 return err;
11281
11282 /* set up for high or low dma */
11283 err = dma_set_mask_and_coherent(&pdev->dev, DMA_BIT_MASK(64));
11284 if (err) {
11285 err = dma_set_mask_and_coherent(&pdev->dev, DMA_BIT_MASK(32));
11286 if (err) {
11287 dev_err(&pdev->dev,
11288 "DMA configuration failed: 0x%x\n", err);
11289 goto err_dma;
11290 }
11291 }
11292
11293 /* set up pci connections */
11294 err = pci_request_mem_regions(pdev, i40e_driver_name);
11295 if (err) {
11296 dev_info(&pdev->dev,
11297 "pci_request_selected_regions failed %d\n", err);
11298 goto err_pci_reg;
11299 }
11300
11301 pci_enable_pcie_error_reporting(pdev);
11302 pci_set_master(pdev);
11303
11304 /* Now that we have a PCI connection, we need to do the
11305 * low level device setup. This is primarily setting up
11306 * the Admin Queue structures and then querying for the
11307 * device's current profile information.
11308 */
11309 pf = kzalloc(sizeof(*pf), GFP_KERNEL);
11310 if (!pf) {
11311 err = -ENOMEM;
11312 goto err_pf_alloc;
11313 }
11314 pf->next_vsi = 0;
11315 pf->pdev = pdev;
11316 set_bit(__I40E_DOWN, pf->state);
11317
11318 hw = &pf->hw;
11319 hw->back = pf;
11320
11321 pf->ioremap_len = min_t(int, pci_resource_len(pdev, 0),
11322 I40E_MAX_CSR_SPACE);
11323
11324 hw->hw_addr = ioremap(pci_resource_start(pdev, 0), pf->ioremap_len);
11325 if (!hw->hw_addr) {
11326 err = -EIO;
11327 dev_info(&pdev->dev, "ioremap(0x%04x, 0x%04x) failed: 0x%x\n",
11328 (unsigned int)pci_resource_start(pdev, 0),
11329 pf->ioremap_len, err);
11330 goto err_ioremap;
11331 }
11332 hw->vendor_id = pdev->vendor;
11333 hw->device_id = pdev->device;
11334 pci_read_config_byte(pdev, PCI_REVISION_ID, &hw->revision_id);
11335 hw->subsystem_vendor_id = pdev->subsystem_vendor;
11336 hw->subsystem_device_id = pdev->subsystem_device;
11337 hw->bus.device = PCI_SLOT(pdev->devfn);
11338 hw->bus.func = PCI_FUNC(pdev->devfn);
11339 hw->bus.bus_id = pdev->bus->number;
11340 pf->instance = pfs_found;
11341
11342 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&pf->l3_flex_pit_list);
11343 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&pf->l4_flex_pit_list);
11344
11345 /* set up the locks for the AQ, do this only once in probe
11346 * and destroy them only once in remove
11347 */
11348 mutex_init(&hw->aq.asq_mutex);
11349 mutex_init(&hw->aq.arq_mutex);
11350
11351 pf->msg_enable = netif_msg_init(debug,
11352 NETIF_MSG_DRV |
11353 NETIF_MSG_PROBE |
11354 NETIF_MSG_LINK);
11355 if (debug < -1)
11356 pf->hw.debug_mask = debug;
11357
11358 /* do a special CORER for clearing PXE mode once at init */
11359 if (hw->revision_id == 0 &&
11360 (rd32(hw, I40E_GLLAN_RCTL_0) & I40E_GLLAN_RCTL_0_PXE_MODE_MASK)) {
11361 wr32(hw, I40E_GLGEN_RTRIG, I40E_GLGEN_RTRIG_CORER_MASK);
11362 i40e_flush(hw);
11363 msleep(200);
11364 pf->corer_count++;
11365
11366 i40e_clear_pxe_mode(hw);
11367 }
11368
11369 /* Reset here to make sure all is clean and to define PF 'n' */
11370 i40e_clear_hw(hw);
11371 err = i40e_pf_reset(hw);
11372 if (err) {
11373 dev_info(&pdev->dev, "Initial pf_reset failed: %d\n", err);
11374 goto err_pf_reset;
11375 }
11376 pf->pfr_count++;
11377
11378 hw->aq.num_arq_entries = I40E_AQ_LEN;
11379 hw->aq.num_asq_entries = I40E_AQ_LEN;
11380 hw->aq.arq_buf_size = I40E_MAX_AQ_BUF_SIZE;
11381 hw->aq.asq_buf_size = I40E_MAX_AQ_BUF_SIZE;
11382 pf->adminq_work_limit = I40E_AQ_WORK_LIMIT;
11383
11384 snprintf(pf->int_name, sizeof(pf->int_name) - 1,
11385 "%s-%s:misc",
11386 dev_driver_string(&pf->pdev->dev), dev_name(&pdev->dev));
11387
11388 err = i40e_init_shared_code(hw);
11389 if (err) {
11390 dev_warn(&pdev->dev, "unidentified MAC or BLANK NVM: %d\n",
11391 err);
11392 goto err_pf_reset;
11393 }
11394
11395 /* set up a default setting for link flow control */
11396 pf->hw.fc.requested_mode = I40E_FC_NONE;
11397
11398 err = i40e_init_adminq(hw);
11399 if (err) {
11400 if (err == I40E_ERR_FIRMWARE_API_VERSION)
11401 dev_info(&pdev->dev,
11402 "The driver for the device stopped because the NVM image is newer than expected. You must install the most recent version of the network driver.\n");
11403 else
11404 dev_info(&pdev->dev,
11405 "The driver for the device stopped because the device firmware failed to init. Try updating your NVM image.\n");
11406
11407 goto err_pf_reset;
11408 }
11409 i40e_get_oem_version(hw);
11410
11411 /* provide nvm, fw, api versions */
11412 dev_info(&pdev->dev, "fw %d.%d.%05d api %d.%d nvm %s\n",
11413 hw->aq.fw_maj_ver, hw->aq.fw_min_ver, hw->aq.fw_build,
11414 hw->aq.api_maj_ver, hw->aq.api_min_ver,
11415 i40e_nvm_version_str(hw));
11416
11417 if (hw->aq.api_maj_ver == I40E_FW_API_VERSION_MAJOR &&
11418 hw->aq.api_min_ver > I40E_FW_API_VERSION_MINOR)
11419 dev_info(&pdev->dev,
11420 "The driver for the device detected a newer version of the NVM image than expected. Please install the most recent version of the network driver.\n");
11421 else if (hw->aq.api_maj_ver < I40E_FW_API_VERSION_MAJOR ||
11422 hw->aq.api_min_ver < (I40E_FW_API_VERSION_MINOR - 1))
11423 dev_info(&pdev->dev,
11424 "The driver for the device detected an older version of the NVM image than expected. Please update the NVM image.\n");
11425
11426 i40e_verify_eeprom(pf);
11427
11428 /* Rev 0 hardware was never productized */
11429 if (hw->revision_id < 1)
11430 dev_warn(&pdev->dev, "This device is a pre-production adapter/LOM. Please be aware there may be issues with your hardware. If you are experiencing problems please contact your Intel or hardware representative who provided you with this hardware.\n");
11431
11432 i40e_clear_pxe_mode(hw);
11433 err = i40e_get_capabilities(pf);
11434 if (err)
11435 goto err_adminq_setup;
11436
11437 err = i40e_sw_init(pf);
11438 if (err) {
11439 dev_info(&pdev->dev, "sw_init failed: %d\n", err);
11440 goto err_sw_init;
11441 }
11442
11443 err = i40e_init_lan_hmc(hw, hw->func_caps.num_tx_qp,
11444 hw->func_caps.num_rx_qp, 0, 0);
11445 if (err) {
11446 dev_info(&pdev->dev, "init_lan_hmc failed: %d\n", err);
11447 goto err_init_lan_hmc;
11448 }
11449
11450 err = i40e_configure_lan_hmc(hw, I40E_HMC_MODEL_DIRECT_ONLY);
11451 if (err) {
11452 dev_info(&pdev->dev, "configure_lan_hmc failed: %d\n", err);
11453 err = -ENOENT;
11454 goto err_configure_lan_hmc;
11455 }
11456
11457 /* Disable LLDP for NICs that have firmware versions lower than v4.3.
11458 * Ignore error return codes because if it was already disabled via
11459 * hardware settings this will fail
11460 */
11461 if (pf->hw_features & I40E_HW_STOP_FW_LLDP) {
11462 dev_info(&pdev->dev, "Stopping firmware LLDP agent.\n");
11463 i40e_aq_stop_lldp(hw, true, NULL);
11464 }
11465
11466 /* allow a platform config to override the HW addr */
11467 i40e_get_platform_mac_addr(pdev, pf);
11468
11469 if (!is_valid_ether_addr(hw->mac.addr)) {
11470 dev_info(&pdev->dev, "invalid MAC address %pM\n", hw->mac.addr);
11471 err = -EIO;
11472 goto err_mac_addr;
11473 }
11474 dev_info(&pdev->dev, "MAC address: %pM\n", hw->mac.addr);
11475 ether_addr_copy(hw->mac.perm_addr, hw->mac.addr);
11476 i40e_get_port_mac_addr(hw, hw->mac.port_addr);
11477 if (is_valid_ether_addr(hw->mac.port_addr))
11478 pf->hw_features |= I40E_HW_PORT_ID_VALID;
11479
11480 pci_set_drvdata(pdev, pf);
11481 pci_save_state(pdev);
11482#ifdef CONFIG_I40E_DCB
11483 err = i40e_init_pf_dcb(pf);
11484 if (err) {
11485 dev_info(&pdev->dev, "DCB init failed %d, disabled\n", err);
11486 pf->flags &= ~(I40E_FLAG_DCB_CAPABLE | I40E_FLAG_DCB_ENABLED);
11487 /* Continue without DCB enabled */
11488 }
11489#endif /* CONFIG_I40E_DCB */
11490
11491 /* set up periodic task facility */
11492 setup_timer(&pf->service_timer, i40e_service_timer, (unsigned long)pf);
11493 pf->service_timer_period = HZ;
11494
11495 INIT_WORK(&pf->service_task, i40e_service_task);
11496 clear_bit(__I40E_SERVICE_SCHED, pf->state);
11497
11498 /* NVM bit on means WoL disabled for the port */
11499 i40e_read_nvm_word(hw, I40E_SR_NVM_WAKE_ON_LAN, &wol_nvm_bits);
11500 if (BIT (hw->port) & wol_nvm_bits || hw->partition_id != 1)
11501 pf->wol_en = false;
11502 else
11503 pf->wol_en = true;
11504 device_set_wakeup_enable(&pf->pdev->dev, pf->wol_en);
11505
11506 /* set up the main switch operations */
11507 i40e_determine_queue_usage(pf);
11508 err = i40e_init_interrupt_scheme(pf);
11509 if (err)
11510 goto err_switch_setup;
11511
11512 /* The number of VSIs reported by the FW is the minimum guaranteed
11513 * to us; HW supports far more and we share the remaining pool with
11514 * the other PFs. We allocate space for more than the guarantee with
11515 * the understanding that we might not get them all later.
11516 */
11517 if (pf->hw.func_caps.num_vsis < I40E_MIN_VSI_ALLOC)
11518 pf->num_alloc_vsi = I40E_MIN_VSI_ALLOC;
11519 else
11520 pf->num_alloc_vsi = pf->hw.func_caps.num_vsis;
11521
11522 /* Set up the *vsi struct and our local tracking of the MAIN PF vsi. */
11523 pf->vsi = kcalloc(pf->num_alloc_vsi, sizeof(struct i40e_vsi *),
11524 GFP_KERNEL);
11525 if (!pf->vsi) {
11526 err = -ENOMEM;
11527 goto err_switch_setup;
11528 }
11529
11530#ifdef CONFIG_PCI_IOV
11531 /* prep for VF support */
11532 if ((pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_SRIOV_ENABLED) &&
11533 (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_MSIX_ENABLED) &&
11534 !test_bit(__I40E_BAD_EEPROM, pf->state)) {
11535 if (pci_num_vf(pdev))
11536 pf->flags |= I40E_FLAG_VEB_MODE_ENABLED;
11537 }
11538#endif
11539 err = i40e_setup_pf_switch(pf, false);
11540 if (err) {
11541 dev_info(&pdev->dev, "setup_pf_switch failed: %d\n", err);
11542 goto err_vsis;
11543 }
11544
11545 /* Make sure flow control is set according to current settings */
11546 err = i40e_set_fc(hw, &set_fc_aq_fail, true);
11547 if (set_fc_aq_fail & I40E_SET_FC_AQ_FAIL_GET)
11548 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev,
11549 "Set fc with err %s aq_err %s on get_phy_cap\n",
11550 i40e_stat_str(hw, err),
11551 i40e_aq_str(hw, hw->aq.asq_last_status));
11552 if (set_fc_aq_fail & I40E_SET_FC_AQ_FAIL_SET)
11553 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev,
11554 "Set fc with err %s aq_err %s on set_phy_config\n",
11555 i40e_stat_str(hw, err),
11556 i40e_aq_str(hw, hw->aq.asq_last_status));
11557 if (set_fc_aq_fail & I40E_SET_FC_AQ_FAIL_UPDATE)
11558 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev,
11559 "Set fc with err %s aq_err %s on get_link_info\n",
11560 i40e_stat_str(hw, err),
11561 i40e_aq_str(hw, hw->aq.asq_last_status));
11562
11563 /* if FDIR VSI was set up, start it now */
11564 for (i = 0; i < pf->num_alloc_vsi; i++) {
11565 if (pf->vsi[i] && pf->vsi[i]->type == I40E_VSI_FDIR) {
11566 i40e_vsi_open(pf->vsi[i]);
11567 break;
11568 }
11569 }
11570
11571 /* The driver only wants link up/down and module qualification
11572 * reports from firmware. Note the negative logic.
11573 */
11574 err = i40e_aq_set_phy_int_mask(&pf->hw,
11575 ~(I40E_AQ_EVENT_LINK_UPDOWN |
11576 I40E_AQ_EVENT_MEDIA_NA |
11577 I40E_AQ_EVENT_MODULE_QUAL_FAIL), NULL);
11578 if (err)
11579 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "set phy mask fail, err %s aq_err %s\n",
11580 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, err),
11581 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw, pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
11582
11583 /* Reconfigure hardware for allowing smaller MSS in the case
11584 * of TSO, so that we avoid the MDD being fired and causing
11585 * a reset in the case of small MSS+TSO.
11586 */
11587 val = rd32(hw, I40E_REG_MSS);
11588 if ((val & I40E_REG_MSS_MIN_MASK) > I40E_64BYTE_MSS) {
11589 val &= ~I40E_REG_MSS_MIN_MASK;
11590 val |= I40E_64BYTE_MSS;
11591 wr32(hw, I40E_REG_MSS, val);
11592 }
11593
11594 if (pf->hw_features & I40E_HW_RESTART_AUTONEG) {
11595 msleep(75);
11596 err = i40e_aq_set_link_restart_an(&pf->hw, true, NULL);
11597 if (err)
11598 dev_info(&pf->pdev->dev, "link restart failed, err %s aq_err %s\n",
11599 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, err),
11600 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw,
11601 pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
11602 }
11603 /* The main driver is (mostly) up and happy. We need to set this state
11604 * before setting up the misc vector or we get a race and the vector
11605 * ends up disabled forever.
11606 */
11607 clear_bit(__I40E_DOWN, pf->state);
11608
11609 /* In case of MSIX we are going to setup the misc vector right here
11610 * to handle admin queue events etc. In case of legacy and MSI
11611 * the misc functionality and queue processing is combined in
11612 * the same vector and that gets setup at open.
11613 */
11614 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_MSIX_ENABLED) {
11615 err = i40e_setup_misc_vector(pf);
11616 if (err) {
11617 dev_info(&pdev->dev,
11618 "setup of misc vector failed: %d\n", err);
11619 goto err_vsis;
11620 }
11621 }
11622
11623#ifdef CONFIG_PCI_IOV
11624 /* prep for VF support */
11625 if ((pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_SRIOV_ENABLED) &&
11626 (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_MSIX_ENABLED) &&
11627 !test_bit(__I40E_BAD_EEPROM, pf->state)) {
11628 /* disable link interrupts for VFs */
11629 val = rd32(hw, I40E_PFGEN_PORTMDIO_NUM);
11630 val &= ~I40E_PFGEN_PORTMDIO_NUM_VFLINK_STAT_ENA_MASK;
11631 wr32(hw, I40E_PFGEN_PORTMDIO_NUM, val);
11632 i40e_flush(hw);
11633
11634 if (pci_num_vf(pdev)) {
11635 dev_info(&pdev->dev,
11636 "Active VFs found, allocating resources.\n");
11637 err = i40e_alloc_vfs(pf, pci_num_vf(pdev));
11638 if (err)
11639 dev_info(&pdev->dev,
11640 "Error %d allocating resources for existing VFs\n",
11641 err);
11642 }
11643 }
11644#endif /* CONFIG_PCI_IOV */
11645
11646 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_IWARP_ENABLED) {
11647 pf->iwarp_base_vector = i40e_get_lump(pf, pf->irq_pile,
11648 pf->num_iwarp_msix,
11649 I40E_IWARP_IRQ_PILE_ID);
11650 if (pf->iwarp_base_vector < 0) {
11651 dev_info(&pdev->dev,
11652 "failed to get tracking for %d vectors for IWARP err=%d\n",
11653 pf->num_iwarp_msix, pf->iwarp_base_vector);
11654 pf->flags &= ~I40E_FLAG_IWARP_ENABLED;
11655 }
11656 }
11657
11658 i40e_dbg_pf_init(pf);
11659
11660 /* tell the firmware that we're starting */
11661 i40e_send_version(pf);
11662
11663 /* since everything's happy, start the service_task timer */
11664 mod_timer(&pf->service_timer,
11665 round_jiffies(jiffies + pf->service_timer_period));
11666
11667 /* add this PF to client device list and launch a client service task */
11668 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_IWARP_ENABLED) {
11669 err = i40e_lan_add_device(pf);
11670 if (err)
11671 dev_info(&pdev->dev, "Failed to add PF to client API service list: %d\n",
11672 err);
11673 }
11674
11675#define PCI_SPEED_SIZE 8
11676#define PCI_WIDTH_SIZE 8
11677 /* Devices on the IOSF bus do not have this information
11678 * and will report PCI Gen 1 x 1 by default so don't bother
11679 * checking them.
11680 */
11681 if (!(pf->hw_features & I40E_HW_NO_PCI_LINK_CHECK)) {
11682 char speed[PCI_SPEED_SIZE] = "Unknown";
11683 char width[PCI_WIDTH_SIZE] = "Unknown";
11684
11685 /* Get the negotiated link width and speed from PCI config
11686 * space
11687 */
11688 pcie_capability_read_word(pf->pdev, PCI_EXP_LNKSTA,
11689 &link_status);
11690
11691 i40e_set_pci_config_data(hw, link_status);
11692
11693 switch (hw->bus.speed) {
11694 case i40e_bus_speed_8000:
11695 strncpy(speed, "8.0", PCI_SPEED_SIZE); break;
11696 case i40e_bus_speed_5000:
11697 strncpy(speed, "5.0", PCI_SPEED_SIZE); break;
11698 case i40e_bus_speed_2500:
11699 strncpy(speed, "2.5", PCI_SPEED_SIZE); break;
11700 default:
11701 break;
11702 }
11703 switch (hw->bus.width) {
11704 case i40e_bus_width_pcie_x8:
11705 strncpy(width, "8", PCI_WIDTH_SIZE); break;
11706 case i40e_bus_width_pcie_x4:
11707 strncpy(width, "4", PCI_WIDTH_SIZE); break;
11708 case i40e_bus_width_pcie_x2:
11709 strncpy(width, "2", PCI_WIDTH_SIZE); break;
11710 case i40e_bus_width_pcie_x1:
11711 strncpy(width, "1", PCI_WIDTH_SIZE); break;
11712 default:
11713 break;
11714 }
11715
11716 dev_info(&pdev->dev, "PCI-Express: Speed %sGT/s Width x%s\n",
11717 speed, width);
11718
11719 if (hw->bus.width < i40e_bus_width_pcie_x8 ||
11720 hw->bus.speed < i40e_bus_speed_8000) {
11721 dev_warn(&pdev->dev, "PCI-Express bandwidth available for this device may be insufficient for optimal performance.\n");
11722 dev_warn(&pdev->dev, "Please move the device to a different PCI-e link with more lanes and/or higher transfer rate.\n");
11723 }
11724 }
11725
11726 /* get the requested speeds from the fw */
11727 err = i40e_aq_get_phy_capabilities(hw, false, false, &abilities, NULL);
11728 if (err)
11729 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev, "get requested speeds ret = %s last_status = %s\n",
11730 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, err),
11731 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw, pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
11732 pf->hw.phy.link_info.requested_speeds = abilities.link_speed;
11733
11734 /* get the supported phy types from the fw */
11735 err = i40e_aq_get_phy_capabilities(hw, false, true, &abilities, NULL);
11736 if (err)
11737 dev_dbg(&pf->pdev->dev, "get supported phy types ret = %s last_status = %s\n",
11738 i40e_stat_str(&pf->hw, err),
11739 i40e_aq_str(&pf->hw, pf->hw.aq.asq_last_status));
11740
11741 /* Add a filter to drop all Flow control frames from any VSI from being
11742 * transmitted. By doing so we stop a malicious VF from sending out
11743 * PAUSE or PFC frames and potentially controlling traffic for other
11744 * PF/VF VSIs.
11745 * The FW can still send Flow control frames if enabled.
11746 */
11747 i40e_add_filter_to_drop_tx_flow_control_frames(&pf->hw,
11748 pf->main_vsi_seid);
11749
11750 if ((pf->hw.device_id == I40E_DEV_ID_10G_BASE_T) ||
11751 (pf->hw.device_id == I40E_DEV_ID_10G_BASE_T4))
11752 pf->hw_features |= I40E_HW_PHY_CONTROLS_LEDS;
11753 if (pf->hw.device_id == I40E_DEV_ID_SFP_I_X722)
11754 pf->hw_features |= I40E_HW_HAVE_CRT_RETIMER;
11755 /* print a string summarizing features */
11756 i40e_print_features(pf);
11757
11758 return 0;
11759
11760 /* Unwind what we've done if something failed in the setup */
11761err_vsis:
11762 set_bit(__I40E_DOWN, pf->state);
11763 i40e_clear_interrupt_scheme(pf);
11764 kfree(pf->vsi);
11765err_switch_setup:
11766 i40e_reset_interrupt_capability(pf);
11767 del_timer_sync(&pf->service_timer);
11768err_mac_addr:
11769err_configure_lan_hmc:
11770 (void)i40e_shutdown_lan_hmc(hw);
11771err_init_lan_hmc:
11772 kfree(pf->qp_pile);
11773err_sw_init:
11774err_adminq_setup:
11775err_pf_reset:
11776 iounmap(hw->hw_addr);
11777err_ioremap:
11778 kfree(pf);
11779err_pf_alloc:
11780 pci_disable_pcie_error_reporting(pdev);
11781 pci_release_mem_regions(pdev);
11782err_pci_reg:
11783err_dma:
11784 pci_disable_device(pdev);
11785 return err;
11786}
11787
11788/**
11789 * i40e_remove - Device removal routine
11790 * @pdev: PCI device information struct
11791 *
11792 * i40e_remove is called by the PCI subsystem to alert the driver
11793 * that is should release a PCI device. This could be caused by a
11794 * Hot-Plug event, or because the driver is going to be removed from
11795 * memory.
11796 **/
11797static void i40e_remove(struct pci_dev *pdev)
11798{
11799 struct i40e_pf *pf = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
11800 struct i40e_hw *hw = &pf->hw;
11801 i40e_status ret_code;
11802 int i;
11803
11804 i40e_dbg_pf_exit(pf);
11805
11806 i40e_ptp_stop(pf);
11807
11808 /* Disable RSS in hw */
11809 i40e_write_rx_ctl(hw, I40E_PFQF_HENA(0), 0);
11810 i40e_write_rx_ctl(hw, I40E_PFQF_HENA(1), 0);
11811
11812 /* no more scheduling of any task */
11813 set_bit(__I40E_SUSPENDED, pf->state);
11814 set_bit(__I40E_DOWN, pf->state);
11815 if (pf->service_timer.data)
11816 del_timer_sync(&pf->service_timer);
11817 if (pf->service_task.func)
11818 cancel_work_sync(&pf->service_task);
11819
11820 /* Client close must be called explicitly here because the timer
11821 * has been stopped.
11822 */
11823 i40e_notify_client_of_netdev_close(pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi], false);
11824
11825 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_SRIOV_ENABLED) {
11826 i40e_free_vfs(pf);
11827 pf->flags &= ~I40E_FLAG_SRIOV_ENABLED;
11828 }
11829
11830 i40e_fdir_teardown(pf);
11831
11832 /* If there is a switch structure or any orphans, remove them.
11833 * This will leave only the PF's VSI remaining.
11834 */
11835 for (i = 0; i < I40E_MAX_VEB; i++) {
11836 if (!pf->veb[i])
11837 continue;
11838
11839 if (pf->veb[i]->uplink_seid == pf->mac_seid ||
11840 pf->veb[i]->uplink_seid == 0)
11841 i40e_switch_branch_release(pf->veb[i]);
11842 }
11843
11844 /* Now we can shutdown the PF's VSI, just before we kill
11845 * adminq and hmc.
11846 */
11847 if (pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi])
11848 i40e_vsi_release(pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi]);
11849
11850 /* remove attached clients */
11851 if (pf->flags & I40E_FLAG_IWARP_ENABLED) {
11852 ret_code = i40e_lan_del_device(pf);
11853 if (ret_code)
11854 dev_warn(&pdev->dev, "Failed to delete client device: %d\n",
11855 ret_code);
11856 }
11857
11858 /* shutdown and destroy the HMC */
11859 if (hw->hmc.hmc_obj) {
11860 ret_code = i40e_shutdown_lan_hmc(hw);
11861 if (ret_code)
11862 dev_warn(&pdev->dev,
11863 "Failed to destroy the HMC resources: %d\n",
11864 ret_code);
11865 }
11866
11867 /* shutdown the adminq */
11868 i40e_shutdown_adminq(hw);
11869
11870 /* destroy the locks only once, here */
11871 mutex_destroy(&hw->aq.arq_mutex);
11872 mutex_destroy(&hw->aq.asq_mutex);
11873
11874 /* Clear all dynamic memory lists of rings, q_vectors, and VSIs */
11875 i40e_clear_interrupt_scheme(pf);
11876 for (i = 0; i < pf->num_alloc_vsi; i++) {
11877 if (pf->vsi[i]) {
11878 i40e_vsi_clear_rings(pf->vsi[i]);
11879 i40e_vsi_clear(pf->vsi[i]);
11880 pf->vsi[i] = NULL;
11881 }
11882 }
11883
11884 for (i = 0; i < I40E_MAX_VEB; i++) {
11885 kfree(pf->veb[i]);
11886 pf->veb[i] = NULL;
11887 }
11888
11889 kfree(pf->qp_pile);
11890 kfree(pf->vsi);
11891
11892 iounmap(hw->hw_addr);
11893 kfree(pf);
11894 pci_release_mem_regions(pdev);
11895
11896 pci_disable_pcie_error_reporting(pdev);
11897 pci_disable_device(pdev);
11898}
11899
11900/**
11901 * i40e_pci_error_detected - warning that something funky happened in PCI land
11902 * @pdev: PCI device information struct
11903 *
11904 * Called to warn that something happened and the error handling steps
11905 * are in progress. Allows the driver to quiesce things, be ready for
11906 * remediation.
11907 **/
11908static pci_ers_result_t i40e_pci_error_detected(struct pci_dev *pdev,
11909 enum pci_channel_state error)
11910{
11911 struct i40e_pf *pf = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
11912
11913 dev_info(&pdev->dev, "%s: error %d\n", __func__, error);
11914
11915 if (!pf) {
11916 dev_info(&pdev->dev,
11917 "Cannot recover - error happened during device probe\n");
11918 return PCI_ERS_RESULT_DISCONNECT;
11919 }
11920
11921 /* shutdown all operations */
11922 if (!test_bit(__I40E_SUSPENDED, pf->state))
11923 i40e_prep_for_reset(pf, false);
11924
11925 /* Request a slot reset */
11926 return PCI_ERS_RESULT_NEED_RESET;
11927}
11928
11929/**
11930 * i40e_pci_error_slot_reset - a PCI slot reset just happened
11931 * @pdev: PCI device information struct
11932 *
11933 * Called to find if the driver can work with the device now that
11934 * the pci slot has been reset. If a basic connection seems good
11935 * (registers are readable and have sane content) then return a
11936 * happy little PCI_ERS_RESULT_xxx.
11937 **/
11938static pci_ers_result_t i40e_pci_error_slot_reset(struct pci_dev *pdev)
11939{
11940 struct i40e_pf *pf = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
11941 pci_ers_result_t result;
11942 int err;
11943 u32 reg;
11944
11945 dev_dbg(&pdev->dev, "%s\n", __func__);
11946 if (pci_enable_device_mem(pdev)) {
11947 dev_info(&pdev->dev,
11948 "Cannot re-enable PCI device after reset.\n");
11949 result = PCI_ERS_RESULT_DISCONNECT;
11950 } else {
11951 pci_set_master(pdev);
11952 pci_restore_state(pdev);
11953 pci_save_state(pdev);
11954 pci_wake_from_d3(pdev, false);
11955
11956 reg = rd32(&pf->hw, I40E_GLGEN_RTRIG);
11957 if (reg == 0)
11958 result = PCI_ERS_RESULT_RECOVERED;
11959 else
11960 result = PCI_ERS_RESULT_DISCONNECT;
11961 }
11962
11963 err = pci_cleanup_aer_uncorrect_error_status(pdev);
11964 if (err) {
11965 dev_info(&pdev->dev,
11966 "pci_cleanup_aer_uncorrect_error_status failed 0x%0x\n",
11967 err);
11968 /* non-fatal, continue */
11969 }
11970
11971 return result;
11972}
11973
11974/**
11975 * i40e_pci_error_resume - restart operations after PCI error recovery
11976 * @pdev: PCI device information struct
11977 *
11978 * Called to allow the driver to bring things back up after PCI error
11979 * and/or reset recovery has finished.
11980 **/
11981static void i40e_pci_error_resume(struct pci_dev *pdev)
11982{
11983 struct i40e_pf *pf = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
11984
11985 dev_dbg(&pdev->dev, "%s\n", __func__);
11986 if (test_bit(__I40E_SUSPENDED, pf->state))
11987 return;
11988
11989 i40e_handle_reset_warning(pf, false);
11990}
11991
11992/**
11993 * i40e_enable_mc_magic_wake - enable multicast magic packet wake up
11994 * using the mac_address_write admin q function
11995 * @pf: pointer to i40e_pf struct
11996 **/
11997static void i40e_enable_mc_magic_wake(struct i40e_pf *pf)
11998{
11999 struct i40e_hw *hw = &pf->hw;
12000 i40e_status ret;
12001 u8 mac_addr[6];
12002 u16 flags = 0;
12003
12004 /* Get current MAC address in case it's an LAA */
12005 if (pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi] && pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi]->netdev) {
12006 ether_addr_copy(mac_addr,
12007 pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi]->netdev->dev_addr);
12008 } else {
12009 dev_err(&pf->pdev->dev,
12010 "Failed to retrieve MAC address; using default\n");
12011 ether_addr_copy(mac_addr, hw->mac.addr);
12012 }
12013
12014 /* The FW expects the mac address write cmd to first be called with
12015 * one of these flags before calling it again with the multicast
12016 * enable flags.
12017 */
12018 flags = I40E_AQC_WRITE_TYPE_LAA_WOL;
12019
12020 if (hw->func_caps.flex10_enable && hw->partition_id != 1)
12021 flags = I40E_AQC_WRITE_TYPE_LAA_ONLY;
12022
12023 ret = i40e_aq_mac_address_write(hw, flags, mac_addr, NULL);
12024 if (ret) {
12025 dev_err(&pf->pdev->dev,
12026 "Failed to update MAC address registers; cannot enable Multicast Magic packet wake up");
12027 return;
12028 }
12029
12030 flags = I40E_AQC_MC_MAG_EN
12031 | I40E_AQC_WOL_PRESERVE_ON_PFR
12032 | I40E_AQC_WRITE_TYPE_UPDATE_MC_MAG;
12033 ret = i40e_aq_mac_address_write(hw, flags, mac_addr, NULL);
12034 if (ret)
12035 dev_err(&pf->pdev->dev,
12036 "Failed to enable Multicast Magic Packet wake up\n");
12037}
12038
12039/**
12040 * i40e_shutdown - PCI callback for shutting down
12041 * @pdev: PCI device information struct
12042 **/
12043static void i40e_shutdown(struct pci_dev *pdev)
12044{
12045 struct i40e_pf *pf = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
12046 struct i40e_hw *hw = &pf->hw;
12047
12048 set_bit(__I40E_SUSPENDED, pf->state);
12049 set_bit(__I40E_DOWN, pf->state);
12050 rtnl_lock();
12051 i40e_prep_for_reset(pf, true);
12052 rtnl_unlock();
12053
12054 wr32(hw, I40E_PFPM_APM, (pf->wol_en ? I40E_PFPM_APM_APME_MASK : 0));
12055 wr32(hw, I40E_PFPM_WUFC, (pf->wol_en ? I40E_PFPM_WUFC_MAG_MASK : 0));
12056
12057 del_timer_sync(&pf->service_timer);
12058 cancel_work_sync(&pf->service_task);
12059 i40e_fdir_teardown(pf);
12060
12061 /* Client close must be called explicitly here because the timer
12062 * has been stopped.
12063 */
12064 i40e_notify_client_of_netdev_close(pf->vsi[pf->lan_vsi], false);
12065
12066 if (pf->wol_en && (pf->hw_features & I40E_HW_WOL_MC_MAGIC_PKT_WAKE))
12067 i40e_enable_mc_magic_wake(pf);
12068
12069 i40e_prep_for_reset(pf, false);
12070
12071 wr32(hw, I40E_PFPM_APM,
12072 (pf->wol_en ? I40E_PFPM_APM_APME_MASK : 0));
12073 wr32(hw, I40E_PFPM_WUFC,
12074 (pf->wol_en ? I40E_PFPM_WUFC_MAG_MASK : 0));
12075
12076 i40e_clear_interrupt_scheme(pf);
12077
12078 if (system_state == SYSTEM_POWER_OFF) {
12079 pci_wake_from_d3(pdev, pf->wol_en);
12080 pci_set_power_state(pdev, PCI_D3hot);
12081 }
12082}
12083
12084#ifdef CONFIG_PM
12085/**
12086 * i40e_suspend - PCI callback for moving to D3
12087 * @pdev: PCI device information struct
12088 **/
12089static int i40e_suspend(struct pci_dev *pdev, pm_message_t state)
12090{
12091 struct i40e_pf *pf = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
12092 struct i40e_hw *hw = &pf->hw;
12093 int retval = 0;
12094
12095 set_bit(__I40E_SUSPENDED, pf->state);
12096 set_bit(__I40E_DOWN, pf->state);
12097
12098 if (pf->wol_en && (pf->hw_features & I40E_HW_WOL_MC_MAGIC_PKT_WAKE))
12099 i40e_enable_mc_magic_wake(pf);
12100
12101 i40e_prep_for_reset(pf, false);
12102
12103 wr32(hw, I40E_PFPM_APM, (pf->wol_en ? I40E_PFPM_APM_APME_MASK : 0));
12104 wr32(hw, I40E_PFPM_WUFC, (pf->wol_en ? I40E_PFPM_WUFC_MAG_MASK : 0));
12105
12106 i40e_stop_misc_vector(pf);
12107 if (pf->msix_entries) {
12108 synchronize_irq(pf->msix_entries[0].vector);
12109 free_irq(pf->msix_entries[0].vector, pf);
12110 }
12111 retval = pci_save_state(pdev);
12112 if (retval)
12113 return retval;
12114
12115 pci_wake_from_d3(pdev, pf->wol_en);
12116 pci_set_power_state(pdev, PCI_D3hot);
12117
12118 return retval;
12119}
12120
12121/**
12122 * i40e_resume - PCI callback for waking up from D3
12123 * @pdev: PCI device information struct
12124 **/
12125static int i40e_resume(struct pci_dev *pdev)
12126{
12127 struct i40e_pf *pf = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
12128 u32 err;
12129
12130 pci_set_power_state(pdev, PCI_D0);
12131 pci_restore_state(pdev);
12132 /* pci_restore_state() clears dev->state_saves, so
12133 * call pci_save_state() again to restore it.
12134 */
12135 pci_save_state(pdev);
12136
12137 err = pci_enable_device_mem(pdev);
12138 if (err) {
12139 dev_err(&pdev->dev, "Cannot enable PCI device from suspend\n");
12140 return err;
12141 }
12142 pci_set_master(pdev);
12143
12144 /* no wakeup events while running */
12145 pci_wake_from_d3(pdev, false);
12146
12147 /* handling the reset will rebuild the device state */
12148 if (test_and_clear_bit(__I40E_SUSPENDED, pf->state)) {
12149 clear_bit(__I40E_DOWN, pf->state);
12150 if (pf->msix_entries) {
12151 err = request_irq(pf->msix_entries[0].vector,
12152 i40e_intr, 0, pf->int_name, pf);
12153 if (err) {
12154 dev_err(&pf->pdev->dev,
12155 "request_irq for %s failed: %d\n",
12156 pf->int_name, err);
12157 }
12158 }
12159 i40e_reset_and_rebuild(pf, false, false);
12160 }
12161
12162 return 0;
12163}
12164
12165#endif
12166static const struct pci_error_handlers i40e_err_handler = {
12167 .error_detected = i40e_pci_error_detected,
12168 .slot_reset = i40e_pci_error_slot_reset,
12169 .resume = i40e_pci_error_resume,
12170};
12171
12172static struct pci_driver i40e_driver = {
12173 .name = i40e_driver_name,
12174 .id_table = i40e_pci_tbl,
12175 .probe = i40e_probe,
12176 .remove = i40e_remove,
12177#ifdef CONFIG_PM
12178 .suspend = i40e_suspend,
12179 .resume = i40e_resume,
12180#endif
12181 .shutdown = i40e_shutdown,
12182 .err_handler = &i40e_err_handler,
12183 .sriov_configure = i40e_pci_sriov_configure,
12184};
12185
12186/**
12187 * i40e_init_module - Driver registration routine
12188 *
12189 * i40e_init_module is the first routine called when the driver is
12190 * loaded. All it does is register with the PCI subsystem.
12191 **/
12192static int __init i40e_init_module(void)
12193{
12194 pr_info("%s: %s - version %s\n", i40e_driver_name,
12195 i40e_driver_string, i40e_driver_version_str);
12196 pr_info("%s: %s\n", i40e_driver_name, i40e_copyright);
12197
12198 /* There is no need to throttle the number of active tasks because
12199 * each device limits its own task using a state bit for scheduling
12200 * the service task, and the device tasks do not interfere with each
12201 * other, so we don't set a max task limit. We must set WQ_MEM_RECLAIM
12202 * since we need to be able to guarantee forward progress even under
12203 * memory pressure.
12204 */
12205 i40e_wq = alloc_workqueue("%s", WQ_MEM_RECLAIM, 0, i40e_driver_name);
12206 if (!i40e_wq) {
12207 pr_err("%s: Failed to create workqueue\n", i40e_driver_name);
12208 return -ENOMEM;
12209 }
12210
12211 i40e_dbg_init();
12212 return pci_register_driver(&i40e_driver);
12213}
12214module_init(i40e_init_module);
12215
12216/**
12217 * i40e_exit_module - Driver exit cleanup routine
12218 *
12219 * i40e_exit_module is called just before the driver is removed
12220 * from memory.
12221 **/
12222static void __exit i40e_exit_module(void)
12223{
12224 pci_unregister_driver(&i40e_driver);
12225 destroy_workqueue(i40e_wq);
12226 i40e_dbg_exit();
12227}
12228module_exit(i40e_exit_module);
